:"Spain on a Fork","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Spain on a Fork"},"logo":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.wpengine.com"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Spanish-Style Chickpea Fritters","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Albert Bevia @ Spain on a Fork"},"description":"","datePublished":"2024-03-29T14:00:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/03\\/image8-22-11.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/03\\/image8-22-11-500x500.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/03\\/image8-22-11-500x375.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/03\\/image8-22-11-480x270.png"],"recipeYield":["4"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT15M","recipeIngredient":["1\\/4 cup extra virgin olive oil (60 ml)","1\\/2 cup all purpose flour (60 grams)","1 large egg","1\\/2 cup beer (120 ml)","1 shallot","1 clove garlic","2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley (8 grams)","1\\/2 tsp sweet smoked Spanish paprika (1.25 grams)","1\\/2 tsp ground cumin (1.50 grams)","1 can chickpeas (garbanzo beans) (15.5 oz \\/ 440 grams)","sea salt &amp; black pepper","2 cloves garlic","1\\/4 tsp saffron threads","1\\/2 cup low fat mayonnaise (120 grams)","1 tsp lemon juice (5 ml)","1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil (15 ml)","sea salt &amp; black pepper"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the flour into a large bowl, make a well in the middle, crack in the egg and whisk the egg, then add in the beer and whisk everything together until you a creamy batter","name":"Add the flour into a large bowl, make a well in the middle, crack in the egg and whisk the egg, then add in the beer and whisk everything together until you a creamy batter","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add in the shallot finely chopped, finely grate in the garlic, add in the chopped parsley, sweet smoked Spanish paprika, ground cumin and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together until well mixed","name":"Add in the shallot finely chopped, finely grate in the garlic, add in the chopped parsley, sweet smoked Spanish paprika, ground cumin and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together until well mixed","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Drain the can of chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, then shake off any excess water, transfer the chickpeas into a bowl and using a potato masher or large fork, mash down on the chickpeas until they&#39;re semi-mashed","name":"Drain the can of chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, then shake off any excess water, transfer the chickpeas into a bowl and using a potato masher or large fork, mash down on the chickpeas until they&#39;re semi-mashed","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the mashed chickpeas into the bowl with batter and mix together","name":"Add the mashed chickpeas into the bowl with batter and mix together","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","name":"Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After a couple of minutes start adding in spoonfuls of the batter, all in a single layer and evenly spaced out, cook in batches, fry for 3 minutes per side or until golden fried, transfer into a dish with paper towels as you finish","name":"After a couple of minutes start adding in spoonfuls of the batter, all in a single layer and evenly spaced out, cook in batches, fry for 3 minutes per side or until golden fried, transfer into a dish with paper towels as you finish","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To make the aioli, add in the cloves garlic roughly chopped into a mortar, along with the saffron and a pinch of sea salt, using a pestle pound down on the ingredients until you get a paste-like texture, then add in the mayonnaise, lemon juice, extra virgin olive oil and season with a kiss of sea salt &amp; black pepper, whisk together until you get a creamy sauce","name":"To make the aioli, add in the cloves garlic roughly chopped into a mortar, along with the saffron and a pinch of sea salt, using a pestle pound down on the ingredients until you get a paste-like texture, then add in the mayonnaise, lemon juice, extra virgin olive oil and season with a kiss of sea salt &amp; black pepper, whisk together until you get a creamy sauce","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Transfer the aioli into a serving dish and decorate the fritters around it, serve warm or at room temperature, enjoy!","name":"Transfer the aioli into a serving dish and decorate the fritters around it, serve warm or at room temperature, enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16429-step-0-7"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"1","reviewCount":"1"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"It turned out awesome and it\'s definitely a keeper! Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Vivian Austin"},"datePublished":"2024-04-19"}],"recipeCategory":["Appetizer"],"recipeCuisine":["Spanish"],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"318 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"18 g","proteinContent":"4 g","fatContent":"25 g","saturatedFatContent":"4 g","transFatContent":"0.02 g","cholesterolContent":"51 mg","sodiumContent":"265 mg","fiberContent":"1 g","sugarContent":"2 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"20 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/spanish-style-chickpea-fritters-recipe\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://i0.wp.com/spainonafork.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/image8-22-11.png?fit=750%2C750&ssl=1',
            'ingredients' => '["1\\/4 cup extra virgin olive oil (60 ml)","1\\/2 cup all purpose flour (60 grams)","1 large egg","1\\/2 cup beer (120 ml)","1 shallot","1 clove garlic","2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley (8 grams)","1\\/2 tsp sweet smoked Spanish paprika (1.25 grams)","1\\/2 tsp ground cumin (1.50 grams)","1 can chickpeas (garbanzo beans) (15.5 oz \\/ 440 grams)","sea salt &amp; black pepper","2 cloves garlic","1\\/4 tsp saffron threads","1\\/2 cup low fat mayonnaise (120 grams)","1 tsp lemon juice (5 ml)","1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil (15 ml)","sea salt &amp; black pepper"]',
                'directions' => '["Add the flour into a large bowl, make a well in the middle, crack in the egg and whisk the egg, then add in the beer and whisk everything together until you a creamy batter","Add in the shallot finely chopped, finely grate in the garlic, add in the chopped parsley, sweet smoked Spanish paprika, ground cumin and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together until well mixed","Drain the can of chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, then shake off any excess water, transfer the chickpeas into a bowl and using a potato masher or large fork, mash down on the chickpeas until they&#39;re semi-mashed","Add the mashed chickpeas into the bowl with batter and mix together","Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","After a couple of minutes start adding in spoonfuls of the batter, all in a single layer and evenly spaced out, cook in batches, fry for 3 minutes per side or until golden fried, transfer into a dish with paper towels as you finish","To make the aioli, add in the cloves garlic roughly chopped into a mortar, along with the saffron and a pinch of sea salt, using a pestle pound down on the ingredients until you get a paste-like texture, then add in the mayonnaise, lemon juice, extra virgin olive oil and season with a kiss of sea salt &amp; black pepper, whisk together until you get a creamy sauce","Transfer the aioli into a serving dish and decorate the fritters around it, serve warm or at room temperature, enjoy!"]',
