#\\/schema\\/person\\/bb7046bf61575d8073e9646a387f53a9","name":"Spain on a Fork","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Spain on a Fork"},"logo":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.wpengine.com"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"One-Pan Tomato Chickpea Skillet","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Albert Bevia @ Spain on a Fork"},"description":"","datePublished":"2024-07-15T14:00:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/image3-74-11.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/image3-74-11-500x500.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/image3-74-11-500x375.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/07\\/image3-74-11-480x270.png"],"recipeYield":["4"],"prepTime":"PT5M","cookTime":"PT20M","recipeIngredient":["2 cage-free organic eggs","2 tbsp extra virgin olive oil (35 ml)","1 small onion","5 cloves garlic","1 tbsp sherry vinegar (15 ml)","1 tsp sweet smoked Spanish paprika (2.50 grams)","1\\/2 tsp ground cumin (1.50 grams)","1 can tomato sauce (15 oz \\/ 425 grams)","2 cans chickpeas (garbanzo beans) (15.5 oz \\/ 425 grams)","3 oz fresh spinach (100 grams)","sea salt &amp; black pepper"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the eggs into a sauce pan, fill with enough water to barely cover the eggs, heat with a high heat, once it comes to a boil, place a lid on the pan and turn off the heat, let the eggs sit for 10 to 11 minutes to end up with perfectly hard boiled eggs","name":"Add the eggs into a sauce pan, fill with enough water to barely cover the eggs, heat with a high heat, once it comes to a boil, place a lid on the pan and turn off the heat, let the eggs sit for 10 to 11 minutes to end up with perfectly hard boiled eggs","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16769-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In the meantime, drain the cans of chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, roughly chop the spinach, finely chop the onion and thinly slice the garlic","name":"In the meantime, drain the cans of chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, roughly chop the spinach, finely chop the onion and thinly slice the garlic","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16769-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","name":"Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16769-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After a couple of minutes add in the chopped onion and garlic, mix continuously, after 3 to 4 minutes and the onion is translucent, add in the sherry vinegar, paprika and cumin, quickly mix together, then add in the drained chickpeas, canned tomato sauce and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together, then place a lid on the pan and lower to a low medium heat","name":"After a couple of minutes add in the chopped onion and garlic, mix continuously, after 3 to 4 minutes and the onion is translucent, add in the sherry vinegar, paprika and cumin, quickly mix together, then add in the drained chickpeas, canned tomato sauce and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together, then place a lid on the pan and lower to a low medium heat","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16769-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After simmering the chickpeas for about 10 minutes remove the lid, add in the spinach, all in a flat layer over the tomato chickpeas, place the lid back on the pan and simmer for another 2 to 3 minutes or until the spinach is lightly steamed, then remove the lid and mix everything together until well mixed","name":"After simmering the chickpeas for about 10 minutes remove the lid, add in the spinach, all in a flat layer over the tomato chickpeas, place the lid back on the pan and simmer for another 2 to 3 minutes or until the spinach is lightly steamed, then remove the lid and mix everything together until well mixed","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16769-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve directly out of the pan or transfer into serving dishes, garnished with the hard boiled eggs cut in half, enjoy!","name":"Serve directly out of the pan or transfer into serving dishes, garnished with the hard boiled eggs cut in half, enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16769-step-0-5"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["Spanish"],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"333 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"39 g","proteinContent":"16 g","fatContent":"14 g","saturatedFatContent":"2 g","transFatContent":"0.01 g","cholesterolContent":"82 mg","sodiumContent":"929 mg","fiberContent":"12 g","sugarContent":"5 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"10 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/one-pan-tomato-chickpea-skillet-recipe\\/"}]}',
