spainonafork.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/bb7046bf61575d8073e9646a387f53a9","name":"Spain on a Fork","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Spain on a Fork"},"logo":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.wpengine.com"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Chickpea Meatballs in Tomato Sauce","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Albert Bevia @ Spain on a Fork"},"description":"","datePublished":"2023-12-04T15:00:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/image13-16-11.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/image13-16-11-500x500.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/image13-16-11-500x375.png","https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/image13-16-11-480x270.png"],"recipeYield":["4"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT25M","recipeIngredient":["1 can chickpeas (15.5 oz \\/ 440 grams)","1\\/3 cup bread crumbs (40 grams)","1 egg","1 small onion finey chopped","1 clove garlic","1 carrot","1\\/2 tsp ground cumin (1.5 grams)","2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley (8 grams)","pinch sea salt","dash black pepper","3 cloves garlic finely chopped","1 tsp sweet smoked Spanish paprika (3 grams)","1 can tomato sauce (14.5 oz \\/ 400 grams)","pinch sea salt","dash black pepper","1\\/4 cup extra virgin olive oil (60 ml)","handful chopped fresh parsley"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Drain the canned chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, then shake off any excess water and transfer the chickpeas into a large bowl, using a potato masher or a large fork, mash down on the chickpeas until well mashed","name":"Drain the canned chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, then shake off any excess water and transfer the chickpeas into a large bowl, using a potato masher or a large fork, mash down on the chickpeas until well mashed","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the chickpeas are mashed, add in the bread crumbs, crack in the egg and add in the chopped onion, then finely grate the garlic over the ingredients, finely grate the carrot (peeled), add in the cumin, parsley and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together until well mixed, then push down on the mixture to end up with a paste-like texture","name":"Once the chickpeas are mashed, add in the bread crumbs, crack in the egg and add in the chopped onion, then finely grate the garlic over the ingredients, finely grate the carrot (peeled), add in the cumin, parsley and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together until well mixed, then push down on the mixture to end up with a paste-like texture","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To shape the meatballs, grab a spoonful of the mixture and squeeze it in your hands, this is to ensure the ingredients and well binded together, the form it into a shape of a golf ball","name":"To shape the meatballs, grab a spoonful of the mixture and squeeze it in your hands, this is to ensure the ingredients and well binded together, the form it into a shape of a golf ball","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","name":"Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After a couple of minutes add in the chickpea meatballs, all in a single layer, fry for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden fried all around, then remove from the pan and set aside","name":"After a couple of minutes add in the chickpea meatballs, all in a single layer, fry for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden fried all around, then remove from the pan and set aside","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Using the same pan with the same heat, add in 3 cloves of garlic that have been finely chopped, mix continuously, after 15 seconds add in a generous tsp of sweet smoked Spanish paprika, quickly mix together, then add in the canned tomato sauce and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together and then simmer without mixing","name":"Using the same pan with the same heat, add in 3 cloves of garlic that have been finely chopped, mix continuously, after 15 seconds add in a generous tsp of sweet smoked Spanish paprika, quickly mix together, then add in the canned tomato sauce and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together and then simmer without mixing","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the tomato sauce has slightly thickened, about 3 minutes, add the chickpea meatballs back into the pan, give each one a gentle flip so they\\u00b4re fully coated in the sauce, simmer for 3 to 4 minutes","name":"Once the tomato sauce has slightly thickened, about 3 minutes, add the chickpea meatballs back into the pan, give each one a gentle flip so they\\u00b4re fully coated in the sauce, simmer for 3 to 4 minutes","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Transfer into serving dishes and sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley, enjoy!","name":"Transfer into serving dishes and sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley, enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-16055-step-0-7"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.89","ratingCount":"17","reviewCount":"7"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I didn\\u2019t know what I was expecting, but it wasn\\u2019t this (in the best way)! One of the best recipes I\\u2019ve made in a long time.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Hailey"},"datePublished":"2025-04-16"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Outstanding flavor and a simple quick meal.\\r\\n\\r\\nThanks for the recipe!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jeff"},"datePublished":"2025-02-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Can you make ahead and put in fridge for a few days? Or even freeze? I\'m afraid they won\'t hold together.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Mark"},"datePublished":"2024-10-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We love the Albondigas de Garbanzos so much! Thank you for sharing this recipe, and we will look forward to trying more. My vegetarian friend introduced me to this site.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cynthia"},"datePublished":"2024-05-26"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Just what i was needing. I just made the chickpea balls and used a jar pasta sauce since i had in my pantry. I used a flax egg instead of a chicken egg and i baked the chickpea balls. Perfect! Definitely a keeper. Thank you for sharing.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Bonnie"},"datePublished":"2024-05-11"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Thank you so much for this recipe! My husband is a picky vegetarian who hates to cook, and he could not stop raving about these. I followed the recipe exactly and watched the video. I did not have a can of tomato sauce, so I substituted pureed fire roasted diced tomatoes and the sauce turned out great. Lo aprecio!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Alison M."},"datePublished":"2024-04-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"3"},"reviewBody":"Tastes good, but I would start with 2 eggs, a touch of flour and pulse everything in a food processor. Then I would bake them, because veggie meatballs seldom hold together when frying. You can always brown them in the skillet after baking them.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Barry"},"datePublished":"2024-04-09"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["Spanish"],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"313 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"31 g","proteinContent":"10 g","fatContent":"18 g","saturatedFatContent":"3 g","transFatContent":"0.01 g","cholesterolContent":"41 mg","sodiumContent":"1469 mg","fiberContent":"8 g","sugarContent":"6 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"14 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/chickpea-meatballs-in-tomato-sauce-recipe\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://i0.wp.com/spainonafork.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/image13-16-11.png?fit=750%2C750&ssl=1',
            'ingredients' => '["1 can chickpeas (15.5 oz \\/ 440 grams)","1\\/3 cup bread crumbs (40 grams)","1 egg","1 small onion finey chopped","1 clove garlic","1 carrot","1\\/2 tsp ground cumin (1.5 grams)","2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley (8 grams)","pinch sea salt","dash black pepper","3 cloves garlic finely chopped","1 tsp sweet smoked Spanish paprika (3 grams)","1 can tomato sauce (14.5 oz \\/ 400 grams)","pinch sea salt","dash black pepper","1\\/4 cup extra virgin olive oil (60 ml)","handful chopped fresh parsley"]',
            'directions' => '["Drain the canned chickpeas into a colander and rinse under water, then shake off any excess water and transfer the chickpeas into a large bowl, using a potato masher or a large fork, mash down on the chickpeas until well mashed","Once the chickpeas are mashed, add in the bread crumbs, crack in the egg and add in the chopped onion, then finely grate the garlic over the ingredients, finely grate the carrot (peeled), add in the cumin, parsley and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together until well mixed, then push down on the mixture to end up with a paste-like texture","To shape the meatballs, grab a spoonful of the mixture and squeeze it in your hands, this is to ensure the ingredients and well binded together, the form it into a shape of a golf ball","Heat a large fry pan with a medium heat and add in the olive oil","After a couple of minutes add in the chickpea meatballs, all in a single layer, fry for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden fried all around, then remove from the pan and set aside","Using the same pan with the same heat, add in 3 cloves of garlic that have been finely chopped, mix continuously, after 15 seconds add in a generous tsp of sweet smoked Spanish paprika, quickly mix together, then add in the canned tomato sauce and season with sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together and then simmer without mixing","Once the tomato sauce has slightly thickened, about 3 minutes, add the chickpea meatballs back into the pan, give each one a gentle flip so they\\u00b4re fully coated in the sauce, simmer for 3 to 4 minutes","Transfer into serving dishes and sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley, enjoy!"]',
