,"thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/08\\/THE-BEST-GRILLABLE-Veggie-Burgers-Hearty-flavorful-and-hold-up-on-the-grill-or-skillet-vegan-veggieburger-grilling-dinner-healthy-744x1024-1.jpg","datePublished":"2015-08-01T12:00:55+00:00","dateModified":"2025-05-01T14:33:02+00:00","description":"Easy, grillable veggie burgers with just 10 ingredients (give or take a spice)! Flavorful, hearty, and perfect for summertime grilling.","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/08\\/THE-BEST-GRILLABLE-Veggie-Burgers-Hearty-flavorful-and-hold-up-on-the-grill-or-skillet-vegan-veggieburger-grilling-dinner-healthy-744x1024-1.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/08\\/THE-BEST-GRILLABLE-Veggie-Burgers-Hearty-flavorful-and-hold-up-on-the-grill-or-skillet-vegan-veggieburger-grilling-dinner-healthy-744x1024-1.jpg","width":1456,"height":2184,"caption":"Collection of grilled Veggie Burgers for a healthy vegan summertime recipe"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Easy Grillable Veggie Burgers"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/","name":"Minimalist Baker","description":"Simple Food, Simply Delicious","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#organization","name":"Minimalist Baker","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/04\\/logo@2x.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/04\\/logo@2x.png","width":660,"height":226,"caption":"Minimalist Baker"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/MinimalistBaker","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/minimalistbaker","https:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/minimalistbaker\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/minimalistbaker\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/c\\/Minimalistbaker"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/ed5ce1b1862e6237956babab32d2dc56","name":"Dana @ Minimalist Baker","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/a37a7f43d1ca99ce8fb4cc1b0998963b6f234a7fc92ed5b5c8957253b3ce8273?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/a37a7f43d1ca99ce8fb4cc1b0998963b6f234a7fc92ed5b5c8957253b3ce8273?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/a37a7f43d1ca99ce8fb4cc1b0998963b6f234a7fc92ed5b5c8957253b3ce8273?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Dana @ Minimalist Baker"},"description":"Hi, I\'m Dana! I am a food stylist, photographer, creator of the Food Photography School, and author of the 31 Meals Cookbook and Everyday Cooking. Find me on Twitter, Instagram, and Pinterest."},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Easy Grillable Veggie Burgers","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Minimalist Baker"},"description":"Easy, grillable veggie burgers with just 10 ingredients (give or take a spice)! Flavorful, hearty, and perfect for summertime grilling. Hearty enough to please meat-eaters and vegans alike!","datePublished":"2015-08-01T05:00:55+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/07\\/GRILLABLE-VEGGIE-BURGERS-SQUARE.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Easy Grillable Veggie Burgers | Minimalist Baker Recipes","description":"Easy, grillable veggie burgers with just 10 ingredients (give or take a spice)! Flavorful, hearty and perfect for summertime grilling. Hearty enough to please meat-eaters and vegans alike!\\n\\nFull Recipe: https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/\\n \\nFOLLOW US!\\nBlog: http:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/\\nInstagram: https:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/minimalistbaker\\/\\nTwitter: https:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/minimalistbaker\\nFacebook: https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/MinimalistBaker","uploadDate":"2020-01-09T09:00:06+00:00","duration":"PT58S","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/i.ytimg.com\\/vi\\/Zq1h-jscXPo\\/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/Zq1h-jscXPo?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=Zq1h-jscXPo","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["5","5 (burgers)"],"prepTime":"PT20M","cookTime":"PT10M","totalTime":"PT30M","recipeIngredient":["1 cup cooked brown rice*","1 cup raw walnuts ((or sub bread crumbs))","1\\/2 Tbsp avocado oil ((plus more for cooking))","1\\/2 medium white onion ((finely diced \\/\\/ 1\\/2 onion yields ~3\\/4 cup))","1 Tbsp each chili powder blend, cumin powder, and smoked paprika","1\\/2 tsp each sea salt and black pepper ((plus more for coating burgers))","1 Tbsp coconut sugar ((or sub organic brown or muscovado sugar))","1 \\u00bd cups cooked black beans* ((well rinsed, drained and patted dry))","1\\/3 cup panko bread crumbs ((if gluten-free, use gluten-free bread crumbs))","3-4 Tbsp vegan BBQ sauce"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"If your brown rice isn\\u2019t cooked yet, start there by following\\u00a0this method\\u00a0for the best results. Otherwise, move onto the next step.","name":"If your brown rice isn\\u2019t cooked yet, start there by following\\u00a0this method\\u00a0for the best results. Otherwise, move onto the next step.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add raw walnuts and toast for 5-7 minutes, stirring frequently, until fragrant and golden brown. Let cool and move onto the next step.","name":"Heat skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add raw walnuts and toast for 5-7 minutes, stirring frequently, until fragrant and golden brown. Let cool and move onto the next step.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In the meantime, heat the same skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add oil and onion. Season with a bit of salt and pepper and saut\\u00e9 for 3-4 minutes, or until onion is fragrant, soft, and translucent. Remove from heat and set aside.","name":"In the meantime, heat the same skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add oil and onion. Season with a bit of salt and pepper and saut\\u00e9 for 3-4 minutes, or until onion is fragrant, soft, and translucent. Remove from heat and set aside.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once walnuts are cooled, add to\\u00a0blender\\u00a0or\\u00a0food processor\\u00a0with chili powder, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, pepper and coconut sugar and blend until a fine meal (see photo) is achieved. Set aside.","name":"Once walnuts are cooled, add to\\u00a0blender\\u00a0or\\u00a0food processor\\u00a0with chili powder, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, pepper and coconut sugar and blend until a fine meal (see photo) is achieved. Set aside.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To a large mixing bowl, add drained, dried black beans and mash well with a fork, leaving only a few whole beans (see photo).","name":"To a large mixing bowl, add drained, dried black beans and mash well with a fork, leaving only a few whole beans (see photo).","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Next add cooked rice, spice-walnut mixture, saut\\u00e9ed onion, panko bread crumbs, BBQ sauce, and mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon for 1-2 minutes, or until a moldable dough forms. If dry, add an extra 1-2 Tbsp BBQ sauce (amount as original recipe is written \\/\\/ adjust if altering batch size). If too wet, add more panko bread crumbs. Taste and adjust seasonings as needed.","name":"Next add cooked rice, spice-walnut mixture, saut\\u00e9ed onion, panko bread crumbs, BBQ sauce, and mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon for 1-2 minutes, or until a moldable dough forms. If dry, add an extra 1-2 Tbsp BBQ sauce (amount as original recipe is written \\/\\/ adjust if altering batch size). If too wet, add more panko bread crumbs. Taste and adjust seasonings as needed.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"For larger burgers, divide into 5 patties (1\\/2 cup in size \\/\\/ amount as original recipe is written), or form 10 smaller burgers (1\\/4 cup in size \\/\\/ amount as original recipe is written). To help form the patties, line your 1\\/2 or 1\\/4 measuring cup with plastic wrap and pack with burger mixture. Press down to pack firmly, then lift out by the plastic wrap\\u2019s edge, and slightly flatten with hands to form a 3\\/4-inch thick patty. Set on a baking sheet or plate for grilling.","name":"For larger burgers, divide into 5 patties (1\\/2 cup in size \\/\\/ amount as original recipe is written), or form 10 smaller burgers (1\\/4 cup in size \\/\\/ amount as original recipe is written). To help form the patties, line your 1\\/2 or 1\\/4 measuring cup with plastic wrap and pack with burger mixture. Press down to pack firmly, then lift out by the plastic wrap\\u2019s edge, and slightly flatten with hands to form a 3\\/4-inch thick patty. Set on a baking sheet or plate for grilling.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"If grilling, heat the grill at this time and brush the grill surface with oil to ease cooking. Otherwise, heat the same skillet you used earlier to medium heat.","name":"If grilling, heat the grill at this time and brush the grill surface with oil to ease cooking. Otherwise, heat the same skillet you used earlier to medium heat.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-7"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once skillet is hot, add just enough oil to lightly coat the bottom of your skillet, then add your burgers - only as many as will comfortably fit in the pan. Otherwise, add burgers to the grill and close lid.","name":"Once skillet is hot, add just enough oil to lightly coat the bottom of your skillet, then add your burgers - only as many as will comfortably fit in the pan. Otherwise, add burgers to the grill and close lid.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-8"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cook for 3-4 minutes or until well browned on the underside, then flip gently. They aren\'t as firm as meat burgers, but will definitely hold their shape. Reduce heat if cooking\\/browning too quickly. Cook for 3-4 minutes on other side.","name":"Cook for 3-4 minutes or until well browned on the underside, then flip gently. They aren\'t as firm as meat burgers, but will definitely hold their shape. Reduce heat if cooking\\/browning too quickly. Cook for 3-4 minutes on other side.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-9"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove burgers from heat to let cool slightly, and prepare any other toppings\\/sides at this time (such as grilling\\/toasting your buns).","name":"Remove burgers from heat to let cool slightly, and prepare any other toppings\\/sides at this time (such as grilling\\/toasting your buns).","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-10"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve burgers as is, or on toasted buns with desired toppings. Leftovers keep in the refrigerator for 2-3 days. See notes for freezing\\/reheating instructions.","name":"Serve burgers as is, or on toasted buns with desired toppings. Leftovers keep in the refrigerator for 2-3 days. See notes for freezing\\/reheating instructions.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#wprm-recipe-35537-step-0-11"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.82","ratingCount":"524","reviewCount":"8"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I have made this recipe multiple times and my family loves it. In fact, this is my go-to veggie burger recipe! We are having a big group of people over on Sunday and I would like to make these, but is there any way I could bake them in the oven instead of grilling them so that I could do more at one time? Please let me know you\'re a recommendations.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sonali"},"datePublished":"2026-07-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I have made a lot of veggie burgers and these are the most impressive by far. They held together perfectly on a flat griddle. We have a nut allergy in our house so I toasted raw sunflower seeds instead of the walnuts, and judging by the video, I still got the desired effect. I will be making these again!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kirsten Vogel"},"datePublished":"2026-07-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"3"},"reviewBody":"These were good but still melted in your mouth like other veggie burgers. Wish the end result was a little chewy :( not sure if it\\u2019s possible to achieve this without an egg.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Victoria"},"datePublished":"2026-07-06"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I really loved the taste of this. I didn\'t have 1 cup of walnuts so I added chopped sliced almonds, and when I was sauteing the onions, I added the spices there to allow the heat to give the spices more of a robust flavor. I added garlic powder and some sauted minced cloves. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe burger broke up quite a bit as I was eating it on a bun. I had sauteed it in a frying pan in olive oil. Would adding more of one ingredient help with the binding (mashed beans or the bread crumbs?). Also, would refrigerating the mix before cooking help?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cynthia"},"datePublished":"2026-07-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Holy moly! This is incredible and will be my new base for BBB\'s! I am not vegetarian but love a good BBB and this one may be the best ever. I am bringing these &amp; the sweet potato ones (slider sized) to a neighborhood 4th of July gathering with several people who are plant based, have food allergies or are sensitive to animal products due to tick bites. I think I will use more traditional burger seasonings for that event (herbs &amp; spices in Montreal steak seasoning). I fully expect them to be a huge hit. I also can\'t wait to make these for my bonus son who is vegan and one of my best friends who\'s vegetarian. 100*\'s! Thank you for being a reliable source for recipes.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Joanne"},"datePublished":"2026-07-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was my favourite patty recipe a while back - it\'s not super complicated but it\'s so good. The patty stays together, even under grilling, freezes well and even my meat-eating partner liked it. \\r\\n\\r\\nI recently realised I hadn\'t made it a while and had been bereft and desperately web searching with all the ingredients I could remember ever since. So glad I managed to find it - will be printing this out for safety immediately!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Chloe Sutherland"},"datePublished":"2026-06-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"These are the best veggie burgers I\'ve ever made. I added 8 oz of chopped baby bella mushrooms to the onions and sauteed them. I should be noted that \\"grillable\\" was not true (the added mushrooms could have been a factor -- they didn\'t hold up well on the grill grate) but when we moved them to stove to pan-fry, problem solved. Please keep giving your excellent recipes! I\'ve tried many and they\'re all five stars but this is my first review.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kat"},"datePublished":"2026-05-25"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Delicious! Cooked up well, very happy with these! Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lisa"},"datePublished":"2026-05-21"}],"recipeCategory":["Entr\\u00e9e"],"recipeCuisine":["Gluten-Free","Vegan"],"keywords":"veggie burger","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 burger","calories":"314 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"36.5 g","proteinContent":"9.4 g","fatContent":"15.9 g","saturatedFatContent":"1.6 g","sodiumContent":"550 mg","fiberContent":"8.4 g","sugarContent":"5.4 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"13.38 g"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/easy-grillable-veggie-burgers\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://minimalistbaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/THE-BEST-GRILLABLE-Veggie-Burgers-Hearty-flavorful-and-hold-up-on-the-grill-or-skillet-vegan-veggieburger-grilling-dinner-healthy-744x1024-1.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["1 cup cooked brown rice*","1 cup raw walnuts ((or sub bread crumbs))","1\\/2 Tbsp avocado oil ((plus more for cooking))","1\\/2 medium white onion ((finely diced \\/\\/ 1\\/2 onion yields ~3\\/4 cup))","1 Tbsp each chili powder blend, cumin powder, and smoked paprika","1\\/2 tsp each sea salt and black pepper ((plus more for coating burgers))","1 Tbsp coconut sugar ((or sub organic brown or muscovado sugar))","1 \\u00bd cups cooked black beans* ((well rinsed, drained and patted dry))","1\\/3 cup panko bread crumbs ((if gluten-free, use gluten-free bread crumbs))","3-4 Tbsp vegan BBQ sauce"]',
            'directions' => '["If your brown rice isn\\u2019t cooked yet, start there by following\\u00a0this method\\u00a0for the best results. Otherwise, move onto the next step.","Heat skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add raw walnuts and toast for 5-7 minutes, stirring frequently, until fragrant and golden brown. Let cool and move onto the next step.","In the meantime, heat the same skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add oil and onion. Season with a bit of salt and pepper and saut\\u00e9 for 3-4 minutes, or until onion is fragrant, soft, and translucent. Remove from heat and set aside.","Once walnuts are cooled, add to\\u00a0blender\\u00a0or\\u00a0food processor\\u00a0with chili powder, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, pepper and coconut sugar and blend until a fine meal (see photo) is achieved. Set aside.","To a large mixing bowl, add drained, dried black beans and mash well with a fork, leaving only a few whole beans (see photo).","Next add cooked rice, spice-walnut mixture, saut\\u00e9ed onion, panko bread crumbs, BBQ sauce, and mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon for 1-2 minutes, or until a moldable dough forms. If dry, add an extra 1-2 Tbsp BBQ sauce (amount as original recipe is written \\/\\/ adjust if altering batch size). If too wet, add more panko bread crumbs. Taste and adjust seasonings as needed.","For larger burgers, divide into 5 patties (1\\/2 cup in size \\/\\/ amount as original recipe is written), or form 10 smaller burgers (1\\/4 cup in size \\/\\/ amount as original recipe is written). To help form the patties, line your 1\\/2 or 1\\/4 measuring cup with plastic wrap and pack with burger mixture. Press down to pack firmly, then lift out by the plastic wrap\\u2019s edge, and slightly flatten with hands to form a 3\\/4-inch thick patty. Set on a baking sheet or plate for grilling.","If grilling, heat the grill at this time and brush the grill surface with oil to ease cooking. Otherwise, heat the same skillet you used earlier to medium heat.","Once skillet is hot, add just enough oil to lightly coat the bottom of your skillet, then add your burgers - only as many as will comfortably fit in the pan. Otherwise, add burgers to the grill and close lid.","Cook for 3-4 minutes or until well browned on the underside, then flip gently. They aren\'t as firm as meat burgers, but will definitely hold their shape. Reduce heat if cooking\\/browning too quickly. Cook for 3-4 minutes on other side.","Remove burgers from heat to let cool slightly, and prepare any other toppings\\/sides at this time (such as grilling\\/toasting your buns).","Serve burgers as is, or on toasted buns with desired toppings. Leftovers keep in the refrigerator for 2-3 days. See notes for freezing\\/reheating instructions."]',
                'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 burger","calories":"314 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"36.5 g","proteinContent":"9.4 g","fatContent":"15.9 g","saturatedFatContent":"1.6 g","sodiumContent":"550 mg","fiberContent":"8.4 g","sugarContent":"5.4 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"13.38 g"}]',
