 Make New York Deli Cucumber Salad","description":"Today we\'re making deli-style cucumber salad. We hope you enjoy the video!\\n\\nTHE SIP AND FEAST PODCAST YOUTUBE CHANNEL:\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/channel\\/UC05WUqc7GiWsUKMAX6jBJoQ\\n\\nSUPPORT ON PATREON:\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.patreon.com\\/sipandfeast\\n\\nMY AMAZON STORE (This is an affiliate link) \\nhttps:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/shop\\/sipandfeast\\n\\n****PRINT RECIPE WITH INSTRUCTIONS AND PROCESS SHOTS****\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.sipandfeast.com\\/cucumber-salad\\/\\n\\nINGREDIENTS WITH GRAM AMOUNTS \\n4 large English cucumbers - thinly sliced (can peel if you like)\\n1 medium sweet onion - sliced\\n1\\/4 teaspoon white pepper\\n3\\/4 teaspoon salt\\n2 cups (480g) white vinegar\\n1 cup (240g) cold water\\n1 cup (200g) sugar\\n2 tablespoons fresh dill - minced\\n\\nFOLLOW ME ON INSTAGRAM:\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/sipandfeast\\/\\n\\nDisclosure:\\nI am a participant in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program. As an Amazon Associate, I earn from qualifying purchases.","uploadDate":"2023-09-07T14:30:06+00:00","duration":"PT9M17S","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/i.ytimg.com\\/vi\\/iQv9Y6-khoU\\/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/iQv9Y6-khoU?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=iQv9Y6-khoU","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["10"],"prepTime":"PT25M","cookTime":"PT5M","totalTime":"PT150M","recipeIngredient":["4 large English cucumbers (thinly sliced)","1 medium sweet onion (sliced)","1\\/4 teaspoon white pepper","3\\/4 teaspoon salt","2 cups white vinegar","1 cup cold water","1 cup sugar","2 tablespoons minced fresh dill"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Slice the cucumbers and onion and spread onto a baking tray or large flat surface. Sprinkle the salt and pepper all over the cucumbers and let them sit for 15 minutes.","name":"Slice the cucumbers and onion and spread onto a baking tray or large flat surface. Sprinkle the salt and pepper all over the cucumbers and let them sit for 15 minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.sipandfeast.com\\/cucumber-salad\\/#wprm-recipe-19151-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Combine the sugar and vinegar in a saucepot and bring to a boil. Once dissolved turn the heat off and add 1 cup of cold water to the pot. Let the mixture cool down.","name":"Combine the sugar and vinegar in a saucepot and bring to a boil. Once dissolved turn the heat off and add 1 cup of cold water to the pot. Let the mixture cool down.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.sipandfeast.com\\/cucumber-salad\\/#wprm-recipe-19151-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the cucumbers into a flat baking dish and pour over the vinegar mixture and mix in the dill. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours but preferably overnight. At the halfway point, mix the cucumber salad and return to the fridge. Enjoy!","name":"Place the cucumbers into a flat baking dish and pour over the vinegar mixture and mix in the dill. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours but preferably overnight. At the halfway point, mix the cucumber salad and return to the fridge. Enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/www.sipandfeast.com\\/cucumber-salad\\/#wprm-recipe-19151-step-0-2"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"13","reviewCount":"6"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Reminds me of when I was living in LI! Excellent!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Bob in AZ"},"datePublished":"2026-05-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"GREAT LOOING PRESENTATION AND FLAVOR","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Diane Juell"},"datePublished":"2025-08-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"It was so delicious. When cold, very refreshing. Even the kids liked it. I also put in some hot pepper flakes. It added a bit of a kick. Good job!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cheri"},"datePublished":"2025-07-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is the perfect cucumber salad!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Debbie"},"datePublished":"2025-06-06"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"It all looks so good I going to try some of them. Think you for posting them.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Wanda"},"datePublished":"2025-05-22"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is become my new go to recipe for a quick and impressive \\u201cpickle\\u201d that is always a crowd favorite. I kick it up a notch by adding Serano peppers, we are on the West Coast after all. What I love about this recipe is how simple it is how delicious it is how adaptable it is and if one stick strictly to the recipe how authentic it is in terms of a New York deli style cucumber salad. Absolutely fabulous!\\nKeep up the good work, James and Tara. Really appreciate you.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jennifer Smith"},"datePublished":"2025-05-19"}],"recipeCategory":["Salad"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"keywords":"cucumber salad, ny deli cucumber salad","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"138 kcal","saturatedFatContent":"0.1 g","sodiumContent":"224 mg","carbohydrateContent":"33.2 g","fiberContent":"1.2 g","sugarContent":"28.8 g","proteinContent":"1.3 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.sipandfeast.com\\/cucumber-salad\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.sipandfeast.com\\/cucumber-salad\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.sipandfeast.com\\/cucumber-salad\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://www.sipandfeast.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/cucumber-salad-recipe-snippet-3.jpg',
