                'user_id' => 1,
                'description' => 'These Creamy Harissa Aubergine Beans are so delicious, they are warming, cosy, lightly spiced and packed with flavour. They are high in plant-based protein, naturally vegan, gluten-free and easy to make in 30 minutes.',
            'content' => '{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"Recipe","name":"Creamy Harissa Aubergine Beans (Vegan High-Protein)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Nourishing Amy"},"datePublished":"2023-11-25","recipeYield":4,"description":"These Creamy Harissa Aubergine Beans are so delicious, they are warming, cosy, lightly spiced and packed with flavour. They are high in plant-based protein, naturally vegan, gluten-free and easy to make in 30 minutes.","image":["https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/Creamy-Harissa-Aubergine-Beans-6-720x720.jpg","https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/Creamy-Harissa-Aubergine-Beans-6-720x540.jpg","https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/Creamy-Harissa-Aubergine-Beans-6-540x720.jpg","https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/Creamy-Harissa-Aubergine-Beans-6-720x405.jpg","https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/11\\/Creamy-Harissa-Aubergine-Beans-6-735x1103.jpg"],"recipeCategory":"30 Mins or Less","recipeCuisine":"Fusion","prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT20M","performTime":"PT20M","totalTime":"PT30M","recipeIngredient":["1 tbsp olive oil","1 spring onion, chopped","2 garlic cloves, crushed","1 aubergine, chopped into small cubes","160g cherry tomatoes, halved","500g white beans (and their juices)*","Salt and pepper","200g white beans (and their juices)*","60g thick coconut yoghurt","60ml plant-based milk","40g sun-dried tomatoes","1 heaped tsp harissa paste","2 tbsp nutritional yeast","Bread or wholegrains","4 tbsp coconut yoghurt","2-4 tsp harissa paste","Fresh herbs e.g. coriander"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"For the aubergine: heat a large non-stick pan with olive oil and fry off the spring onion and garlic with some salt for 1-2 minutes. Now add the aubergine and continue to fry for 5-10 minutes, until softening, before adding the tomatoes.","position":1,"name":"For the aubergine: heat a large non-stick pan...","url":"https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/2023\\/11\\/27\\/creamy-harissa-aubergine-beans-vegan-high-protein\\/#mv_create_267_1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Meanwhile make the sauce: add all of the ingredients to a small blender and process until creamy, seasoning to taste.","position":2,"name":"Meanwhile make the sauce: add all of the...","url":"https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/2023\\/11\\/27\\/creamy-harissa-aubergine-beans-vegan-high-protein\\/#mv_create_267_2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Into the aubergine pan: add the beans and their juices and all of the creamy harissa sauce. Stir well and bring to a gentle bubble and cook with a lid on for 10 minutes, adding a splash of water, if needed.","position":3,"name":"Into the aubergine pan: add the beans and...","url":"https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/2023\\/11\\/27\\/creamy-harissa-aubergine-beans-vegan-high-protein\\/#mv_create_267_3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To serve: ladle into bowls and top with some yoghurt, harissa paste and fresh herbs and mop up with bread\\/toast or some wholegrains like quinoa or buckwheat.","position":4,"name":"To serve: ladle into bowls and top with...","url":"https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/2023\\/11\\/27\\/creamy-harissa-aubergine-beans-vegan-high-protein\\/#mv_create_267_4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To store: allow to cool fully and keep in a sealed container in the fridge for 2-3 days or in the freezer for 1 month. Allow to defrost before warming back up.","position":5,"name":"To store: allow to cool fully and keep...","url":"https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/2023\\/11\\/27\\/creamy-harissa-aubergine-beans-vegan-high-protein\\/#mv_create_267_5"}],"keywords":"vegan, healthy, beans","suitableForDiet":"VeganDiet","url":"https:\\/\\/nourishingamy.com\\/2023\\/11\\/27\\/creamy-harissa-aubergine-beans-vegan-high-protein\\/","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.5","reviewCount":75}}',
                'image' => 'https://nourishingamy.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Creamy-Harissa-Aubergine-Beans-6-720x720.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["1 tbsp olive oil","1 spring onion, chopped","2 garlic cloves, crushed","1 aubergine, chopped into small cubes","160g cherry tomatoes, halved","500g white beans (and their juices)*","Salt and pepper","200g white beans (and their juices)*","60g thick coconut yoghurt","60ml plant-based milk","40g sun-dried tomatoes","1 heaped tsp harissa paste","2 tbsp nutritional yeast","Bread or wholegrains","4 tbsp coconut yoghurt","2-4 tsp harissa paste","Fresh herbs e.g. coriander"]',
                'directions' => '["For the aubergine: heat a large non-stick pan with olive oil and fry off the spring onion and garlic with some salt for 1-2 minutes. Now add the aubergine and continue to fry for 5-10 minutes, until softening, before adding the tomatoes.","Meanwhile make the sauce: add all of the ingredients to a small blender and process until creamy, seasoning to taste.","Into the aubergine pan: add the beans and their juices and all of the creamy harissa sauce. Stir well and bring to a gentle bubble and cook with a lid on for 10 minutes, adding a splash of water, if needed.","To serve: ladle into bowls and top with some yoghurt, harissa paste and fresh herbs and mop up with bread\\/toast or some wholegrains like quinoa or buckwheat.","To store: allow to cool fully and keep in a sealed container in the fridge for 2-3 days or in the freezer for 1 month. Allow to defrost before warming back up."]',
