rl":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-6.jpg","datePublished":"2024-04-09T08:00:00+00:00","dateModified":"2024-07-30T21:25:01+00:00","description":"20-minute shredded tofu taco \\u201cmeat\\u201d that\'s smoky & spicy! A versatile, protein-packed filling for tacos, bowls, burritos, nachos, and beyond.","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-6.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-6.jpg","width":1456,"height":2184,"caption":"Using a wooden spoon to mix a skillet of our shredded tofu taco meat recipe"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Smoky Shredded Tofu Taco &#8220;Meat&#8221;"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/","name":"Minimalist Baker","description":"Simple Food, Simply Delicious","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#organization","name":"Minimalist Baker","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/04\\/logo@2x.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/04\\/logo@2x.png","width":660,"height":226,"caption":"Minimalist Baker"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/MinimalistBaker","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/minimalistbaker","https:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/minimalistbaker\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/minimalistbaker\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/c\\/Minimalistbaker"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/ed5ce1b1862e6237956babab32d2dc56","name":"Dana @ Minimalist Baker","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/a37a7f43d1ca99ce8fb4cc1b0998963b6f234a7fc92ed5b5c8957253b3ce8273?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/a37a7f43d1ca99ce8fb4cc1b0998963b6f234a7fc92ed5b5c8957253b3ce8273?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/a37a7f43d1ca99ce8fb4cc1b0998963b6f234a7fc92ed5b5c8957253b3ce8273?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Dana @ Minimalist Baker"},"description":"Hi, I\'m Dana! I am a food stylist, photographer, creator of the Food Photography School, and author of the 31 Meals Cookbook and Everyday Cooking. Find me on Twitter, Instagram, and Pinterest."},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Smoky Shredded Tofu Taco \\u201cMeat\\u201d","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Minimalist Baker"},"description":"Smoky, spicy shredded tofu taco \\u201cmeat\\u201d! A versatile, protein-packed filling for tacos, bowls, burritos, nachos, and beyond. Just 10 ingredients and 20 minutes required!","datePublished":"2024-04-09T03:00:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-SQUARE.jpg","https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-SQUARE-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-SQUARE-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-SQUARE-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["4","4 (~3\\/4-cup servings)"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT10M","totalTime":"PT20M","recipeIngredient":["2 Tbsp olive or avocado oil","1\\/2 large onion (any color), finely diced ((1\\/2 onion yields ~1 \\u00bc cups or 180 g))","1 large red bell pepper, finely diced ((1 pepper yields ~1 \\u00bc cups or 120 g))","1 medium jalape\\u00f1o, finely diced, seeds removed ((1 jalape\\u00f1o yields ~1\\/3 cup or 60 g))","4 medium cloves garlic, minced","1 Tbsp chili powder ((or store-bought))","1 \\u00bd tsp smoked paprika","3\\/4 tsp sea salt","2-3 Tbsp adobo sauce ((from a can of chipotle peppers in adobo \\/\\/ optionally, for more heat, add 1\\/2-1 chipotle pepper, finely diced))","1\\/4 cup water ((plus more as needed))","16 oz. super firm high protein tofu, drained and shredded","Tortillas (for tacos or burritos), rice (for bowls) or tortilla chips (for nachos)","Lettuce","Tomatoes","Cilantro","Guacamole ((or Easy Vegan Avocado Crema))","Salsa"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"If you haven\\u2019t already shredded your tofu, do so now. Drain the tofu and pat dry. Then, using the largest side of a box grater, shred the tofu and set aside.","name":"If you haven\\u2019t already shredded your tofu, do so now. Drain the tofu and pat dry. Then, using the largest side of a box grater, shred the tofu and set aside.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#wprm-recipe-119219-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and cook for 3-5 minutes, until soft, translucent, and beginning to brown.","name":"Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and cook for 3-5 minutes, until soft, translucent, and beginning to brown.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#wprm-recipe-119219-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add bell peppers and jalape\\u00f1os and cook for another 2-3 minutes, until softened. Add the garlic and toss to combine. Then add the chili powder, smoked paprika, and salt. Mix to evenly coat the veggies in the spices, then add the adobo sauce, optional chipotle pepper, and water and mix once more.","name":"Add bell peppers and jalape\\u00f1os and cook for another 2-3 minutes, until softened. Add the garlic and toss to combine. Then add the chili powder, smoked paprika, and salt. Mix to evenly coat the veggies in the spices, then add the adobo sauce, optional chipotle pepper, and water and mix once more.","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#wprm-recipe-119219-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the tofu to the saucy veggies and toss to evenly coat. Spread the tofu into an even layer, turn the heat up slightly, and cook for 2-3 minutes until the bottom of the tofu begins to sizzle. Stir the tofu and scrape up any browned bits. Taste and adjust as needed, adding more water if too dry, adobo sauce for more heat\\/smokiness (we added the full amount), or more salt to taste. If the tofu is too wet, continue to cook uncovered to evaporate any extra liquid (we didn\\u2019t find this necessary!).","name":"Add the tofu to the saucy veggies and toss to evenly coat. Spread the tofu into an even layer, turn the heat up slightly, and cook for 2-3 minutes until the bottom of the tofu begins to sizzle. Stir the tofu and scrape up any browned bits. Taste and adjust as needed, adding more water if too dry, adobo sauce for more heat\\/smokiness (we added the full amount), or more salt to taste. If the tofu is too wet, continue to cook uncovered to evaporate any extra liquid (we didn\\u2019t find this necessary!).","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#wprm-recipe-119219-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Enjoy! We love serving this tofu in bowls with beans, rice, roasted sweet potatoes, and guacamole, or in tacos topped with guacamole and slaw. This tofu also makes a delicious topping for nachos!","name":"Enjoy! We love serving this tofu in bowls with beans, rice, roasted sweet potatoes, and guacamole, or in tacos topped with guacamole and slaw. This tofu also makes a delicious topping for nachos!","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#wprm-recipe-119219-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Leftovers keep in a sealed container in the refrigerator for 3-4 days or in the freezer for 1 month (or longer).","name":"Leftovers keep in a sealed container in the refrigerator for 3-4 days or in the freezer for 1 month (or longer).","url":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#wprm-recipe-119219-step-0-5"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"4","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Yum!! This was easy, quick, and delicious for a hot lunch of soft tacos. I added vegan cheese and shredded lettuce to the tacos. This was my first time shredding tofu and I will be doing it more often now. Another time I might make it a bit eggier with black salt and nutritional yeast and put it in a breakfast burrito. It\\u2019s perfect the way it is, but I can see it could be easily modified for whatever flavors I\\u2019m going for. Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Toni"},"datePublished":"2025-10-26"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was nice! I expected it to be a bit more chewy, but it was very like scrambled egg (as another person said). It needed more texture the way that I served it (in a wrap, with avocado). \\r\\n\\r\\nNext time I\'d pair it with something crunchier, like chickpeas, shredded red cabbage with lime\\/cilantro, and\\/or baked yam. First time shredding tofu so thanks for this idea!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Megan"},"datePublished":"2025-03-11"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"My wife and I have just begun to add plant-based meals to our diet, this being our second entree. I made soft tacos last night with corn tortillas using this recipe for the filling. The recipe was easy to follow and the results were amazing! The only modification was adding the juice of one lime at the end after everything was combined. We were so happy with the flavor that we did not use the vegan cheese that I bought to go with the tacos.\\r\\nI must admit that I had never cooked with tofu so I was a little apprehensive about how the texture would turn out. For us, the texture of the tofu was kind of like scrambled eggs - not a bad thing, just different from the beef and fish we have used in the past. When I asked my wife if I should make these again she said definitely!!! I agree. Thanks again for posting these delicious recipes!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Mark S"},"datePublished":"2024-07-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Loved it! Came together pretty easily and super tasty. My one modification that helped a lot is that I added a little lime juice in the dish and served with lime wedges","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Emily"},"datePublished":"2024-04-14"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course","Protein"],"recipeCuisine":["Gluten-Free","Mexican-Inspired","Vegan"],"keywords":"shredded tofu, shredded tofu tacos, tofu taco meat","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 serving","calories":"267 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"11.9 g","proteinContent":"19.1 g","fatContent":"16.1 g","saturatedFatContent":"2.8 g","sodiumContent":"547 mg","fiberContent":"5.1 g","sugarContent":"4.2 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"6.1 g"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/minimalistbaker.com\\/smoky-shredded-tofu-taco-meat\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://minimalistbaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Smoky-Shredded-Tofu-Vegan-Taco-Meat-6.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["2 Tbsp olive or avocado oil","1\\/2 large onion (any color), finely diced ((1\\/2 onion yields ~1 \\u00bc cups or 180 g))","1 large red bell pepper, finely diced ((1 pepper yields ~1 \\u00bc cups or 120 g))","1 medium jalape\\u00f1o, finely diced, seeds removed ((1 jalape\\u00f1o yields ~1\\/3 cup or 60 g))","4 medium cloves garlic, minced","1 Tbsp chili powder ((or store-bought))","1 \\u00bd tsp smoked paprika","3\\/4 tsp sea salt","2-3 Tbsp adobo sauce ((from a can of chipotle peppers in adobo \\/\\/ optionally, for more heat, add 1\\/2-1 chipotle pepper, finely diced))","1\\/4 cup water ((plus more as needed))","16 oz. super firm high protein tofu, drained and shredded","Tortillas (for tacos or burritos), rice (for bowls) or tortilla chips (for nachos)","Lettuce","Tomatoes","Cilantro","Guacamole ((or Easy Vegan Avocado Crema))","Salsa"]',
            'directions' => '["If you haven\\u2019t already shredded your tofu, do so now. Drain the tofu and pat dry. Then, using the largest side of a box grater, shred the tofu and set aside.","Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and cook for 3-5 minutes, until soft, translucent, and beginning to brown.","Add bell peppers and jalape\\u00f1os and cook for another 2-3 minutes, until softened. Add the garlic and toss to combine. Then add the chili powder, smoked paprika, and salt. Mix to evenly coat the veggies in the spices, then add the adobo sauce, optional chipotle pepper, and water and mix once more.","Add the tofu to the saucy veggies and toss to evenly coat. Spread the tofu into an even layer, turn the heat up slightly, and cook for 2-3 minutes until the bottom of the tofu begins to sizzle. Stir the tofu and scrape up any browned bits. Taste and adjust as needed, adding more water if too dry, adobo sauce for more heat\\/smokiness (we added the full amount), or more salt to taste. If the tofu is too wet, continue to cook uncovered to evaporate any extra liquid (we didn\\u2019t find this necessary!).","Enjoy! We love serving this tofu in bowls with beans, rice, roasted sweet potatoes, and guacamole, or in tacos topped with guacamole and slaw. This tofu also makes a delicious topping for nachos!","Leftovers keep in a sealed container in the refrigerator for 3-4 days or in the freezer for 1 month (or longer)."]',
                'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 serving","calories":"267 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"11.9 g","proteinContent":"19.1 g","fatContent":"16.1 g","saturatedFatContent":"2.8 g","sodiumContent":"547 mg","fiberContent":"5.1 g","sugarContent":"4.2 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"6.1 g"}]',
