d Paella Recipe is loaded with flavor and easier to make than you think. Surprise yourself and your guest with this seafood paella recipe from Valencia, Spain.","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/i0.wp.com\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/02\\/paella3-11.png?fit=750%2C750&ssl=1","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/i0.wp.com\\/spainonafork.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/02\\/paella3-11.png?fit=750%2C750&ssl=1","width":750,"height":750,"caption":"Authentic Spanish Seafood Paella Recipe"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Authentic Spanish Seafood Paella Recipe"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/","name":"Spain on a Fork","description":"Easy to Make Spanish Recipes","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/bb7046bf61575d8073e9646a387f53a9"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":["Person","Organization"],"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/bb7046bf61575d8073e9646a387f53a9","name":"Spain on a Fork","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Spain on a Fork"},"logo":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/1e8709ffbf762ce98cf11b19eed76154f6088c5b0eb5ff06afbe0fec31ed969c?s=96&d=mm&r=g"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/spainonafork.wpengine.com"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Authentic Spanish Seafood Paella","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Albert Bevia @ Spain on a Fork"},"description":"","datePublished":"2018-02-24T23:16:14+00:00","recipeYield":["2"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT35M","recipeIngredient":["3 cloves garlic","1\\/2 onion","1\\/2 red bell pepper","1 tube of squid (cleaned)","12 raw jumbo shrimp (peeled &amp; deveined)","8 fresh mussels (cleaned)","1\\/3 cup extra virgin olive oil (80 ml)","1\\/2 cup tomato sauce (112 grams)","1\\/2 tsp sweet smoked Spanish paprika (1.30 grams)","2 1\\/2 cups fish broth (600 ml)","1\\/4 tsp saffron threads or powder (.17 grams)","1 cup uncooked round rice (200 grams)","2 lemon wedges","handful finely chopped parsley","sea salt &amp; black pepper"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Rouchly chop 3 cloves of garlic, finely dice 1\\/2 onion, finely chop 1\\/2 red bell pepper and cut 1 cleaned tube of squid into small squares","name":"Rouchly chop 3 cloves of garlic, finely dice 1\\/2 onion, finely chop 1\\/2 red bell pepper and cut 1 cleaned tube of squid into small squares","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-12640-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat a paella pan with a medium-high heat and add in 1\\/3 cup extra virgin olive oil, after 1 minute season the olive oil with sea salt and add in the cut squid, mix with the olive oil and cook for 1 1\\/2 to 2 minutes, then remove from the pan and set aside, then add in the diced onion &amp; chopped garlic into the pan, mix with the olive oil, after 1 minute add in the chopped bell pepper and continue to mix so everything evenly sautees","name":"Heat a paella pan with a medium-high heat and add in 1\\/3 cup extra virgin olive oil, after 1 minute season the olive oil with sea salt and add in the cut squid, mix with the olive oil and cook for 1 1\\/2 to 2 minutes, then remove from the pan and set aside, then add in the diced onion &amp; chopped garlic into the pan, mix with the olive oil, after 1 minute add in the chopped bell pepper and continue to mix so everything evenly sautees","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-12640-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After 3 minutes, add in 1\\/2 cup tomato sauce and season everything with 1\\/2 tsp sweet smoked paprika, sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together, after 2 minutes and the tomato sauce has thickened, add the squid back into the pan, mix together, then add in 2 1\\/2 cups fish broth and the saffron","name":"After 3 minutes, add in 1\\/2 cup tomato sauce and season everything with 1\\/2 tsp sweet smoked paprika, sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together, after 2 minutes and the tomato sauce has thickened, add the squid back into the pan, mix together, then add in 2 1\\/2 cups fish broth and the saffron","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-12640-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the broth comes to a boil add in 1 cup round rice, give it one final mix so everything is evenly distributed, after 5 to 6 minutes add in the shrimp and the cleaned mussels, after another 5 minutes, lower the fire to a low-medium heat and simmer until all the broth has been absorbed by the rice, then hit back to a medium-high heat to achieve the socarrat, just go between 1 to 2 minutes, then remove the pan from the heat and cover","name":"Once the broth comes to a boil add in 1 cup round rice, give it one final mix so everything is evenly distributed, after 5 to 6 minutes add in the shrimp and the cleaned mussels, after another 5 minutes, lower the fire to a low-medium heat and simmer until all the broth has been absorbed by the rice, then hit back to a medium-high heat to achieve the socarrat, just go between 1 to 2 minutes, then remove the pan from the heat and cover","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-12640-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After 5 minutes uncover the pan, and garnish the paella with lemon wedges and finely chopped parsley, enjoy!","name":"After 5 minutes uncover the pan, and garnish the paella with lemon wedges and finely chopped parsley, enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#wprm-recipe-12640-step-0-4"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.96","ratingCount":"23","reviewCount":"1"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made this for my family yesterday - superb! My Dad is Spanish (Madrid) and he\'s been asking me for ages to make a paella. I\'d been putting it off as I was always intimidated. (I\'ve lived in Spain so I know what it should taste like). Albert, the simplicity of your explanation and your enthusiasm gave me the courage to try. We were over the moon thrilled with the flavourful results... achieved Soccarat too... my grandfather\'s favourite part. Not a grain of rice was left! We were (4): I used the serving sizes above, except doubled the rice (to 400g) (34cm pan). I will add clams (chirlas) and langostinas next time. Mil gracias, Albert. I follow your work.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Steph"},"datePublished":"2025-07-27"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["Spanish"],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"365 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"11 g","proteinContent":"2 g","fatContent":"36 g","saturatedFatContent":"5 g","sodiumContent":"325 mg","fiberContent":"3 g","sugarContent":"6 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"30 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/spainonafork.com\\/authentic-spanish-seafood-paella-recipe\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://i0.wp.com/spainonafork.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/paella3-11.png?fit=750%2C750&ssl=1',
            'ingredients' => '["3 cloves garlic","1\\/2 onion","1\\/2 red bell pepper","1 tube of squid (cleaned)","12 raw jumbo shrimp (peeled &amp; deveined)","8 fresh mussels (cleaned)","1\\/3 cup extra virgin olive oil (80 ml)","1\\/2 cup tomato sauce (112 grams)","1\\/2 tsp sweet smoked Spanish paprika (1.30 grams)","2 1\\/2 cups fish broth (600 ml)","1\\/4 tsp saffron threads or powder (.17 grams)","1 cup uncooked round rice (200 grams)","2 lemon wedges","handful finely chopped parsley","sea salt &amp; black pepper"]',
                'directions' => '["Rouchly chop 3 cloves of garlic, finely dice 1\\/2 onion, finely chop 1\\/2 red bell pepper and cut 1 cleaned tube of squid into small squares","Heat a paella pan with a medium-high heat and add in 1\\/3 cup extra virgin olive oil, after 1 minute season the olive oil with sea salt and add in the cut squid, mix with the olive oil and cook for 1 1\\/2 to 2 minutes, then remove from the pan and set aside, then add in the diced onion &amp; chopped garlic into the pan, mix with the olive oil, after 1 minute add in the chopped bell pepper and continue to mix so everything evenly sautees","After 3 minutes, add in 1\\/2 cup tomato sauce and season everything with 1\\/2 tsp sweet smoked paprika, sea salt &amp; black pepper, mix together, after 2 minutes and the tomato sauce has thickened, add the squid back into the pan, mix together, then add in 2 1\\/2 cups fish broth and the saffron","Once the broth comes to a boil add in 1 cup round rice, give it one final mix so everything is evenly distributed, after 5 to 6 minutes add in the shrimp and the cleaned mussels, after another 5 minutes, lower the fire to a low-medium heat and simmer until all the broth has been absorbed by the rice, then hit back to a medium-high heat to achieve the socarrat, just go between 1 to 2 minutes, then remove the pan from the heat and cover","After 5 minutes uncover the pan, and garnish the paella with lemon wedges and finely chopped parsley, enjoy!"]',
