ent\\/uploads\\/2024\\/12\\/General-768x556.png","width":2560,"height":1853,"caption":"Miss Molly Makes"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/pg\\/missmollymakestv\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/MissMolly_Makes"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/46a9a279bc9d13071677ee30cf0f34ec","name":"Lauren George \\/ Miss Molly","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-AU","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/e40be13b024b808199d3097e2de229dc0d5c54e3e4bd74d623859154f78eb5f8?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/e40be13b024b808199d3097e2de229dc0d5c54e3e4bd74d623859154f78eb5f8?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/e40be13b024b808199d3097e2de229dc0d5c54e3e4bd74d623859154f78eb5f8?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Lauren George \\/ Miss Molly"}},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Easy Greek Yoghurt Naan Bread","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/46a9a279bc9d13071677ee30cf0f34ec"},"description":"THE best accompaniment to your favourite curry, dip or just eaten on their own!","datePublished":"2022-11-29T16:21:06+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/03\\/naan-bread.webp","https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/03\\/naan-bread-500x500.webp","https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/03\\/naan-bread-500x375.webp","https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/03\\/naan-bread-480x270.webp"],"recipeYield":["8","8 flatbread"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT120M","recipeIngredient":["345 g bread or plain flour (+ extra for dusting)","6 g instant yeast","7 g salt","70 g Greek yoghurt","30 g olive oil","165 g water (warmed (about 37\\u00b0C\\/100\\u00b0F))","125 g butter","4 cloves garlic (minced)","2 tbsp fresh parsley (chopped)","\\u00bd tsp salt"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a large bowl, combine all ingredients for the dough and mix with a chopstick or spatula. When the dough is about to come together, dust your hands with flour and knead gently into a soft, slightly sticky dough. As soon as it comes together, stop kneading.","name":"In a large bowl, combine all ingredients for the dough and mix with a chopstick or spatula. When the dough is about to come together, dust your hands with flour and knead gently into a soft, slightly sticky dough. As soon as it comes together, stop kneading.","url":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#wprm-recipe-1200-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Clean the bowl then lightly oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl and cover with plastic wrap or a damp kitchen towel (I like to use a reusable shower cap). Let sit in a warm place for 1 to 1.5 hours, or until about doubled in size.","name":"Clean the bowl then lightly oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl and cover with plastic wrap or a damp kitchen towel (I like to use a reusable shower cap). Let sit in a warm place for 1 to 1.5 hours, or until about doubled in size.","url":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#wprm-recipe-1200-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Garlic Butter","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a small bowl, place melted butter, finely minced garlic and chopped parsley. Sprinkle 1\\/4-1\\/2 tsp salt and mix well. Get a pastry brush ready to baste the Naan.","name":"In a small bowl, place melted butter, finely minced garlic and chopped parsley. Sprinkle 1\\/4-1\\/2 tsp salt and mix well. Get a pastry brush ready to baste the Naan.","url":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#wprm-recipe-1200-step-1-0"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Cooking the Naan","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"When the dough is ready, dust the bench or silicone mat with enough flour so that it doesn&#39;t stick. Place the dough onto bench.Divide into 8 portions (6 if you want larger ones), dusting with more flour as necessary so the dough doesn&#39;t stick.","name":"When the dough is ready, dust the bench or silicone mat with enough flour so that it doesn&#39;t stick. Place the dough onto bench.Divide into 8 portions (6 if you want larger ones), dusting with more flour as necessary so the dough doesn&#39;t stick.","url":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#wprm-recipe-1200-step-2-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Using a rolling pin, roll one of the dough balls into an oval shape about (3mm or 1\\/8-inch thick). Remove any excess flour. Allow the flatbreads to sit for 10 minutes before frying to proof. Place a large cast iron or pan over medium-high heat until hot.","name":"Using a rolling pin, roll one of the dough balls into an oval shape about (3mm or 1\\/8-inch thick). Remove any excess flour. Allow the flatbreads to sit for 10 minutes before frying to proof. Place a large cast iron or pan over medium-high heat until hot.","url":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#wprm-recipe-1200-step-2-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Gently baste each side with oil or optional garlic butter then lay the dough in the skillet and cook until the top is bursting with air bubbles and the bottom is golden and browned in spots, 2-3 minutes.Flip the naan and cook about 1-2 minutes more until the the bottom is browned.Remove &amp; place the naan in a tea towel-lined dish to keep warm. Serve warm on their own or with a yummy curry!","name":"Gently baste each side with oil or optional garlic butter then lay the dough in the skillet and cook until the top is bursting with air bubbles and the bottom is golden and browned in spots, 2-3 minutes.Flip the naan and cook about 1-2 minutes more until the the bottom is browned.Remove &amp; place the naan in a tea towel-lined dish to keep warm. Serve warm on their own or with a yummy curry!","url":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#wprm-recipe-1200-step-2-2"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"5","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This recipe is great, it\\u2019s easy, quick to make and very tasty. I made them to go with some leftover chilli and it was delicious, I\\u2019ll make that next time I eat chilli for sure. I also use the rest of the naan to make veggie pizzas for lunch and a breakfast \\u201cwraps\\u201d also. I recommend this recipe 100%.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anne-Sophie"},"datePublished":"2024-05-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"A very easy-to-make recipe! I\'d consider myself a beginner cook and I made it for my boyfriend\'s family with raving reviews. I\'d suggest this to anyone who loves a quick, yummy naan! I will be making it in the future. &lt;3","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Krys"},"datePublished":"2024-03-27"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I made these for a party, and they were so good people didn\'t believe they were homemade! Super-easy and super tasty! If you are a bread person, make two batches, because you will eat one all by yourself. :)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"casvelyn"},"datePublished":"2022-12-30"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"No special skills required to make this recipe, it\\u2019s just simple and delicious! This will beat anything you buy yourself at the store and you\\u2019ll be super proud of yourself too.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Hayley"},"datePublished":"2022-12-07"}],"recipeCategory":["Bread","Side Dish"],"recipeCuisine":["Indian","SE Asia"],"keywords":"Basic Recipe, Bread, flat bread, instant yeast, kid friendly, Yeasted Dough","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"210 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"33 g","proteinContent":"7 g","fatContent":"5 g","saturatedFatContent":"1 g","cholesterolContent":"2 mg","sodiumContent":"510 mg","fiberContent":"1 g","sugarContent":"1 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"4 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/missmollymakes.com\\/easy-greek-yoghurt-naan-bread\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://missmollymakes.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/naan-bread.webp',
            'ingredients' => '["345 g bread or plain flour (+ extra for dusting)","6 g instant yeast","7 g salt","70 g Greek yoghurt","30 g olive oil","165 g water (warmed (about 37\\u00b0C\\/100\\u00b0F))","125 g butter","4 cloves garlic (minced)","2 tbsp fresh parsley (chopped)","\\u00bd tsp salt"]',
            'directions' => '{"0":"In a large bowl, combine all ingredients for the dough and mix with a chopstick or spatula. When the dough is about to come together, dust your hands with flour and knead gently into a soft, slightly sticky dough. As soon as it comes together, stop kneading.","1":"Clean the bowl then lightly oil. Transfer the dough to the bowl and cover with plastic wrap or a damp kitchen towel (I like to use a reusable shower cap). Let sit in a warm place for 1 to 1.5 hours, or until about doubled in size.","Garlic Butter":["In a small bowl, place melted butter, finely minced garlic and chopped parsley. Sprinkle 1\\/4-1\\/2 tsp salt and mix well. Get a pastry brush ready to baste the Naan."],"Cooking the Naan":["When the dough is ready, dust the bench or silicone mat with enough flour so that it doesn&#39;t stick. Place the dough onto bench.Divide into 8 portions (6 if you want larger ones), dusting with more flour as necessary so the dough doesn&#39;t stick.","Using a rolling pin, roll one of the dough balls into an oval shape about (3mm or 1\\/8-inch thick). Remove any excess flour. Allow the flatbreads to sit for 10 minutes before frying to proof. Place a large cast iron or pan over medium-high heat until hot.","Gently baste each side with oil or optional garlic butter then lay the dough in the skillet and cook until the top is bursting with air bubbles and the bottom is golden and browned in spots, 2-3 minutes.Flip the naan and cook about 1-2 minutes more until the the bottom is browned.Remove &amp; place the naan in a tea towel-lined dish to keep warm. Serve warm on their own or with a yummy curry!"]}',
