e":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/10\\/live_eat_learn_logo.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2015\\/10\\/live_eat_learn_logo.jpg","width":600,"height":221,"caption":"Live Eat Learn"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/liveeatlearn\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/liveeatlearn","https:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/liveeatlearn\\/","https:\\/\\/www.linkedin.com\\/in\\/sarahlorrainebond","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/live_eat_learn\\/","https:\\/\\/tiktok.com\\/@liveeatlearn","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/c\\/liveeatlearn"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/33a4a3d84c1dee069d08677ee885218b","name":"Sarah Bond","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/9f24172c555b289a188fba12d7c6efebea801f46d12ca1be77e88f54ab178b43?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/9f24172c555b289a188fba12d7c6efebea801f46d12ca1be77e88f54ab178b43?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/9f24172c555b289a188fba12d7c6efebea801f46d12ca1be77e88f54ab178b43?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Sarah Bond"},"description":"A flavor-loving nutritionist and sensory science specialist showing you how to make easy vegetarian recipes, one ingredient at a time. Read more\\u2026","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/sarah-bond\\/","https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/liveeatlearn\\/","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/liveeatlearn\\/","https:\\/\\/www.linkedin.com\\/in\\/sarahlorrainebond\\/","http:\\/\\/pinterest.com\\/live_eat_learn\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/liveeatlearn","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/c\\/liveeatlearn"],"honorificSuffix":"MSc","gender":"Female","knowsAbout":["sensory science","food science","human nutrition","vegetarian cooking"],"knowsLanguage":["English","Dutch"],"jobTitle":"Vegetarian Food Blogger","worksFor":"Eats Media Group LLC","url":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/sarah-bond\\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"The Very Best Boursin Tomato Sandwich","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/33a4a3d84c1dee069d08677ee885218b"},"description":"After making this sandwich nearly every day in the summer, this Boursin tomato sandwich really is the most delicious lunch...ever. And with juicy tomatoes and crispy garlic bread, it&#039;s elevated enough to serve to friends and family. (Ready in just 15 minutes, so you can spend more time enjoying your company and less time preparing food!)","datePublished":"2024-07-01T10:08:49+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-vert.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-vert-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-vert-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-vert-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"The Very Best Boursin Tomato Sandwich","description":"After making this sandwich nearly every day in the summer, this Boursin tomato sandwich really is the most delicious lunch\\u2026ever. And with juicy tomatoes and crispy garlic bread, it\\u2019s elevated enough to serve to friends and family. (Ready in just 15 minutes, so you can spend more time enjoying your company and less time preparing food!)\\n\\nGrab the full written recipe here: https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/boursin-tomato-sandwich\\/\\n\\nInstagram: https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/liveeatlearn\\/ \\nTikTok: https:\\/\\/tiktok.com\\/@liveeatlearn\\/ \\nFacebook: https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/liveeatlearn\\/ \\nPinterest: https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/live_eat_learn","uploadDate":"2024-07-01T16:32:56+00:00","duration":"PT37S","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/i.ytimg.com\\/vi\\/TbWZMxlASSg\\/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/TbWZMxlASSg?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=TbWZMxlASSg","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["1","1 sandwich"],"prepTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT15M","recipeIngredient":["1 medium tomato","A pinch of salt and pepper","2 slices sourdough bread","2 Tbsp Boursin cheese","2 Tbsp fresh basil","2 Tbsp margarine","2 cloves garlic (minced)","Optional: fresh spinach"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Prep Tomato: Slice the tomato into thin slabs and lay it on a paper towel. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Let sit while you gather everything else, then pat slightly dry.","name":"Prep Tomato: Slice the tomato into thin slabs and lay it on a paper towel. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Let sit while you gather everything else, then pat slightly dry.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/boursin-tomato-sandwich\\/#wprm-recipe-104696-step-0-0","image":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-salting-tomato.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Assemble: Build the sandwich by spreading Boursin onto a slice of sourdough, then layering on the tomatoes, basil, and optional spinach, topping with the other slice of bread. In a separate bowl, stir together margarine and garlic. Spread garlic mixture onto the outsides of the sandwich.","name":"Assemble: Build the sandwich by spreading Boursin onto a slice of sourdough, then layering on the tomatoes, basil, and optional spinach, topping with the other slice of bread. In a separate bowl, stir together margarine and garlic. Spread garlic mixture onto the outsides of the sandwich.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/boursin-tomato-sandwich\\/#wprm-recipe-104696-step-0-1","image":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-4.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cook in a skillet over medium heat until both sides are toasty and golden brown, about 3 to 5 minutes per side.","name":"Cook in a skillet over medium heat until both sides are toasty and golden brown, about 3 to 5 minutes per side.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/boursin-tomato-sandwich\\/#wprm-recipe-104696-step-0-2","image":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-social.jpg"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"16","reviewCount":"10"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made the homemade Boursin cheese and then this sandwich and added bacon. OMG! My family LOVED IT!! We had it with fresh tomatoes from the garden. It is definitely one I will be making again!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"S."},"datePublished":"2025-07-26"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Just made this sandwich. My Gahawd is this GOOOD! The addition of the spinach is worth the effort, however, did cause the Sammy to slide a bit when I flipped it but was fine to push back together, just be careful. This is delicious will be making it again. Am on the hunt for some nice heirloom tomatoes....as opposed the the generic hot house toms from my local Fry\'s would really take this off the chart! Thanks for the recipe!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Ken"},"datePublished":"2025-07-19"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Easy and delicious recipe. Great summer recipe when it\'s too hot to cook and when summer ripened tomatoes are available. \\nThis recipe is a keeper!! Thanks for sharing it!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Irene"},"datePublished":"2025-06-25"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Delightful! I might have to go down to 1 layer but still... Finally another great use for those summer tomatoes of which I always find myself having too many of!! But as-advertised, easy to make, easy to store for lunch and tastes great!\\r\\n\\r\\n(Better Late than Never Hint: Don\'t plant tomatoes while hungry or else you\'ll end up with too many, all at once, even for neighbors and friends!!)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kimberly"},"datePublished":"2025-06-02"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Try this! The smell of that cheese grilling was wonderful. A great sandwich. I would love to post a photo, but I can never get mine to look as good as the ones posted. But seriously try this super easy sandwich.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Walter"},"datePublished":"2024-07-19"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"love it! It\\u2019s a messy but delicious sandwich that I\\u2019ll make again and again!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lolly"},"datePublished":"2024-07-19"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"So good! All the flavors go together so good. I will definitely be making this more when my tomatoes come in. Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Stephanie"},"datePublished":"2024-07-14"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Perfect summer dinner with fresh basil from the garden. Only thing that will make it better I are my own tomatoes when they come in! \\r\\n\\r\\nPS: paired this with a cup of freshly made cold cucumber soup! Chef\\u2019s kiss","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Mare"},"datePublished":"2024-07-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is such an easy delicious recipe! Made it before work in 10 minutes. I\'ve never cooked with Boursin cheese but have always seen it in the store.. ITS SO GOOD. I like this one bc its quick, savory but still fresh with the basil. Def a new staple","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rosie B"},"datePublished":"2024-07-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Yummy and refreshing- a great BBT (Boursin, Basil &amp; Tomato)! Made homemade sourdough and fresh basil from the garden to complement this winner of a meal.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kari Ward"},"datePublished":"2024-07-07"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course","Sandwiches and Wraps"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/DiabeticDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/HalalDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/HinduDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/KosherDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/LowCalorieDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/LowFatDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/LowSaltDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VegetarianDiet"],"keywords":"boursin sandwich, tomato boursin, tomato sandwich","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 sandwich","calories":"748 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"62.2 g","proteinContent":"17 g","fatContent":"50.7 g","saturatedFatContent":"22.2 g","cholesterolContent":"70 mg","sodiumContent":"1411 mg","fiberContent":"3.7 g","sugarContent":"4.9 g"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/boursin-tomato-sandwich\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/boursin-tomato-sandwich\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.liveeatlearn.com\\/boursin-tomato-sandwich\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://www.liveeatlearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tomato-sandwich-boursin-basil-vert.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["1 medium tomato","A pinch of salt and pepper","2 slices sourdough bread","2 Tbsp Boursin cheese","2 Tbsp fresh basil","2 Tbsp margarine","2 cloves garlic (minced)","Optional: fresh spinach"]',
                'directions' => '["Prep Tomato: Slice the tomato into thin slabs and lay it on a paper towel. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Let sit while you gather everything else, then pat slightly dry.","Assemble: Build the sandwich by spreading Boursin onto a slice of sourdough, then layering on the tomatoes, basil, and optional spinach, topping with the other slice of bread. In a separate bowl, stir together margarine and garlic. Spread garlic mixture onto the outsides of the sandwich.","Cook in a skillet over medium heat until both sides are toasty and golden brown, about 3 to 5 minutes per side."]',
                'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 sandwich","calories":"748 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"62.2 g","proteinContent":"17 g","fatContent":"50.7 g","saturatedFatContent":"22.2 g","cholesterolContent":"70 mg","sodiumContent":"1411 mg","fiberContent":"3.7 g","sugarContent":"4.9 g"}]',
