            23 => 
            array (
                'id' => 24,
                'name' => 'The Best Grilled Chicken For Tacos, Burritos, or Salads',
                'url' => 'https://gimmedelicious.com/the-best-taco-grilled-chicken/',
                'site_domain' => 'https://gimmedelicious.com',
                'site_name' => 'Layla Atik',
                'user_id' => 1,
                'description' => 'Charred and Tender grilled or chicken spiced with a special blend of homemade taco seasoning can be grilled or cooked in a skillet on the stove-top. It\'s delicious in tacos, burritos, on salads, or for meal-prep!&nbsp;',
            'content' => '{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org\\/","@type":"Recipe","name":"The Best Grilled Chicken For Tacos, Burritos, or Salads","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Layla Atik"},"description":"Charred and Tender grilled or chicken spiced with a special blend of homemade taco seasoning can be grilled or cooked in a skillet on the stove-top. It\'s delicious in tacos, burritos, on salads, or for meal-prep!&nbsp;","datePublished":"2018-03-17T16:47:37+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/03\\/The-BEST-Taco-Chicken_-2.jpg","https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/03\\/The-BEST-Taco-Chicken_-2-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/03\\/The-BEST-Taco-Chicken_-2-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/03\\/The-BEST-Taco-Chicken_-2-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["4","4 people"],"prepTime":"PT5M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT20M","recipeIngredient":["1 pound Boneless, Skinless chicken thighs or breasts (we prefer thighs )","2 cloves garlic (minced)","1 tablespoon lime juice (optional)","1 tablespoon olive oil","1 tablespoons chili powder","1 teaspoon cumin","1 teaspoon paprika","1 teaspoon salt","1\\/2 teaspoon oregano","1\\/4 teaspoon black pepper","1 teaspoon corn starch (optional)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the chicken, garlic, olive oil, lime, spices, and cornstarch to a large bowl or zip-seal bag.","name":"Add the chicken, garlic, olive oil, lime, spices, and cornstarch to a large bowl or zip-seal bag.","url":"https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/the-best-taco-grilled-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-13455-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place in fridge and let marinate for at least 15-30 minutes or up to 24 hours.&nbsp;","name":"Place in fridge and let marinate for at least 15-30 minutes or up to 24 hours.&nbsp;","url":"https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/the-best-taco-grilled-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-13455-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove chicken from marinade and discard marinade. Place chicken on a grill or pan&nbsp;heated to medium-high heat. Let chicken cook until it is no longer pink on the inside, about 6-7 minutes per side&nbsp; (or until it has reached an internal temperature of 165 degrees F).&nbsp;","name":"Remove chicken from marinade and discard marinade. Place chicken on a grill or pan&nbsp;heated to medium-high heat. Let chicken cook until it is no longer pink on the inside, about 6-7 minutes per side&nbsp; (or until it has reached an internal temperature of 165 degrees F).&nbsp;","url":"https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/the-best-taco-grilled-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-13455-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve chicken in tacos, burritos, on salads or rice.","name":"Serve chicken in tacos, burritos, on salads or rice.","url":"https:\\/\\/gimmedelicious.com\\/the-best-taco-grilled-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-13455-step-0-3"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.86","ratingCount":"128","reviewCount":"14"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We love this recipe so much and recommend it to everyone. I love making a LOT at one time and then freezing for even easier chicken tacos at a later date in addition to eating two nights that week. I skip the cornstarch but add the lime juice. I also cut back a little bit on the salt. Otherwise, I make it as written. I prefer chicken thighs with this as they are more forgiving when grilling.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kim"},"datePublished":"2026-02-02"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Recipe sound fantastic, just what I was looking for. I want to prep it as much as I can ahead of time. To freeze the chicken, do I marinate it, then remove the marinade, and then freeze it? One cooking day, can I cook it from frozen, or should it be defrosted first?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Gail McCarthy"},"datePublished":"2025-12-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This makes for very tasty chicken for tacos and quesadillas. Both times we\'ve made it, we\'ve cooked the chicken in the air fryer and it comes out tender, juicy and flavorful. Next time, I\'ll probably try it on the gas grill at 350 degrees or so with smoke bellowing out of a smoker box on the grill too.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"David"},"datePublished":"2025-10-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We made this last night. It was easy and delicious!! Thank you!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Estella Kangos"},"datePublished":"2025-06-30"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We make this often and have for a couple of years now!! It is a no fail recipe.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dana"},"datePublished":"2025-05-25"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was REALLY. I rarely grill so I pan fried. It was crispy on outside and juicy on inside. Definitely will keep this recipe. Thanks for sharing.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Ann N"},"datePublished":"2025-02-13"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I use this all the time! I add to a mexican mac and cheese recipe, or use for chicken tacos. 1 question... do you cook before freezing or freeze raw in or after marinade?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sean"},"datePublished":"2025-01-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I use this all the time! I add to a mexican mac and cheese recipe, or use for chicken tacos. 1 question... don\'t you cook before freezing or freeze raw in or after marinade?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sean"},"datePublished":"2025-01-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Found this recipe a month ago and have lost count on how many times I\'ve made it. This is absolutely the best chicken marinade! It\'s meal prep perfect. Huge thank you..","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Adam"},"datePublished":"2024-09-19"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made this tonight for tacos. We loved it!! Thanks for sharing. We will definitely make it again","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jean"},"datePublished":"2024-08-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Cannot count the number of times I have made this in the past few years or how many people I have given the recipe to, but it\'s a lot. Simple and Delicious.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Tom Sokel"},"datePublished":"2024-05-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I am overdue to review this recipe. I make it several times a year and it is my \'go-to\' if we have a larger group at our house. It usually becomes a make your own burrito\\/taco\\/rice bowl bar so that everyone can add foods they like. But the chicken is the real winner and it is so nice to marinade\\/prep the night before and then throw it on the grill. Our sides usually include the following: yellow rice (NYT recipe), black beans, refried beans, cojita, Mexican cheese blend, limes, cilantro, sauteed bell peppers and onions, scallions, avocado, salsa, and I am sure I am forgetting something. I am working on my grocery list now for a team dinner we\'re hosting on Friday!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anouk"},"datePublished":"2024-05-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"So delicious! Turned out perfect and my family was happy!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Erika"},"datePublished":"2024-01-17"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I have a hard time finding recipes I like online but I have to say this recipe was great! I absolutely loved it! It was super easy and I didn\'t have to change the recipe at all. My husband and I loved it so much I\'m making it again tomorrow. Just wanted to say thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dionne"},"datePublished":"2023-07-16"}],"recipeCategory":["Dinner"],"recipeCuisine":["Mexican"]}',
                'image' => 'https://gimmedelicious.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/The-BEST-Taco-Chicken_-2.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["1 pound Boneless, Skinless chicken thighs or breasts (we prefer thighs )","2 cloves garlic (minced)","1 tablespoon lime juice (optional)","1 tablespoon olive oil","1 tablespoons chili powder","1 teaspoon cumin","1 teaspoon paprika","1 teaspoon salt","1\\/2 teaspoon oregano","1\\/4 teaspoon black pepper","1 teaspoon corn starch (optional)"]',
            'directions' => '["Add the chicken, garlic, olive oil, lime, spices, and cornstarch to a large bowl or zip-seal bag.","Place in fridge and let marinate for at least 15-30 minutes or up to 24 hours.&nbsp;","Remove chicken from marinade and discard marinade. Place chicken on a grill or pan&nbsp;heated to medium-high heat. Let chicken cook until it is no longer pink on the inside, about 6-7 minutes per side&nbsp; (or until it has reached an internal temperature of 165 degrees F).&nbsp;","Serve chicken in tacos, burritos, on salads or rice."]',
