            24 => 
            array (
                'id' => 25,
                'name' => 'Butter-Roasted Carrots with Hazelnut Crumble and Goat Cheese',
                'url' => 'https://www.americastestkitchen.com/recipes/15201-butter-roasted-carrots-with-hazelnut-crumble-and-goat-cheese',
                'site_domain' => 'https//www.americastestkitchen.com',
                'site_name' => 'Mark Huxsoll',
                'user_id' => 1,
            'description' => 'This composed side dish is as delicious as it is pretty. For this recipe, we roasted carrots in butter in a very hot (450-degree) oven to bring out their natural sweetness and a wonderful roasted flavor and texture. To dress them up, we toasted hazelnuts, sesame seeds, and coriander seeds together. We finely chopped the nuts and seeds into a crumble along with fresh thyme and lemon zest to brighten the mixture up before sprinkling it over the plated carrots. A combination of pepperoncini and goat cheese added some tang and a creamy element. We chose to let the carrots and the supporting elements shine rather than adding a sauce or dressing.',
            'content' => '{"@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"Recipe","name":"Butter-Roasted Carrots with Hazelnut Crumble and Goat Cheese","url":"https:\\/\\/www.americastestkitchen.com\\/recipes\\/15201-butter-roasted-carrots-with-hazelnut-crumble-and-goat-cheese","datePublished":"2022-10-03","dateModified":"2025-02-04","author":[{"@type":"Person","name":"Mark Huxsoll","url":"https:\\/\\/www.americastestkitchen.com\\/authors\\/192-Mark-Huxsoll"}],"description":"This composed side dish is as delicious as it is pretty. For this recipe, we roasted carrots in butter in a very hot (450-degree) oven to bring out their natural sweetness and a wonderful roasted flavor and texture. To dress them up, we toasted hazelnuts, sesame seeds, and coriander seeds together. We finely chopped the nuts and seeds into a crumble along with fresh thyme and lemon zest to brighten the mixture up before sprinkling it over the plated carrots. A combination of pepperoncini and goat cheese added some tang and a creamy element. We chose to let the carrots and the supporting elements shine rather than adding a sauce or dressing.","recipeYield":[8,"Serves 6 to 8"],"commentCount":19,"isAccessibleForFree":"False","hasPart":{"@type":"WebPageElement","isAccessibleForFree":"False","cssSelector":".detail-page-full"},"totalTime":"PT1H30M","recipeCategory":"Side Dishes","keywords":"Side Dishes, Vegetables, Cheese","suitableForDiet":"high fiber diet","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.3","reviewCount":85},"tool":[{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"The Best Food Processors","image":"https:\\/\\/res.cloudinary.com\\/hksqkdlah\\/image\\/upload\\/ar_1:1,c_fill,dpr_2.0,f_auto,fl_lossy.progressive.strip_profile,g_faces:auto,q_auto:low,w_150\\/v1\\/TnT\\/2020\\/6_CIND_Food%20Processors\\/SPS_Food-processors_Hero_2"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"The Best Mixing Bowls","image":"https:\\/\\/res.cloudinary.com\\/hksqkdlah\\/image\\/upload\\/ar_1:1,c_fill,dpr_2.0,f_auto,fl_lossy.progressive.strip_profile,g_faces:auto,q_auto:low,w_150\\/v1\\/Equipment%20Images\\/SIL_MixingBowls_Pyrex-SmartEssentials"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"The Best Rimmed Baking Sheets","image":"https:\\/\\/res.cloudinary.com\\/hksqkdlah\\/image\\/upload\\/ar_1:1,c_fill,dpr_2.0,f_auto,fl_lossy.progressive.strip_profile,g_faces:auto,q_auto:low,w_150\\/RimmedBakingSheets-Hero_1_qh5qgt"}],"recipeIngredient":[" \\u00bc cup skinned, hazelnuts "," 1 tablespoon, sesame seeds "," 2 teaspoons, coriander seeds "," 1 teaspoon, minced fresh thyme "," 1 teaspoon, grated lemon zest "," \\u00bc teaspoon, table salt "," 5 tablespoons, unsalted butter, melted, divided"," 3 pounds, carrots, peeled"," 2 teaspoons, table salt "," 2 teaspoons, pepper "," 4 ounces, goat cheese, crumbled (1 cup)"," 3 tablespoons, pepperoncini, stemmed and sliced into thin rings"," 2 tablespoons, extra-virgin olive oil "," 2 tablespoons, chopped fresh parsley "],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Recipe Instructions","position":"1","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Look for carrots that are 1 to 1\\u00bd inches in diameter at the larger end; larger or smaller carrots may need to be cooked for a slightly longer or slightly shorter time, respectively. The carrots may appear crowded on the baking sheet in step 4; this is OK."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"FOR THE HAZELNUT CRUMBLE: Adjust oven rack to lowest position and heat oven to 350 degrees. Spread hazelnuts, sesame seeds, and coriander seeds in even layer on rimmed baking sheet and bake until hazelnuts are deep golden brown and seeds are fragrant, 7 to 9 minutes. Let mixture cool on sheet for 10 minutes."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Transfer hazelnut mixture to food processor. Add thyme, lemon zest, and salt and pulse until finely chopped, 8 to 10 pulses. Transfer hazelnut crumble to small bowl; set aside. (Crumble can be stored in airtight container for up to 1 month.)"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"FOR THE CARROTS: Increase oven temperature to 450 degrees. Pour 4 tablespoons melted butter onto rimmed baking sheet; tilt and swirl sheet until surface is evenly coated with butter."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cut carrots in half crosswise, then cut each piece in half lengthwise. Toss carrots, salt, pepper, and remaining 1 tablespoon melted butter together in large bowl, then arrange carrots in even layer on prepared sheet. Roast carrots on lowest rack until well browned on bottoms and paring knife inserted into thickest carrots meets with little resistance, 40 to 50 minutes."},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Using spatula, transfer carrots to serving platter. Sprinkle with hazelnut crumble, goat cheese, and pepperoncini. Drizzle with oil and sprinkle with parsley. Serve warm or at room temperature."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Test Kitchen Techniques","position":"2","itemListElement":[]}],"nutrition":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":260,"sodiumContent":"502 miligrams","fatContent":"19 grams","unsaturatedFatContent":"8 grams","cholesterolContent":"29 miligrams","saturatedFatContent":"9 grams","transFatContent":"0 grams","sugarContent":"8 grams","proteinContent":"7 grams","carbohydrateContent":"12 grams"}}',
                'image' => NULL,
            'ingredients' => '[" \\u00bc cup skinned, hazelnuts "," 1 tablespoon, sesame seeds "," 2 teaspoons, coriander seeds "," 1 teaspoon, minced fresh thyme "," 1 teaspoon, grated lemon zest "," \\u00bc teaspoon, table salt "," 5 tablespoons, unsalted butter, melted, divided"," 3 pounds, carrots, peeled"," 2 teaspoons, table salt "," 2 teaspoons, pepper "," 4 ounces, goat cheese, crumbled (1 cup)"," 3 tablespoons, pepperoncini, stemmed and sliced into thin rings"," 2 tablespoons, extra-virgin olive oil "," 2 tablespoons, chopped fresh parsley "]',
            'directions' => '{"Recipe Instructions":["Look for carrots that are 1 to 1\\u00bd inches in diameter at the larger end; larger or smaller carrots may need to be cooked for a slightly longer or slightly shorter time, respectively. The carrots may appear crowded on the baking sheet in step 4; this is OK.","FOR THE HAZELNUT CRUMBLE: Adjust oven rack to lowest position and heat oven to 350 degrees. Spread hazelnuts, sesame seeds, and coriander seeds in even layer on rimmed baking sheet and bake until hazelnuts are deep golden brown and seeds are fragrant, 7 to 9 minutes. Let mixture cool on sheet for 10 minutes.","Transfer hazelnut mixture to food processor. Add thyme, lemon zest, and salt and pulse until finely chopped, 8 to 10 pulses. Transfer hazelnut crumble to small bowl; set aside. (Crumble can be stored in airtight container for up to 1 month.)","FOR THE CARROTS: Increase oven temperature to 450 degrees. Pour 4 tablespoons melted butter onto rimmed baking sheet; tilt and swirl sheet until surface is evenly coated with butter.","Cut carrots in half crosswise, then cut each piece in half lengthwise. Toss carrots, salt, pepper, and remaining 1 tablespoon melted butter together in large bowl, then arrange carrots in even layer on prepared sheet. Roast carrots on lowest rack until well browned on bottoms and paring knife inserted into thickest carrots meets with little resistance, 40 to 50 minutes.","Using spatula, transfer carrots to serving platter. Sprinkle with hazelnut crumble, goat cheese, and pepperoncini. Drizzle with oil and sprinkle with parsley. Serve warm or at room temperature."]}',
                'nutrition' => '{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":260,"sodiumContent":"502 miligrams","fatContent":"19 grams","unsaturatedFatContent":"8 grams","cholesterolContent":"29 miligrams","saturatedFatContent":"9 grams","transFatContent":"0 grams","sugarContent":"8 grams","proteinContent":"7 grams","carbohydrateContent":"12 grams"}',
                'slug' => 'butter-roasted-carrots-with-hazelnut-crumble-and-goat-cheese',
