                'user_id' => 1,
                'description' => 'Make this simple 5-minute Lemon Tahini Sauce for falafels, fritters, salads. This lemon tahini dressing is creamy, nutty, and savory. Vegam, GF, DF, nut-free.',
            'content' => '{"@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"Article","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#article","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/"},"author":{"name":"Samira Kazan","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/6ad94cc8952d7a21539edc7d6f9db8f0"},"headline":"Lemon Tahini Sauce","datePublished":"2022-02-08T10:25:00+00:00","dateModified":"2024-08-03T08:30:51+00:00","wordCount":1862,"commentCount":2,"publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/6ad94cc8952d7a21539edc7d6f9db8f0"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square.jpeg","keywords":["15 minutes or less","30 minutes or less","5 minutes","condiment","dairy-free","dip","dipping sauce","diy","dressing","freezer friendly","garlic","gluten free","how-to","lebanese","lemon","meal prep","mediterranean","mezze","middle eastern","nut free","quick and easy","sauce","tahini","vegan","vegetarian"],"articleSection":["Appetizers","DIYs","Gluten Free","Recipes","Sides","Vegan"],"inLanguage":"en-GB","potentialAction":[{"@type":"CommentAction","name":"Comment","target":["https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#respond"]}]},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/","name":"6-Ingredient Lemon Tahini Sauce (Falafel Sauce) - Alphafoodie","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#primaryimage"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square.jpeg","datePublished":"2022-02-08T10:25:00+00:00","dateModified":"2024-08-03T08:30:51+00:00","description":"Make this simple 5-minute Lemon Tahini Sauce for falafels, fritters, salads. This lemon tahini dressing is creamy, nutty, and savory. Vegam, GF, DF, nut-free.","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-GB","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-GB","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square.jpeg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square.jpeg","width":1200,"height":1200,"caption":"Lemon tahini sauce in a bowl"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/recipe-index\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Vegan","item":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/category\\/recipes\\/vegan\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Lemon Tahini Sauce"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/","name":"Alphafoodie","description":"Healthy recipes, simple DIYs and lifestyle blog","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/6ad94cc8952d7a21539edc7d6f9db8f0"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-GB"},{"@type":["Person","Organization"],"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/6ad94cc8952d7a21539edc7d6f9db8f0","name":"Samira Kazan","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-GB","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/samira-kazan.jpeg","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/samira-kazan.jpeg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/samira-kazan.jpeg","width":800,"height":800,"caption":"Samira Kazan"},"logo":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/samira-kazan.jpeg"},"description":"Samira Kazan is a University of Oxford graduate with over 12 years of experience in recipe development. Level 4 Food Safety &amp; HACCP certified, she shares reliable, delicious recipes and kitchen know-how inspired by her Lebanese roots and scientific background.","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/home\\/about-me\\/","https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/alphafoodie\\/","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/alphafoodie\\/","https:\\/\\/www.linkedin.com\\/in\\/samira-kazan-alphafoodie\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/alphafoodie\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/@alphafoodie\\/"],"honorificPrefix":"\\ufeff\\ufeffDr","honorificSuffix":"PhD","gender":"female","award":["Level 4 Food Safety & HACCP (Distinction)"],"knowsAbout":["Lebanese recipes","Middle Eastern cooking","recipe development","DIY food projects","from-scratch cooking","food science","food safety","HACCP","healthy cooking"],"knowsLanguage":["English","Arabic"],"jobTitle":"Food Blogger","worksFor":"Alphafoodie"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Lemon Tahini Sauce (Falafel Tahini Sauce)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Samira Kazan"},"description":"Make this simple 6-ingredient, 5-minute lemon tahini sauce for falafels, fritters, and salads! This lemon tahini dressing is creamy, nutty, savory, and super moreish! Gluten-free, dairy-free, nut-free, vegan!","datePublished":"2022-02-08T10:25:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square.jpeg","https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square-500x500.jpeg","https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square-500x375.jpeg","https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square-480x270.jpeg"],"recipeYield":["8"],"prepTime":"PT5M","totalTime":"PT5M","recipeIngredient":["1\\/2 cup tahini (creamy and either raw or toasted)","1 lemon (3-4 Tbsp juice)","2 cloves garlic","1\\/2 tsp salt","1\\/4 tsp ground cumin","black pepper (to taste (optional))","3-4 Tbsp water (ice-cold; to thin the sauce - use more if needed)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Mince\\/crush the garlic.","name":"Mince\\/crush the garlic.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-65426-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a small bowl, combine the tahini, seasonings, garlic, and lemon juice. Using either a whisk or fork, mix everything until well combined.","name":"In a small bowl, combine the tahini, seasonings, garlic, and lemon juice. Using either a whisk or fork, mix everything until well combined.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-65426-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add ice-cold water, one tablespoon at a time, whisking well in between, until the sauce is a creamy consistency (perfect to drizzle over falafel) or to your desired consistency.Note that, similar to chocolate seizing, adding a small amount of water to tahini can first cause it to thicken up\\/clump. However, it will eventually smooth out if you continue to add more. I recommend using a fork up until it starts to thin, then you can swap to a whisk.","name":"Add ice-cold water, one tablespoon at a time, whisking well in between, until the sauce is a creamy consistency (perfect to drizzle over falafel) or to your desired consistency.Note that, similar to chocolate seizing, adding a small amount of water to tahini can first cause it to thicken up\\/clump. However, it will eventually smooth out if you continue to add more. I recommend using a fork up until it starts to thin, then you can swap to a whisk.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-65426-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Allow it to rest for 20-30 minutes to meld and marinate. Then taste and adjust any of the seasonings to taste. Enjoy!","name":"Allow it to rest for 20-30 minutes to meld and marinate. Then taste and adjust any of the seasonings to taste. Enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-65426-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"How to Store","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Store: store any leftovers in an airtight jar in the refrigerator for up to a week (more when omitting the fresh garlic).Freeze: I haven&#39;t actually tried freezing the tahini sauce, though it should be okay. Leave headspace in the container and freeze for up to 2 months. Upon thawing, you may find you need to boost the flavor with additional lemon\\/garlic.Note that the lemon tahini sauce may thicken when chilled, so whisk in more water if needed.","name":"Store: store any leftovers in an airtight jar in the refrigerator for up to a week (more when omitting the fresh garlic).Freeze: I haven&#39;t actually tried freezing the tahini sauce, though it should be okay. Leave headspace in the container and freeze for up to 2 months. Upon thawing, you may find you need to boost the flavor with additional lemon\\/garlic.Note that the lemon tahini sauce may thicken when chilled, so whisk in more water if needed.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-65426-step-1-0"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"6"},"recipeCategory":["Condiment","DIYs"],"recipeCuisine":["Lebanese","Mediterranean","Middle Eastern"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/GlutenFreeDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VeganDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VegetarianDiet"],"keywords":"5 minute, dressing, falafel, garlic, lemon, sauce, tahini","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"2 Tbsp","calories":"94 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"5 g","proteinContent":"3 g","fatContent":"8 g","saturatedFatContent":"1 g","sodiumContent":"297 mg","fiberContent":"1 g","sugarContent":"1 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"7 g"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.alphafoodie.com\\/lemon-tahini-sauce\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://www.alphafoodie.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Lemon-Tahini-Dressing-Square.jpeg',
            'ingredients' => '["1\\/2 cup tahini (creamy and either raw or toasted)","1 lemon (3-4 Tbsp juice)","2 cloves garlic","1\\/2 tsp salt","1\\/4 tsp ground cumin","black pepper (to taste (optional))","3-4 Tbsp water (ice-cold; to thin the sauce - use more if needed)"]',
            'directions' => '{"0":"Mince\\/crush the garlic.","1":"In a small bowl, combine the tahini, seasonings, garlic, and lemon juice. Using either a whisk or fork, mix everything until well combined.","2":"Add ice-cold water, one tablespoon at a time, whisking well in between, until the sauce is a creamy consistency (perfect to drizzle over falafel) or to your desired consistency.Note that, similar to chocolate seizing, adding a small amount of water to tahini can first cause it to thicken up\\/clump. However, it will eventually smooth out if you continue to add more. I recommend using a fork up until it starts to thin, then you can swap to a whisk.","3":"Allow it to rest for 20-30 minutes to meld and marinate. Then taste and adjust any of the seasonings to taste. Enjoy!","How to Store":["Store: store any leftovers in an airtight jar in the refrigerator for up to a week (more when omitting the fresh garlic).Freeze: I haven&#39;t actually tried freezing the tahini sauce, though it should be okay. Leave headspace in the container and freeze for up to 2 months. Upon thawing, you may find you need to boost the flavor with additional lemon\\/garlic.Note that the lemon tahini sauce may thicken when chilled, so whisk in more water if needed."]}',
                'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"2 Tbsp","calories":"94 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"5 g","proteinContent":"3 g","fatContent":"8 g","saturatedFatContent":"1 g","sodiumContent":"297 mg","fiberContent":"1 g","sugarContent":"1 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"7 g"}]',
                'slug' => 'lemon-tahini-sauce-falafel-tahini-sauce',
                'raw_data' => NULL,
