                'description' => 'This vegan Lentil Bolognese is an easy, yet gourmet meal made with 10 pantry staple ingredients. It’s deceptively meaty and ultra-satisfying!',
            'content' => '{"@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"Article","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#article","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/"},"author":{"name":"Nisha Vora","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d"},"headline":"Lentil Bolognese","datePublished":"2020-04-11T13:29:00+00:00","dateModified":"2023-07-27T20:13:19+00:00","wordCount":2794,"commentCount":2676,"publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta.png","keywords":["10-Ingredient Vegan Red Lentil Bolognese","Red Lentil Bolognese","Vegan Red Lentil Bolognese","10-Ingredient Lentil Bolognese","10-Ingredient Red Lentil Bolognese"],"articleSection":["Recipes","Lunch","Dinner","Featured Favorites"],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"CommentAction","name":"Comment","target":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#respond"]}]},{"@type":["WebPage","FAQPage"],"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/","name":"Lentil Bolognese - Rainbow Plant Life","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#primaryimage"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta.png","datePublished":"2020-04-11T13:29:00+00:00","dateModified":"2023-07-27T20:13:19+00:00","description":"This vegan Lentil Bolognese is an easy, yet gourmet meal made with 10 pantry staple ingredients. It\\u2019s deceptively meaty and ultra-satisfying!","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#breadcrumb"},"mainEntity":[{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689981705184"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982224559"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982245107"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982262485"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982293421"}],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta.png","width":800,"height":1000,"caption":"a fork twirling spaghetti in a bowl of red lentil bolognese."},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/category\\/recipes\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Dinner","item":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/category\\/recipes\\/dinner\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Lentil Bolognese"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/","name":"Rainbow Plant Life","description":"Master vegan cooking at home.","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization","name":"Rainbow Plant Life","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/08\\/RPL-Logo-SQUARE.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/08\\/RPL-Logo-SQUARE.png","width":453,"height":453,"caption":"Rainbow Plant Life"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/rainbowplantlife","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\/","https:\\/\\/pinterest.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/channel\\/UCDbZvuDA_tZ6XP5wKKFuemQ"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d","name":"Nisha Vora","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Nisha Vora"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/about-nisha\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/rainbowplantlife@gmail.com"],"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/about-nisha\\/"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689981705184","position":1,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689981705184","name":"How should you serve vegan bolognese?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Scoop the sauce over bowls of freshly cooked tagliatelle, pappardelle, or fettuccine pasta noodles (make sure they\\u2019re egg-free). If you don\\u2019t have a long pasta, use a ridged pasta instead, like rigatoni and penne rigate (the ridged variety). Even gnocchi works well!<br\\/><br\\/>For a lighter option, serve the sauce over zucchini noodles or sweet potato noodles. You can even use it as a filling on vegan sloppy joes or dolloped on top of <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/vegan-nachos\\/\\">nachos<\\/a> with <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/the-best-vegan-queso-ever\\/\\">queso sauce<\\/a> for an Italian spin on \\u201cchili cheese nachos.\\u201d","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982224559","position":2,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982224559","name":"Is this recipe gluten-free?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, the bolognese itself is naturally gluten-free. To make the entire meal gluten-free, serve it with gluten-free pasta.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982245107","position":3,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982245107","name":"How do you store leftover bolognese?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A good rule of thumb is to store the sauce and cooked pasta separately, otherwise, the noodles will soak up the sauce and become soggy. That said, the combined leftovers are still very tasty and should last 3 to 4 days in the fridge.<br\\/><br\\/>The lentil bolognese will last a bit longer, 5 to 6 days, when stored in a separate airtight container in the fridge.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982262485","position":4,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982262485","name":"Can I freeze it?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! The bolognese sauce (without pasta) freezes quite well. I like to freeze it in these <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3sDvjlu\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\\">Souper Cubes<\\/a> (affiliate link), although an airtight container (don\\u2019t pack it to the top) and freezer bags work well, too. Thaw in the fridge overnight before reheating.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982293421","position":5,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#faq-question-1689982293421","name":"How do you reheat bolognese sauce?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Reheat the leftover sauce in a saucepan on the stove over medium heat until warmed through. If it\\u2019s too thick, you can thin it out a bit with a splash of water or vegetable broth.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Lentil Bolognese","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d"},"description":"This 10-ingredient Lentil Bolognese is what comfort food dreams are made of. The meaty, umami, and flavor-rich sauce simmers together wholesome, pantry-staple ingredients in one pot in less than 1 hour. An easy, yet gourmet Italian-inspired sauce for pasta night!","datePublished":"2020-04-11T13:29:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta-1.png","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta-1-500x500.png","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta-1-500x375.png","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/04\\/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta-1-480x270.png"],"video":{"name":"$9 vs. $39 Vegan Bolognese","description":"You can find both vegan bolognese recipes below!\\n\\n\\ud83c\\udf1f Our brand new weekly meal plan service, Meal Plans by Rainbow Plant Life, is OFFICIALLY LIVE!! Sign up here for a 7-day free trial: https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/mealplans\\/ \\n\\nWant more details on how the plans work? Watch this video! https:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/KTuGLVIWsMg?si=-4VSAFdzjrD9KB7O\\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- \\n\\nPANTRY-FRIENDLY LENTIL BOLOGNESE: https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/\\n\\nFANCY PANTS BOLOGNESE \\n- 1 \\u00bd TBSP olive oil\\n- 1 large onion, diced\\n- 4 garlic cloves, minced\\n- 1 tsp dried oregano\\n- 1 tsp dried thyme\\n- Kosher salt + freshly ground black pepper\\n- 4 TBSP tomato paste\\n- 1 package Beyond Beef \\n- \\u00be cup dry red wine (check that it\'s vegan-friendly!) \\n- 1 (28-ounce) can whole peeled tomatoes\\n- 2 to 3 tsp good-quality balsamic vinegar\\n- 1 pound egg-free tagliatelle, pappardelle, or fettuccine; or rigatoni or penne; or gnocchi\\n\\nCashew Cream \\n- 1 cup raw cashews, soaked overnight, or in boiling water for 1 hour\\n- \\u00be cup water\\n- 2 TBSP lemon juice \\n- 1 tsp kosher salt \\n- 2 tbsp nutritional yeast\\n- \\u00bd to \\u00be cup fresh basil, slivered \\n- \\u00bd cup vegan parmesan cheese\\n\\n1. Heat a 12-inch saute pan or Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add olive oil, and once shimmering, add onions and season with a pinch of salt. Stir occasionally and cook for 5 minutes. Add a few spoons of water to deglaze the pan. Continue cooking the onions, adding more water every few minutes and stirring frequently to prevent burning, until the onions are softened and nicely browned, 9-10 minutes.\\n2. Add the garlic, thyme, and oregano. Stir frequently and cook for 60-90 seconds.\\n3. Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 2-3 minutes to caramelize, stirring frequently, until darker red in color.\\n4. Add the Beyond Beef, 1\\/2 tsp kosher salt, and pepper to taste. Break up into small pieces with a wooden spoon. Cook until lightly browned and liquid has evaporated, 6 to 8 minutes.\\n5. Pour in the wine and simmer until completely reduced, 1 to 2 minutes. Pour in the juice from the canned tomatoes; add the tomatoes with your hands, crushing them as you add them to the pot (or crush in a separate bowl). Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened and the flavors have married, about 15 minutes.\\n6. Meanwhile, cook your pasta in a large pot of salted boiling water until just al dente. Drain.\\n7. Meanwhile, make the Cashew Cream. Drain soaked cashews and add to a high-powered blender or food processor, along with water, lemon juice, salt, and nutritional yeast. Blend until uniformly creamy and smooth, scraping down the sides as you go. \\n8. Add \\u00bc to \\u00bd cup of the cashew cream to the bolognese and gently simmer for another 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking, and adding a bit of water as needed.\\n9. Taste for seasonings, adding more salt and pepper to taste. Finish with the balsamic vinegar and stir to combine. Add cooked pasta to the bolognese and toss until well coated in the sauce. Finish with slivered basil and vegan parmesan. \\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\nMY COOKBOOK: The Vegan Instant Pot Cookbook: Wholesome, Indulgent Plant-Based Recipes! \\n\\nORDER ON AMAZON: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/2liT4lZ\\nMORE COOKBOOK INFO: https:\\/\\/www.rainbowplantlife.com\\/blog\\/vegan-instant-pot-cookbook\\n\\n*90+ delicious vegan recipes made in the Instant Pot*\\n*With tons of gluten-free, soy-free, nut-free, and refined-sugar-free options\\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\n*IN THIS VIDEO*\\nFavorite balsamic vinegars \\n*https:\\/\\/shop.weolive.com\\/we-olive-aged-balsamic-vinegar\\/\\n*https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3dNmu4E\\nFavorite knives: https:\\/\\/kankitchen.com\\/meet-the-knives\\/ (get $5 off using code \\"nisha\\") \\nDeep nonstick saute pan: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3vgIqL4\\n\\n*MY KITCHEN ESSENTIALS* \\n\\nInstant Pot 6 quart: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3aQY1aQ\\nFood Processor: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/38L8Aub\\nDutch oven: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/35SLfa6\\nLarge Cutting Board: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3spsW60\\nNonstick frying pan: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/2ZZwOhT\\nCast iron skillet: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/2DXvuol\\nVitamix blender: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/36xtZFN\\nVitamix 64-ounce container: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3cp5SNj\\nGrater: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3pYQ7CP\\nOven Thermometer: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/3mwrKw2\\nDigital Scale: https:\\/\\/amzn.to\\/2PNOfRf\\n\\nAll Other Kitchen Equipment: http:\\/\\/bit.ly\\/kitchen-equipment-shop\\nFilm & Photography Equipment: http:\\/\\/bit.ly\\/photo-gear-shop\\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\nWANT MORE DELICIOUS VEGAN RECIPES & INSPIRATION? \\nhttps:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/ \\nhttp:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\/\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/rainbowplantlife","uploadDate":"2021-04-24T14:00:06+00:00","duration":"PT11M6S","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/i.ytimg.com\\/vi\\/NBiicQZSbX4\\/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/NBiicQZSbX4?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NBiicQZSbX4&","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["6"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT45M","totalTime":"PT55M","recipeIngredient":["1 \\u00bd tablespoons olive oil","1 large onion, (diced)","4 garlic cloves, (minced)","1 teaspoon dried oregano","1 teaspoon dried thyme ((or use more oregano) )","1 \\u00bd teaspoons kosher salt, (plus more to taste)","Freshly ground black pepper to taste","1 (5.3-ounce) (150g) tube of tomato paste ((see note 1))","1\\/2 cup (120 mL) dry red wine ((optional, see note 2))","3 cups (720 mL) vegetable broth","1 cup (185g) red lentils, soaked (see step #1)","\\u00bc cup (32g) walnuts (or pecans), crushed finely","1 (14.5-ounce\\/410g) can of crushed tomatoes or whole peeled tomatoes, crushed by hand ((see note 3))","12-16 ounces (340-454g) long, wide pasta","1 tablespoon high-quality balsamic vinegar ((see note 5))","Flat-leaf Italian parsley or fresh basil, (chopped or slivered (optional))"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Soak the 1 cup of lentils in water for 30 minutes, or up to 60 minutes. Meanwhile, prep all the other ingredients (i.e., chop the onions and garlic, chop the walnuts, etc.)","name":"Soak the 1 cup of lentils in water for 30 minutes, or up to 60 minutes. Meanwhile, prep all the other ingredients (i.e., chop the onions and garlic, chop the walnuts, etc.)","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat a 12-inch deep saut\\u00e9 pan or Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Add the olive oil, and once it\\u2019s shimmering, add the onions and season with a pinch of salt. Stir occasionally and cook the onions until a light brown fond starts form on the surface of the pan, about 5 minutes. Add a few spoons of water to deglaze the pan, and stir. Continue cooking the onions, adding more water every few minutes and stirring frequently to prevent burning, until the onions are softened and golden brown, 9-10 minutes.","name":"Heat a 12-inch deep saut\\u00e9 pan or Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Add the olive oil, and once it\\u2019s shimmering, add the onions and season with a pinch of salt. Stir occasionally and cook the onions until a light brown fond starts form on the surface of the pan, about 5 minutes. Add a few spoons of water to deglaze the pan, and stir. Continue cooking the onions, adding more water every few minutes and stirring frequently to prevent burning, until the onions are softened and golden brown, 9-10 minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the garlic, thyme, oregano, 1 1\\/2 teaspoons kosher salt, and pepper to taste. Stir frequently and cook for 60-90 seconds.","name":"Add the garlic, thyme, oregano, 1 1\\/2 teaspoons kosher salt, and pepper to taste. Stir frequently and cook for 60-90 seconds.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 2-3 minutes to caramelize, stirring very frequently, until it\\u2019s darker red in color.","name":"Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 2-3 minutes to caramelize, stirring very frequently, until it\\u2019s darker red in color.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Optional: If using the red wine, pour the wine into the pan and deglaze, scraping up any browned bits. Cook for 1-2 minutes, until the smell of alcohol has burned off and the mixture is jammy.","name":"Optional: If using the red wine, pour the wine into the pan and deglaze, scraping up any browned bits. Cook for 1-2 minutes, until the smell of alcohol has burned off and the mixture is jammy.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour in the broth to deglaze the pan, stirring any browned bits on the bottom of the pot and stirring the broth into the tomato paste to combine. Add the lentils and walnuts, and stir to incorporate. Heat until the mixture comes to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low to maintain a rapid simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.","name":"Pour in the broth to deglaze the pan, stirring any browned bits on the bottom of the pot and stirring the broth into the tomato paste to combine. Add the lentils and walnuts, and stir to incorporate. Heat until the mixture comes to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low to maintain a rapid simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the crushed tomatoes and simmer for another 15-20 minutes, or until the lentils are tender but still al dente, stirring occasionally to prevent burning and sticking. If using crushed tomatoes, you may need to add a little water or lower the heat as needed to prevent burning.I prefer to cook for 20 minutes for a more developed flavor.","name":"Add the crushed tomatoes and simmer for another 15-20 minutes, or until the lentils are tender but still al dente, stirring occasionally to prevent burning and sticking. If using crushed tomatoes, you may need to add a little water or lower the heat as needed to prevent burning.I prefer to cook for 20 minutes for a more developed flavor.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Meanwhile, bring a large pot of water to a boil and salt generously. Add the pasta and cook until just al dente. Reserve a ladle or so of pasta water (may not need it). Drain the pasta but do not rinse it.","name":"Meanwhile, bring a large pot of water to a boil and salt generously. Add the pasta and cook until just al dente. Reserve a ladle or so of pasta water (may not need it). Drain the pasta but do not rinse it.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-7"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Taste the bolognese for seasonings, adding more salt and pepper to taste. Finish with the balsamic vinegar (or sugar, see note 5), and stir to combine.","name":"Taste the bolognese for seasonings, adding more salt and pepper to taste. Finish with the balsamic vinegar (or sugar, see note 5), and stir to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-8"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the hot cooked pasta to the bolognese and toss until well coated in the sauce, adding a bit of pasta water as needed to ensure the sauce coats the noodles. Garnish with chopped parsley or basil, if using.Note: If you&#039;re not serving all of the bolognese at this time, transfer the amount of bolognese sauce you&#039;d like to eat to the pasta pot. Add the hot cooked pasta, turn the heat to medium, and toss to coat. Store the leftover bolognese sauce separately in the fridge.","name":"Add the hot cooked pasta to the bolognese and toss until well coated in the sauce, adding a bit of pasta water as needed to ensure the sauce coats the noodles. Garnish with chopped parsley or basil, if using.Note: If you&#039;re not serving all of the bolognese at this time, transfer the amount of bolognese sauce you&#039;d like to eat to the pasta pot. Add the hot cooked pasta, turn the heat to medium, and toss to coat. Store the leftover bolognese sauce separately in the fridge.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#wprm-recipe-5570-step-0-9"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.96","ratingCount":"1519","reviewCount":"7"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Best vegetarian bolognese ever!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Fiona Redmond"},"datePublished":"2026-07-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Absolutely delicious! I made a small change by using pecans instead of walnuts, and it turned out amazing. The pecans added a rich, buttery flavor and a great texture that worked perfectly with the hearty lentils and savory sauce. Even without meat, this bolognese was incredibly satisfying, comforting, and full of flavor. This is definitely going into my regular meal rotation. Highly recommend!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sherri"},"datePublished":"2026-06-30"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Hiya,\\r\\nCould I use white or rose wine if I don\\u2019t have red?\\r\\nThanks","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Grace Mcloughlin"},"datePublished":"2026-06-29"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Really good recipe","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Michelle"},"datePublished":"2026-06-27"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This tastes great! It was easy to make, did not require any exotic ingredients and tastes fantastic, just like \\"real\\" ragu. And so healthy. Will definitely make it again, and maybe add mushrooms and carrots.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lorna"},"datePublished":"2026-06-23"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I love the recipe! I\\u2019ve made it several times\\r\\n\\r\\nI do replace the walnuts (nut allergy) with finely diced mushrooms and I add them when I\\u2019m frying the onion","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Emma"},"datePublished":"2026-06-23"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Justin, I am going to make it this evening. I cut all the veggies, and measure out the spices and liquids beforehand, and then it is quite easy to cook. Honest!! Nisha\'s recipes are delicious!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Margaret Vansoest"},"datePublished":"2026-06-11"}],"recipeCategory":["Dinner","Lunch"],"recipeCuisine":["Italian"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VeganDiet"],"keywords":"10 ingredients, bolognese, gluten-free, pantry recipe, red lentils, soy-free","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"434 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"74 g","proteinContent":"18 g","fatContent":"8 g","saturatedFatContent":"1 g","sodiumContent":"873 mg","fiberContent":"14 g","sugarContent":"9 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"6 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/10-ingredient-vegan-red-lentil-bolognese\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://rainbowplantlife.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/red-lentil-bolognese-twirling-pasta.png',
            'ingredients' => '["1 \\u00bd tablespoons olive oil","1 large onion, (diced)","4 garlic cloves, (minced)","1 teaspoon dried oregano","1 teaspoon dried thyme ((or use more oregano) )","1 \\u00bd teaspoons kosher salt, (plus more to taste)","Freshly ground black pepper to taste","1 (5.3-ounce) (150g) tube of tomato paste ((see note 1))","1\\/2 cup (120 mL) dry red wine ((optional, see note 2))","3 cups (720 mL) vegetable broth","1 cup (185g) red lentils, soaked (see step #1)","\\u00bc cup (32g) walnuts (or pecans), crushed finely","1 (14.5-ounce\\/410g) can of crushed tomatoes or whole peeled tomatoes, crushed by hand ((see note 3))","12-16 ounces (340-454g) long, wide pasta","1 tablespoon high-quality balsamic vinegar ((see note 5))","Flat-leaf Italian parsley or fresh basil, (chopped or slivered (optional))"]',
            'directions' => '["Soak the 1 cup of lentils in water for 30 minutes, or up to 60 minutes. Meanwhile, prep all the other ingredients (i.e., chop the onions and garlic, chop the walnuts, etc.)","Heat a 12-inch deep saut\\u00e9 pan or Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Add the olive oil, and once it\\u2019s shimmering, add the onions and season with a pinch of salt. Stir occasionally and cook the onions until a light brown fond starts form on the surface of the pan, about 5 minutes. Add a few spoons of water to deglaze the pan, and stir. Continue cooking the onions, adding more water every few minutes and stirring frequently to prevent burning, until the onions are softened and golden brown, 9-10 minutes.","Add the garlic, thyme, oregano, 1 1\\/2 teaspoons kosher salt, and pepper to taste. Stir frequently and cook for 60-90 seconds.","Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 2-3 minutes to caramelize, stirring very frequently, until it\\u2019s darker red in color.","Optional: If using the red wine, pour the wine into the pan and deglaze, scraping up any browned bits. Cook for 1-2 minutes, until the smell of alcohol has burned off and the mixture is jammy.","Pour in the broth to deglaze the pan, stirring any browned bits on the bottom of the pot and stirring the broth into the tomato paste to combine. Add the lentils and walnuts, and stir to incorporate. Heat until the mixture comes to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low to maintain a rapid simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.","Add the crushed tomatoes and simmer for another 15-20 minutes, or until the lentils are tender but still al dente, stirring occasionally to prevent burning and sticking. If using crushed tomatoes, you may need to add a little water or lower the heat as needed to prevent burning.I prefer to cook for 20 minutes for a more developed flavor.","Meanwhile, bring a large pot of water to a boil and salt generously. Add the pasta and cook until just al dente. Reserve a ladle or so of pasta water (may not need it). Drain the pasta but do not rinse it.","Taste the bolognese for seasonings, adding more salt and pepper to taste. Finish with the balsamic vinegar (or sugar, see note 5), and stir to combine.","Add the hot cooked pasta to the bolognese and toss until well coated in the sauce, adding a bit of pasta water as needed to ensure the sauce coats the noodles. Garnish with chopped parsley or basil, if using.Note: If you&#039;re not serving all of the bolognese at this time, transfer the amount of bolognese sauce you&#039;d like to eat to the pasta pot. Add the hot cooked pasta, turn the heat to medium, and toss to coat. Store the leftover bolognese sauce separately in the fridge."]',
                'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"434 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"74 g","proteinContent":"18 g","fatContent":"8 g","saturatedFatContent":"1 g","sodiumContent":"873 mg","fiberContent":"14 g","sugarContent":"9 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"6 g","servingSize":"1 serving"}]',
