 spicy, healthy and vegan! One pot recipe with brown lentils or green lentils.","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/10\\/Instant-Pot-Lentil-Curry-Coconut.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/10\\/Instant-Pot-Lentil-Curry-Coconut.jpg","width":1200,"height":1628,"caption":"Easy, CREAMY Instant Pot Lentil Curry. Amazing flavors, not too spicy, and it\\u2019s hands free, vegan, and healthy! Made with green or brown lentils, Indian spices, and coconut milk."},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/category\\/recipes-by-type\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Instant Pot","item":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/category\\/recipes-by-type\\/instant-pot\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":4,"name":"Instant Pot Lentil Curry"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/","name":"Well Plated","description":"Easy, Healthy, Family-Friendly Recipes","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/#organization","name":"Well Plated","url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/04\\/Well-Plated-Logo-Square.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/04\\/Well-Plated-Logo-Square.jpg","width":900,"height":900,"caption":"Well Plated"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/wellplated","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/wellplated","http:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/wellplated","https:\\/\\/www.linkedin.com\\/in\\/erin-clarke-36386350","http:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/wellplated","https:\\/\\/youtube.com\\/c\\/wellplated","https:\\/\\/www.tiktok.com\\/@wellplated","https:\\/\\/wellplated.substack.com\\/"],"description":"Well Plated is a trusted resource for home cooks and busy families who are eager to eat wholesome food, but who don\\u2019t want to give up their favorite dishes, spend hours cooking, or buy pricey, fussy ingredients. The recipes are developed by successful two-time cookbook author Erin Clarke and go through a rigorous testing process so you can feel confident they work. Well Plated recipes are meant for cooks of all levels: kitchen novices, families, young kids, and seasoned-cooks can all find something to love. On Well Plated, you\\u2019ll find hundreds of easy-to-follow, from-scratch recipes from easy dinners, to breakfasts, to sides, to desserts, appetizers, drinks, and more. In addition to recipes, Erin shares helpful kitchen tips, step-by-step photos, and video tutorials that will give you confidence in the kitchen. She has millions of followers on social media who have fallen in love for her genuine personality and thoughtful, realistic approach to cooking.","email":"hello@wellplated.com","legalName":"Well Plated by Erin","foundingDate":"2012-05-31"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/erin-clarke\\/#person","name":"Erin Clarke","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/cropped-About-Erin-Clarke-well-plated-96x96.jpg","url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/cropped-About-Erin-Clarke-well-plated-96x96.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/cropped-About-Erin-Clarke-well-plated-96x96.jpg","caption":"Erin Clarke"},"description":"Hi, I\\u2019m Erin Clarke, cookbook author and the home cook behind Well Plated. I\\u2019ve helped millions of people cook healthier meals that actually taste amazing and sold over 200,000 books! I\\u2019m here to help you save time, dirty fewer dishes, and feel great about what you\\u2019re eating, without overthinking it. Welcome!","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/erin-clarke\\/","https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/wellplated\\/","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/wellplated\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/wellplated\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/wellplated"],"url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/erin-clarke\\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Instant Pot Lentil Curry","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/erin-clarke\\/#person"},"description":"Easy Instant Pot Lentil Curry with Indian flavors, not too spicy, healthy and vegan! One pot recipe with brown lentils or green lentils.","datePublished":"2018-12-18T21:43:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/10\\/Instant-Pot-Lentil-Curry-Coconut.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/10\\/Instant-Pot-Lentil-Curry-Coconut-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/10\\/Instant-Pot-Lentil-Curry-Coconut-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2017\\/10\\/Instant-Pot-Lentil-Curry-Coconut-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Instant Pot Lentil Curry Video","description":"Easy Instant Pot Lentil Curry. Amazing Indian flavors, not too spicy, healthy and vegan! Use brown lentils or green lentils for a filling, delicious meal.","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/thumbs\\/MnjKExNu-720.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/videos\\/MnjKExNu.mp4","uploadDate":"2018-12-18T00:00:00.000Z","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["3","3 cups, approx. (4 to 6 servings)"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT45M","recipeIngredient":["1 1\\/2 cups lentils (green or brown )","1\\/2 tablespoon coconut oil","1 cup plus 1 tablespoon water (divided)","1 small shallot (finely chopped)","3 tablespoons minced fresh ginger","2 tablespoons minced garlic (about 6 cloves)","1 tablespoon curry powder (plus 1 teaspoon )","1\\/2 tablespoon coconut sugar ( or brown sugar)","1 teaspoon kosher salt","3\\/4 teaspoon ground turmeric","1\\/8 to 1\\/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper (use more for more spice or omit if sensitive to spice)","1 can light coconut milk (about 14 ounces)","2 tablespoons freshly squeezed lemon juice (about 1\\/2 large lemon)","Cooked brown rice (for serving)","Chopped fresh cilantro (for serving)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Rinse and drain the lentils, then set aside. Set the Instant Pot to saut\\u00e9 and add the coconut oil. Once the oil has melted, add 1 tablespoon water, the shallot, ginger, and garlic. Cook, stirring often, until very fragrant and the shallot is soft, about 2 minutes. Add the curry powder, coconut sugar, salt, turmeric, and cayenne and stir vigorously. Stand back and try not to breath in any of the steam coming from the pot (it\\u2019s spicy!). Add the lentils, coconut milk, and 1 cup of water. Stir to coat the lentils completely with the liquid.","name":"Cook","url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-33209-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Hit cancel to stop the saut\\u00e9 function, seal the lid, then set to cook on HIGH pressure for 15 minutes. (It will take about 8 minutes for the pressure to build, then the timer will begin.) Once the timer has stopped, let the pressure release naturally for 10 minutes, then vent to release the pressure completely. Open the lid and stir in the lemon juice. Taste and adjust the seasoning as desired. If the curry is too thick, add a bit more water to loosen as needed. Serve hot with rice, sprinkled with cilantro.","name":"Serve","url":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-33209-step-0-1"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.87","ratingCount":"236","reviewCount":"7"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Thank you, Erin! This was a great recipe. It was delicious. I\'m so glad you stressed the importance of the fresh lemon. Will be making this again.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Siobhan"},"datePublished":"2026-01-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is a great recipe base. I always add a couple chopped carrots, sweet potatoes, a can of tomatoes, can of green chilies, mustard seeds and cumin seeds as well. It\'s a hit at gatherings, too. Thanks for the instant pot lentil recipe!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Christina"},"datePublished":"2025-10-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We really enjoyed this recipe","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Emily Worley"},"datePublished":"2025-10-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is a huge hit every time I make it. Thank you! \\r\\nI\'m really shocked someone left out the cayenne and then went to the trouble if giving the recipe a 1 star for being bland!! Honestly! This is one of the best things I make in the Pot, so thank you again","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sue"},"datePublished":"2025-09-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is seriously so easy and SO delicious, I\\u2019ve made it twice in a week!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jessica T."},"datePublished":"2025-05-02"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Going to try this tonight! I have a ton of heavy whipping cream on hand, do you think I could sub the coconut milk out for it? Even with the lemon and everything?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Yan"},"datePublished":"2025-03-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is delicious and is a staple now- I love it..it went down a storm at a recent BBQ too..\\r\\nI generally need to add some water on reheating- it mixes up easily when warm.\\r\\nThe only note I have is......I won\'t again be adding the water to the hot oil. Even though my saute setting was \'medium\', it was a bit of a kaboom moment. \\r\\nI add the water after the onions\\/garlic\\/ginger. \\r\\nOther than that, this recipe is perfection and I 100% recommend.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sue"},"datePublished":"2025-02-01"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["Indian"],"keywords":"curry with coconut milk, Easy Curry Recipe, Healthy Instant Pot Recipe, Indian lentil curry, instant pot curry recipe, instant pot Indian curry, Instant Pot Lentil Curry","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"0.5 cup cooked lentils with 1\\/2 cup cooked brown rice","calories":"315 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"59 g","proteinContent":"7 g","fatContent":"12 g","saturatedFatContent":"4 g","fiberContent":"6 g","sugarContent":"8 g"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.wellplated.com\\/instant-pot-lentil-curry\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://www.wellplated.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Lentil-Curry-Coconut.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["1 1\\/2 cups lentils (green or brown )","1\\/2 tablespoon coconut oil","1 cup plus 1 tablespoon water (divided)","1 small shallot (finely chopped)","3 tablespoons minced fresh ginger","2 tablespoons minced garlic (about 6 cloves)","1 tablespoon curry powder (plus 1 teaspoon )","1\\/2 tablespoon coconut sugar ( or brown sugar)","1 teaspoon kosher salt","3\\/4 teaspoon ground turmeric","1\\/8 to 1\\/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper (use more for more spice or omit if sensitive to spice)","1 can light coconut milk (about 14 ounces)","2 tablespoons freshly squeezed lemon juice (about 1\\/2 large lemon)","Cooked brown rice (for serving)","Chopped fresh cilantro (for serving)"]',
            'directions' => '["Rinse and drain the lentils, then set aside. Set the Instant Pot to saut\\u00e9 and add the coconut oil. Once the oil has melted, add 1 tablespoon water, the shallot, ginger, and garlic. Cook, stirring often, until very fragrant and the shallot is soft, about 2 minutes. Add the curry powder, coconut sugar, salt, turmeric, and cayenne and stir vigorously. Stand back and try not to breath in any of the steam coming from the pot (it\\u2019s spicy!). Add the lentils, coconut milk, and 1 cup of water. Stir to coat the lentils completely with the liquid.","Hit cancel to stop the saut\\u00e9 function, seal the lid, then set to cook on HIGH pressure for 15 minutes. (It will take about 8 minutes for the pressure to build, then the timer will begin.) Once the timer has stopped, let the pressure release naturally for 10 minutes, then vent to release the pressure completely. Open the lid and stir in the lemon juice. Taste and adjust the seasoning as desired. If the curry is too thick, add a bit more water to loosen as needed. Serve hot with rice, sprinkled with cilantro."]',
                'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"0.5 cup cooked lentils with 1\\/2 cup cooked brown rice","calories":"315 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"59 g","proteinContent":"7 g","fatContent":"12 g","saturatedFatContent":"4 g","fiberContent":"6 g","sugarContent":"8 g"}]',
                'slug' => 'instant-pot-lentil-curry',
                'raw_data' => NULL,
                'category' => 'Main Course',
                'cuisine' => 'Indian',
                'created_at' => '2025-04-23 21:58:41',
                'updated_at' => '2026-07-13 04:44:05',
                'site_link' => 'https://www.wellplated.com/instant-pot-lentil-curry/#recipe',
            ),
