","datePublished":"2018-10-11T03:30:17+00:00","dateModified":"2019-02-26T02:30:07+00:00","description":"This Healthy Pumpkin Black Bean Enchilada Casserole is perfect for this time of year, warm and filling, full of flavor, yet loaded with nutrition!","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/Pumpkin-Enchilada-Casserole1.gif","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/Pumpkin-Enchilada-Casserole1.gif","width":910,"height":600,"caption":"Pumpkin-Enchilada-Casserole1"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Healthy Pumpkin Black Bean Enchilada Casserole"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/","name":"Lemons and Basil","description":"Healthy Food \\u2022 Healthy Living","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/2f6b78e9ec50d9515a326c974942eb6e"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":["Person","Organization"],"@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/2f6b78e9ec50d9515a326c974942eb6e","name":"Kaylee Pauley","logo":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/image\\/"},"description":"Health and nutrition have always been important to me, but over the past several years, my knowledge and interest in food and how it affects our body has really expanded. So, with my love for cooking, organic produce, and whole foods, with my food blog Lemons and Basil, I hope to inspire you in your cooking adventures and journey of good health, the way so many other food blogs have inspired me!","sameAs":["http:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com","http:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/lemonsandbasil","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/lemonsnbasil"],"url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/author\\/kdpauley\\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Healthy Pumpkin Black Bean Enchilada Casserole","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kaylee Pauley"},"description":"This Healthy Pumpkin Black Bean Enchilada Casserole is perfect for this time of year, warm and filling, full of flavor, yet loaded with nutrition!","datePublished":"2018-10-10T22:30:17+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/Pumpkin-Enchilada-Casserole1.gif"],"recipeYield":["12"],"prepTime":"PT20M","cookTime":"PT30M","totalTime":"PT50M","recipeIngredient":["1 tbsp coconut oil","2 garlic cloves (minced)","1\\/2 red onion (diced)","1 bell peppers (diced)","1 can black beans (rinsed and drained)","1 cup cooked pumpkin puree (I used organic canned pumpkin)","2 tsp chili powder","1 tsp cumin","1 tsp smoked paprika","\\u00bc tsp ground black pepper","\\u00be cup mild salsa","6 Xtreme Wellness High Fiber tortillas (cut into 2\\" strips)","2 cups enchilada sauce","2 cups cheddar or Mexican blend cheese shredded","Garnishing: Fresh Cilantro (Chives, Sour Cream, Cotija cheese, Avocado)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat oven to 425 degrees.","name":"Preheat oven to 425 degrees.","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#wprm-recipe-40025-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add coconut oil, red onion, bell pepper, and garlic to large sauce pan, and cook over medium heat for 5-7 minutes or until onions are translucent.","name":"Add coconut oil, red onion, bell pepper, and garlic to large sauce pan, and cook over medium heat for 5-7 minutes or until onions are translucent.","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#wprm-recipe-40025-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add black beans, pumpkin puree, salsa and all seasonings (chili powder through black pepper) then stir to combine.","name":"Add black beans, pumpkin puree, salsa and all seasonings (chili powder through black pepper) then stir to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#wprm-recipe-40025-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a large 9x13 baking dish, add 1\\/4-1\\/2 cup enchilada sauce to the bottom, followed by first layer of tortillas.","name":"In a large 9x13 baking dish, add 1\\/4-1\\/2 cup enchilada sauce to the bottom, followed by first layer of tortillas.","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#wprm-recipe-40025-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"On top of the tortillas, add 1\\/3 black bean, pumpkin and veggie mixture, followed by approximately 2\\/3 cup shredded cheese.","name":"On top of the tortillas, add 1\\/3 black bean, pumpkin and veggie mixture, followed by approximately 2\\/3 cup shredded cheese.","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#wprm-recipe-40025-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Repeat with enchilada sauce, tortillas, black bean\\/veggie mix and cheese two more times, finishing with the enchilada sauce and cheese on top.","name":"Repeat with enchilada sauce, tortillas, black bean\\/veggie mix and cheese two more times, finishing with the enchilada sauce and cheese on top.","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#wprm-recipe-40025-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Wrap the casserole dish in aluminum foil, then bake for 30 minutes. Then remove foil and bake additional 5-7 minutes or until cheese begins to brown. Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting and serving.","name":"Wrap the casserole dish in aluminum foil, then bake for 30 minutes. Then remove foil and bake additional 5-7 minutes or until cheese begins to brown. Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting and serving.","url":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#wprm-recipe-40025-step-0-6"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4","ratingCount":"1"},"recipeCategory":["Dinner"],"recipeCuisine":["Mexican"],"keywords":"black beans, casserole, enchiladas, Pumpkin","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 g","calories":"196 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"21 g","proteinContent":"9 g","fatContent":"10 g","saturatedFatContent":"5 g","cholesterolContent":"17 mg","sodiumContent":"580 mg","fiberContent":"9 g","sugarContent":"3 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"3 g"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/lemonsandbasil.com\\/healthy-pumpkin-black-bean-enchilada-casserole\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://lemonsandbasil.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Pumpkin-Enchilada-Casserole1.gif',
            'ingredients' => '["1 tbsp coconut oil","2 garlic cloves (minced)","1\\/2 red onion (diced)","1 bell peppers (diced)","1 can black beans (rinsed and drained)","1 cup cooked pumpkin puree (I used organic canned pumpkin)","2 tsp chili powder","1 tsp cumin","1 tsp smoked paprika","\\u00bc tsp ground black pepper","\\u00be cup mild salsa","6 Xtreme Wellness High Fiber tortillas (cut into 2\\" strips)","2 cups enchilada sauce","2 cups cheddar or Mexican blend cheese shredded","Garnishing: Fresh Cilantro (Chives, Sour Cream, Cotija cheese, Avocado)"]',
            'directions' => '["Preheat oven to 425 degrees.","Add coconut oil, red onion, bell pepper, and garlic to large sauce pan, and cook over medium heat for 5-7 minutes or until onions are translucent.","Add black beans, pumpkin puree, salsa and all seasonings (chili powder through black pepper) then stir to combine.","In a large 9x13 baking dish, add 1\\/4-1\\/2 cup enchilada sauce to the bottom, followed by first layer of tortillas.","On top of the tortillas, add 1\\/3 black bean, pumpkin and veggie mixture, followed by approximately 2\\/3 cup shredded cheese.","Repeat with enchilada sauce, tortillas, black bean\\/veggie mix and cheese two more times, finishing with the enchilada sauce and cheese on top.","Wrap the casserole dish in aluminum foil, then bake for 30 minutes. Then remove foil and bake additional 5-7 minutes or until cheese begins to brown. Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting and serving."]',
