"name":"Rainbow Plant Life","description":"Master vegan cooking at home.","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization","name":"Rainbow Plant Life","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/08\\/RPL-Logo-SQUARE.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/08\\/RPL-Logo-SQUARE.png","width":453,"height":453,"caption":"Rainbow Plant Life"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/rainbowplantlife","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\/","https:\\/\\/pinterest.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/channel\\/UCDbZvuDA_tZ6XP5wKKFuemQ"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d","name":"Nisha Vora","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Nisha Vora"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/about-nisha\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/rainbowplantlife@gmail.com"],"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/about-nisha\\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Instant Pot Butternut Squash Lentil Curry","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d"},"description":"With just a few minutes of hands-on cooking, this Instant Pot Butternut Squash Lentil Curry will become your go-to for weeknight meals. It\\u2019s hearty, healthy comfort food at its finest (and easiest).","datePublished":"2018-11-28T13:09:36+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/11\\/327_image-asset.jpg","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/11\\/327_image-asset-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/11\\/327_image-asset-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/11\\/327_image-asset-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["6"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT45M","totalTime":"PT60M","recipeIngredient":["1 1\\/2 tablespoons unrefined (virgin coconut oil, divided)","1 teaspoon whole cumin seeds","1 medium yellow onion, (diced)","1 1\\/2 teaspoons kosher salt, (divided)","6 garlic cloves, (minced)","1 (2-inch) piece of fresh ginger, (finely minced or grated)","1 tablespoon curry powder","1 1\\/2 teaspoons ground turmeric","1\\/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper ((optional, for spiciness))","2 tablespoons water","5-6 cups (700-850g) peeled and roughly chopped butternut squash, ((can buy pre-cut squash)*)","1 1\\/2 cups (360 mL) low-sodium vegetable broth","1 cup brown lentils or green lentils","1 (15-ounce\\/ (400 mL) can \\u201clite\\u201d coconut milk","3 tablespoons cashew butter ((can substitute with almond butter or tahini))","4 ounces baby kale or baby spinach ((or 4-5 large handfuls) )","1 tablespoon fresh lemon or lime juice","1 large handful fresh cilantro, (roughly chopped)","For serving: white rice and\\/or flatbread"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Instant Pot Directions","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Rinse the lentils and drain them.","name":"Rinse the lentils and drain them.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Select the Saut\\u00e9 setting on the Instant Pot and after a few minutes, add 1\\/2 tablespoon of the coconut oil, followed by the cumin seeds. Toss for 30-60 seconds until lightly browned and very fragrant.","name":"Select the Saut\\u00e9 setting on the Instant Pot and after a few minutes, add 1\\/2 tablespoon of the coconut oil, followed by the cumin seeds. Toss for 30-60 seconds until lightly browned and very fragrant.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the remaining 1 tablespoon oil, followed by the onion and 1\\/2 teaspoon of the kosher salt. Cook the onion for 4-5 minutes until lightly browned. Then add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.","name":"Add the remaining 1 tablespoon oil, followed by the onion and 1\\/2 teaspoon of the kosher salt. Cook the onion for 4-5 minutes until lightly browned. Then add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Stir in the the curry powder, turmeric, and cayenne (if using) for 30 seconds, adding the 2 tbsp water to prevent the mixture from drying out too much.","name":"Stir in the the curry powder, turmeric, and cayenne (if using) for 30 seconds, adding the 2 tbsp water to prevent the mixture from drying out too much.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the chopped butternut squash and stir to coat it in the spice mixture. Pour in the vegetable broth and use a wooden spoon or spatula to scrape up any browned bits at the bottom of the pan. Then add the remaining 1 teaspoon kosher salt, the lentils, and coconut milk. Scoop the cashew butter on top but do not stir. This helps prevent the nut butter from sinking to the bottom and possibly triggering the Instant Pot burn warning.","name":"Add the chopped butternut squash and stir to coat it in the spice mixture. Pour in the vegetable broth and use a wooden spoon or spatula to scrape up any browned bits at the bottom of the pan. Then add the remaining 1 teaspoon kosher salt, the lentils, and coconut milk. Scoop the cashew butter on top but do not stir. This helps prevent the nut butter from sinking to the bottom and possibly triggering the Instant Pot burn warning.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Secure the Instant Pot lid and set the Pressure Release to Sealing. Select the Pressure Cook or Manual setting and set the cook time for 10 minutes.","name":"Secure the Instant Pot lid and set the Pressure Release to Sealing. Select the Pressure Cook or Manual setting and set the cook time for 10 minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the timer goes off, allow a natural pressure release. Once the pressure has released, open the pot and stir in the baby kale. Select the Saut\\u00e9 setting and heat for about 2 minutes or until the kale has wilted, then select Cancel. Add the lemon or lime juice and the cilantro and stir to combine.","name":"Once the timer goes off, allow a natural pressure release. Once the pressure has released, open the pot and stir in the baby kale. Select the Saut\\u00e9 setting and heat for about 2 minutes or until the kale has wilted, then select Cancel. Add the lemon or lime juice and the cilantro and stir to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve the butternut squash lentil curry over white rice or with flatbread.","name":"Serve the butternut squash lentil curry over white rice or with flatbread.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-0-7"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Stovetop Directions","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat a deep, heavy skillet or a Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add 1 1\\/2 tablespoons of coconut oil, and once hot, add the cumin seeds and fry for 30-60 seconds until lightly browned and very fragrant.","name":"Heat a deep, heavy skillet or a Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add 1 1\\/2 tablespoons of coconut oil, and once hot, add the cumin seeds and fry for 30-60 seconds until lightly browned and very fragrant.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-1-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the onions and cook until they are translucent, about 5 minutes. Then add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1-2 minutes until lightly golden and fragrant. Add the curry powder, turmeric, and cayenne (if using) and a splash of water, stirring very frequently for 20 to 30 seconds.","name":"Add the onions and cook until they are translucent, about 5 minutes. Then add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1-2 minutes until lightly golden and fragrant. Add the curry powder, turmeric, and cayenne (if using) and a splash of water, stirring very frequently for 20 to 30 seconds.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-1-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the butternut squash, vegetable broth, lentils, coconut milk, and cashew butter. Stir well to combine.","name":"Add the butternut squash, vegetable broth, lentils, coconut milk, and cashew butter. Stir well to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-1-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bring the curry mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat, and simmer for about 30 minutes, until the lentils are tender and the squash is cooked through, stirring every few minutes.","name":"Bring the curry mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat, and simmer for about 30 minutes, until the lentils are tender and the squash is cooked through, stirring every few minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-1-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the baby kale and allow to cook for 1-2 minutes until wilted. Add the lemon or lime juice and the cilantro and stir to combine.","name":"Add the baby kale and allow to cook for 1-2 minutes until wilted. Add the lemon or lime juice and the cilantro and stir to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-1-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve the butternut squash lentil curry over white rice or with flatbread.","name":"Serve the butternut squash lentil curry over white rice or with flatbread.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-5690-step-1-5"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.88","ratingCount":"107","reviewCount":"8"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Awesome thanks! It turned out very yummy","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rebs"},"datePublished":"2026-05-09"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This looks great! In the stovetop instructions are we to add the second portion of the oil at some point? And do we need to add the 2 tb water? The modified instructions don\\u2019t seem to have these steps.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rebs"},"datePublished":"2026-04-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I just made this for the First time &amp; it was so good! My butternut squash kind of melted into the dish, which was delicious! I had previously had to freeze my squash chunks. Even the lentils broke down &amp; were just part of the soup. It was almost like I blended it, but I didn\\u2019t. The flavor &amp; smells were fabulous! We topped ours with some plain yogurt! My husband raved &amp; I will make this again for sure. It was quick &amp; pretty easy to make. Thank you Nisha!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Claire"},"datePublished":"2026-03-27"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I have made this recipe so many times over the last few years\\u2026 sometimes I substitute sweet potato and add extra veggies, or add fresh tumeric. It freezes up beautifully. I always come back to this recipe, I did get the cookbook but honestly, I could eat this one for the rest of my life! It\\u2019s a bit time consuming with prep but mmmmm! \\ud83d\\ude03\\u2764\\ufe0f\\ud83d\\ude0d","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Donni"},"datePublished":"2026-03-18"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This recipe is amazing. Simple to make and the flavor is perfect. I really enjoyed this meal. It is a definite keeper.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Brenda"},"datePublished":"2026-03-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Really yummy and easy, especially if you get pre-cut squash cubes. Gave some of this curry to a friend who really liked it.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Caroline"},"datePublished":"2025-10-25"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Was fantastic! Made the naan to go with it :)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Molli"},"datePublished":"2025-10-16"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"reviewBody":"The first time I made this it was amazing!\\r\\nThis time though, it looks weird. It seems too mushy and like the coconut milk broke into a bunch of tiny tiny pieces throughout instead of blending in(?) if that makes sense. Haven\\u2019t tasted it yet, but it certainly doesn\\u2019t look appetizing.. Any idea of what could have gone wrong?","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Hannah Mudge"},"datePublished":"2025-09-15"}],"recipeCategory":["Dinner"],"recipeCuisine":["Indian-Inspired"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VeganDiet"],"keywords":"black beluga lentils, butternut squash, curry, gluten-free, instant pot, soy-free","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"344 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"44 g","proteinContent":"12 g","fatContent":"14 g","saturatedFatContent":"10 g","sodiumContent":"678 mg","fiberContent":"14 g","sugarContent":"5 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"4 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/instant-pot-butternut-squash-lentil-curry\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://rainbowplantlife.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/lentilpumpkincurry281of129-scaled.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["1 1\\/2 tablespoons unrefined (virgin coconut oil, divided)","1 teaspoon whole cumin seeds","1 medium yellow onion, (diced)","1 1\\/2 teaspoons kosher salt, (divided)","6 garlic cloves, (minced)","1 (2-inch) piece of fresh ginger, (finely minced or grated)","1 tablespoon curry powder","1 1\\/2 teaspoons ground turmeric","1\\/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper ((optional, for spiciness))","2 tablespoons water","5-6 cups (700-850g) peeled and roughly chopped butternut squash, ((can buy pre-cut squash)*)","1 1\\/2 cups (360 mL) low-sodium vegetable broth","1 cup brown lentils or green lentils","1 (15-ounce\\/ (400 mL) can \\u201clite\\u201d coconut milk","3 tablespoons cashew butter ((can substitute with almond butter or tahini))","4 ounces baby kale or baby spinach ((or 4-5 large handfuls) )","1 tablespoon fresh lemon or lime juice","1 large handful fresh cilantro, (roughly chopped)","For serving: white rice and\\/or flatbread"]',
            'directions' => '{"Instant Pot Directions":["Rinse the lentils and drain them.","Select the Saut\\u00e9 setting on the Instant Pot and after a few minutes, add 1\\/2 tablespoon of the coconut oil, followed by the cumin seeds. Toss for 30-60 seconds until lightly browned and very fragrant.","Add the remaining 1 tablespoon oil, followed by the onion and 1\\/2 teaspoon of the kosher salt. Cook the onion for 4-5 minutes until lightly browned. Then add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.","Stir in the the curry powder, turmeric, and cayenne (if using) for 30 seconds, adding the 2 tbsp water to prevent the mixture from drying out too much.","Add the chopped butternut squash and stir to coat it in the spice mixture. Pour in the vegetable broth and use a wooden spoon or spatula to scrape up any browned bits at the bottom of the pan. Then add the remaining 1 teaspoon kosher salt, the lentils, and coconut milk. Scoop the cashew butter on top but do not stir. This helps prevent the nut butter from sinking to the bottom and possibly triggering the Instant Pot burn warning.","Secure the Instant Pot lid and set the Pressure Release to Sealing. Select the Pressure Cook or Manual setting and set the cook time for 10 minutes.","Once the timer goes off, allow a natural pressure release. Once the pressure has released, open the pot and stir in the baby kale. Select the Saut\\u00e9 setting and heat for about 2 minutes or until the kale has wilted, then select Cancel. Add the lemon or lime juice and the cilantro and stir to combine.","Serve the butternut squash lentil curry over white rice or with flatbread."],"Stovetop Directions":["Heat a deep, heavy skillet or a Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add 1 1\\/2 tablespoons of coconut oil, and once hot, add the cumin seeds and fry for 30-60 seconds until lightly browned and very fragrant.","Add the onions and cook until they are translucent, about 5 minutes. Then add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1-2 minutes until lightly golden and fragrant. Add the curry powder, turmeric, and cayenne (if using) and a splash of water, stirring very frequently for 20 to 30 seconds.","Add the butternut squash, vegetable broth, lentils, coconut milk, and cashew butter. Stir well to combine.","Bring the curry mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat, and simmer for about 30 minutes, until the lentils are tender and the squash is cooked through, stirring every few minutes.","Add the baby kale and allow to cook for 1-2 minutes until wilted. Add the lemon or lime juice and the cilantro and stir to combine.","Serve the butternut squash lentil curry over white rice or with flatbread."]}',
