e! It\'s much tastier than takeout and healthier, too. This recipe is vegetarian, vegan and gluten free!","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2015\\/10\\/thai-red-curry-with-vegetables-1.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2015\\/10\\/thai-red-curry-with-vegetables-1.jpg","width":1100,"height":1512,"caption":"This Thai red curry with vegetables is the best! cookieandkate.com"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Thai","item":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/category\\/vegetarian-thai-recipes\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Thai Red Curry with Vegetables"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/","name":"Cookie and Kate","description":"Whole Foods and Vegetarian Recipe Blog","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/#organization","name":"Cookie and Kate","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2024\\/10\\/logo-696.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2024\\/10\\/logo-696.png","width":696,"height":696,"caption":"Cookie and Kate"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/cookieandkate","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/cookieandkate","https:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/cookieandkate","https:\\/\\/www.linkedin.com\\/in\\/kathryne-taylor-20012213\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/cookieandkate\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/user\\/cookieandkate\\/"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/c609c24a34a1976d0a3c1a1b0cd7f46a","name":"Kathryne Taylor","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2024\\/10\\/cropped-kathryne-taylor-200-96x96.jpg","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2024\\/10\\/cropped-kathryne-taylor-200-96x96.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2024\\/10\\/cropped-kathryne-taylor-200-96x96.jpg","caption":"Kathryne Taylor"},"description":"I\'m a vegetable enthusiast, dog lover, mother and bestselling cookbook author. I\'ve been sharing recipes here on Cookie and Kate since 2010, and I\'m always cooking something new in my Kansas City kitchen. Cook with me!","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/about\\/"]},{"@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/","@type":"Recipe","name":"Thai Red Curry with Vegetables","description":"This Thai red curry recipe is so easy to make at home! It\'s much tastier than takeout and healthier, too. Feel free to change up the vegetables (you\'ll need about 3 cups total) and skip the kale if you want a more traditional Thai curry. This recipe is vegetarian, vegan and gluten free for all to enjoy. Recipe yields 4 servings.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cookie and Kate","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/about\\/"},"keywords":"Thai red curry","image":["https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2015\\/10\\/thai-red-curry-with-vegetables-1-225x225.jpg","https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2015\\/10\\/thai-red-curry-with-vegetables-1-260x195.jpg","https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2015\\/10\\/thai-red-curry-with-vegetables-1-320x180.jpg","https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/images\\/2015\\/10\\/thai-red-curry-with-vegetables-1.jpg"],"url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/","recipeIngredient":["1 \\u00bc\\u00a0cups brown jasmine rice or long-grain brown rice, rinsed","1 tablespoon coconut oil or olive oil","1 small white onion,\\u00a0chopped (about 1 cup)","Pinch of salt, more to taste","1 tablespoon finely grated fresh ginger (about a 1-inch nub of ginger)","2 cloves garlic, pressed or minced","1 red bell pepper, sliced into thin 2-inch long strips","1 yellow, orange or green bell pepper, sliced into thin 2-inch long strips","3 carrots, peeled and sliced on the diagonal into \\u00bc-inch thick rounds (about 1 cup)","2 tablespoons Thai red curry paste*","1 can (14 ounces) regular coconut milk**","&frac12; cup water","1 &frac12; cups packed thinly sliced kale (tough ribs removed first), preferably the Tuscan\\/lacinato\\/dinosaur variety","1 &frac12; teaspoons coconut sugar or turbinado (raw) sugar or brown sugar","1 tablespoon tamari or soy sauce***","2 teaspoons rice vinegar or fresh lime juice","Garnishes\\/sides: handful of chopped fresh basil or cilantro, optional red pepper flakes, optional sriracha or chili garlic sauce"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To cook the rice, bring a large pot of water to boil. Add the rinsed rice and continue boiling for 30 minutes, reducing heat as necessary to prevent overflow. Remove from heat, drain the rice and return the rice to pot. Cover and let the rice rest for 10 minutes or longer, until you&#8217;re ready to serve. Just before serving, season the rice to taste with salt and fluff it with a fork.","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#instruction-step-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To make the curry, warm a large skillet with deep sides over medium heat. Once it\\u2019s hot, add the oil. Add the onion and a sprinkle of salt and cook, stirring often, until the onion has softened and is turning translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the ginger and garlic and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds, while stirring continuously.","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#instruction-step-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the bell peppers and carrots. Cook until the bell peppers are fork-tender, 3 to 5 more minutes, stirring occasionally. Then add the curry paste and cook, stirring often, for 2 minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#instruction-step-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the coconut milk, water, kale and sugar, and stir to combine. Bring the mixture to a simmer over medium heat. Reduce heat as necessary to maintain a gentle simmer and cook until the peppers, carrots and kale have softened to your liking, about 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#instruction-step-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove the pot from the heat and season with tamari and rice vinegar. Add salt (I added &frac14; teaspoon for optimal flavor), to taste. If the curry needs a little more punch, add &frac12; teaspoon more tamari, or for more acidity, add &frac12; teaspoon more rice vinegar. Divide rice and curry into bowls and garnish with chopped cilantro and a sprinkle of red pepper flakes, if you&#8217;d like. If you love spicy curries, serve with sriracha or chili garlic sauce on the side.","url":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#instruction-step-5"}],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT30M","totalTime":"PT40M","recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"recipeCategory":"Entree","cookingMethod":"Stovetop","recipeCuisine":"Thai","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","reviewCount":"1262","ratingValue":"4.9"},"nutrition":{"servingSize":null,"calories":"340 calories","sugarContent":"9.3 g","sodiumContent":"473.3 mg","fatContent":"11.3 g","saturatedFatContent":"8 g","transFatContent":"0 g","carbohydrateContent":"56.3 g","fiberContent":"5.6 g","proteinContent":"8.3 g","cholesterolContent":"0 mg","@type":"nutritionInformation"},"video":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"\\u201dThai","description":"\\u201dWatch","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/videos\\/&rdquo;Ooc4kv3K&rdquo;.mp4","thumbnailUrl":["https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/thumbs\\/&rdquo;Ooc4kv3K&rdquo;-720.jpg"],"uploadDate":"1970-01-01T00:00:00+00:00"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Prerna"},"datePublished":"2025-11-29","reviewBody":"It\\u2019s one of my favorite recipes from you, have been making in for about 7 years now and love how it turns out. I tweak the veggies here and there a bit but keep everything else consistent. Always make extra as this makes great leftovers. Thank you!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Amy"},"datePublished":"2026-03-25","reviewBody":"Made this for dinner tonight and it was incredible !! Thank you for sharing this recipe :)"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Adam R"},"datePublished":"2026-04-05","reviewBody":"House favorite! My 2 year old loves it. I add extra veggies and chickpeas and call it rainbow curry. I only wish I didnt have to save it all for the kids."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Julie"},"datePublished":"2025-11-30","reviewBody":"I love this recipe but as a UK cook I have no idea about cup measurements and have to Google conversion to grams every time or if I\'m in a rush just guess. Please could you consider adding the gram equivalent to recipes? Thank you."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Megan"},"datePublished":"2025-12-08","reviewBody":"So delicious!!!!! It really is as good as a restaurant."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Reuben Weiss"},"datePublished":"2025-12-20","reviewBody":"I love this recipe. When I managed a Kitchen in Fiji years ago, with 4 Fijian ladies, we made it many times. It was well loved by all. Now I am back in the US, and want to make it for a rather unorthodox holiday dinner. One of my guests is diabetic and so I wondered whether an alternative sweetener might work -- like monk fruit. Any thoughts about that?\\r\\nThank you for all of your wonderful recipes."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Arti"},"datePublished":"2025-12-25","reviewBody":"Hi\\r\\nI made this recipe first time and it is an instant hit for my family. The recipe is simple and a sure success. This one matches to a restaurant level taste. I added pineapple and reduced the sugar a bit. Thank you."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Meighan"},"datePublished":"2026-01-04","reviewBody":"Hi Kate-\\r\\nThanks so much for this wonderful recipe. I ended up adding garbanzo beans and baked tofu(thanks for that recipe too!) for added protein. I also added fried eggplant cuz it\'s one of my fave things. The lime juice adds a great kick!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Ash"},"datePublished":"2026-01-06","reviewBody":"If I could give this 10000 stars I would.\\r\\nThis is in our fortnightly meal plan!\\r\\n*standing ovation* \\r\\nLove,\\r\\nTwo very happy and full aussies"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Vanessa Fromm"},"datePublished":"2026-01-10","reviewBody":"This recipe with the added tofu is now a staple in my family. I just cube the tofu and add at the end. It is delicious!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lin"},"datePublished":"2026-01-24","reviewBody":"Forgot to rate the A+ curry. Sorry. Five stars."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Winnie"},"datePublished":"2026-01-26","reviewBody":"Delicious! I needed a simple red curry recipe and your\'s looked easiest. I cooked up some chicken before and used the same pan to follow the rest of the recipe, removed kale, added potato and mushroom, and put the chicken back in as it was simmering. Amazing!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Patti"},"datePublished":"2026-01-27","reviewBody":"Outstanding!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Christine"},"datePublished":"2026-02-03","reviewBody":"I love this recipe so much and have made it many times as is. I\\u2019m having a dinner party this week and two friends are allergic to coconut. My question is would this be okay with alternatives like perhaps Greek yogurt, evaporated milk\\/ condensed milk? Any thoughts are appreciated!! \\u2764\\ufe0f"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lara"},"datePublished":"2026-02-03","reviewBody":"We make this often in our household and I love to add broccoli and sometimes I use spinach as opposed to kale.... It is consistently wonderful! I add the whole little jar of Thai red curry and then put chili crisp on the table for whomever wants even more heat. Strongly encourage everyone to try this! Thank you for such a great recipe!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Maggie"},"datePublished":"2026-02-12","reviewBody":"So delicious! I saut\\u00e9ed tofu cubes first, then added the onion. I used baby spinach instead of kale, and sprinkled peanuts on top as a garnish. Otherwise, no changes. This recipe is a keeper!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rachel"},"datePublished":"2026-02-18","reviewBody":"So delicious!!!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Mary"},"datePublished":"2026-02-23","reviewBody":"so delicious!!! I left out the sugar to make it a little healthier"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kim"},"datePublished":"2026-02-24","reviewBody":"My family loves this recipe! It has become one of the staples in our home. Thank you for sharing your talents."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"May"},"datePublished":"2026-04-05","reviewBody":"Would it change the flavor if I just add potatoes, no other vegis?"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Karina Avakyan"},"datePublished":"2026-03-01","reviewBody":"Amazing recipe, perfect! Now it is my go to when I cook Thai curries, I used mushrooms instead of kale and added a little soft tofu for protein, so delicious with the rice, it is great that we can use lots of different veggies with this wonderful dish."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rae Quirke"},"datePublished":"2026-04-22","reviewBody":"Loved it the Thai vegetable curry. It\\u2019s a keeper"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"May"},"datePublished":"2026-05-06","reviewBody":"How do I add chicken to this recipe?"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Grace"},"datePublished":"2026-06-16","reviewBody":"My go to recipe for thai red curry! Have been using for years. SO TASTY!!!\\r\\n\\r\\nThank you so much :)"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Caroline Daniel"},"datePublished":"2026-06-22","reviewBody":"I made this with crispy tempeh for protein and everyone was a fan-even my picky 10 year-old. He did request less vegetables, but still ate all the vegetables . I served it with thai basil, cilantro and lime. Next time I will double bc we did not have leftovers and this would pack a great lunch the next day."}],"datePublished":"2015-10-20","@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/cookieandkate.com\\/thai-red-curry-recipe\\/"}]}',
