                'user_id' => 1,
                'description' => 'Cabbage melts into silky sweetness in this nourishing yet creamy Indian-spiced cabbage curry. You won’t even realize you’re eating cabbage!',
            'content' => '{"@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"Article","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#article","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/"},"author":{"name":"Nisha Vora","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d"},"headline":"Creamy Cabbage Curry","datePublished":"2025-10-21T21:36:19+00:00","dateModified":"2025-10-21T21:38:27+00:00","wordCount":2385,"commentCount":289,"publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-scaled.jpg","articleSection":["Recipes","Dinner"],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"CommentAction","name":"Comment","target":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#respond"]}]},{"@type":["WebPage","FAQPage"],"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/","name":"Creamy Cabbage Curry - Rainbow Plant Life","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#primaryimage"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#primaryimage"},"thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-scaled.jpg","datePublished":"2025-10-21T21:36:19+00:00","dateModified":"2025-10-21T21:38:27+00:00","description":"Cabbage melts into silky sweetness in this nourishing yet creamy Indian-spiced cabbage curry. You won\\u2019t even realize you\\u2019re eating cabbage!","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#breadcrumb"},"mainEntity":[{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993318522"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993359336"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993359948"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993360715"}],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-scaled.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-scaled.jpg","width":1200,"height":1500,"caption":"Curry topped with cilantro and serrano slices, served in a skillet with naan."},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/category\\/recipes\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Dinner","item":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/category\\/recipes\\/dinner\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Creamy Cabbage Curry"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/","name":"Rainbow Plant Life","description":"Master vegan cooking at home.","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#organization","name":"Rainbow Plant Life","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/08\\/RPL-Logo-SQUARE.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/08\\/RPL-Logo-SQUARE.png","width":453,"height":453,"caption":"Rainbow Plant Life"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/rainbowplantlife","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\/","https:\\/\\/pinterest.com\\/rainbowplantlife\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/channel\\/UCDbZvuDA_tZ6XP5wKKFuemQ"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d","name":"Nisha Vora","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/d8da3061e552a5f9f06550473846d6956b8804d85b2bcec84006babc4a85262e?s=96&d=mm&r=g","caption":"Nisha Vora"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/about-nisha\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/rainbowplantlife@gmail.com"],"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/about-nisha\\/"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993318522","position":1,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993318522","name":"What can I use instead of coconut milk?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Follow these steps to make a cashew cream which can be used in place of the coconut milk:<br\\/><br\\/>1. Soak \\u00bd cup (70g) of raw, unsalted cashews in water overnight, or do a quick soak by adding them to a saucepan, covering with water, and boiling for 15 minutes. Drain the cashews and rinse well.<br\\/>2. Add \\u00bd cup (120 mL) of water to a small-capacity high-powered blender (small blender jug, 32 oz \\/ 1L or smaller) [see note below]. Add the drained cashews, 1 TBSP of freshly squeezed lemon juice, and \\u00bd tsp kosher salt.<br\\/>3. Blend for about 2 minutes, starting on low and gradually moving up to high speed. Scrape down the sides as you go and blend until it\\u2019s completely smooth and no cashew bits remain.<br\\/><br\\/><strong>Note:<\\/strong> If you only have a large-capacity high-powered blender, you\\u2019ll need to double the ingredients, as there isn\\u2019t enough liquid here to blend in a large container. A food processor can be used, but the texture won\\u2019t be as smooth. In a food processor, blend the ingredients for approximately 4 minutes.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993359336","position":2,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993359336","name":"I have a nut allergy\\u2014what can I use instead of almond butter?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No nuts, no problem! Sub with tahini!","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993359948","position":3,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993359948","name":"How should I serve this cabbage curry?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"I love it with <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/vegan-naan\\/\\">vegan naan<\\/a> or the <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.angelbakeries.com\\/pita-pages\\/classic%C2%A0white\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">fluffy pita bread from Angel Bakery<\\/a>, but you can also serve it with rice. And voil\\u00e0, you have a complete, balanced, and truly delicious meal.\\u00a0<br\\/><br\\/>But if you\\u2019re looking for a little something extra on your plate, you could serve it with a green salad or an Indian kachumber salad (sliced or diced cucumbers, tomatoes, and red onions dressed with lime juice, salt, pepper, chopped cilantro, and a bit of garam masala or chaat masala, if you like).","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993360715","position":4,"url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#faq-question-1760993360715","name":"How do you store leftovers? Can you freeze it?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Store leftovers in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 5 days (and get excited\\u2014this meal tastes even better the next day as the flavors and spices have a chance to mingle).\\u00a0<br\\/><br\\/>The curry thickens A LOT in the fridge because of the coconut milk, but once you heat it up in the microwave it will return to its original texture, more or less. If you are heating it up on the stove, you might want to add a splash of water to thin it out.<br\\/><br\\/>You can freeze leftovers for up to 3 months, but be sure to leave a bit of headspace in the container.<br\\/><br\\/><strong>Defrosting tip<\\/strong>: You\\u2019ll get the best results by defrosting the curry in the fridge first, rather than heating it straight from frozen. I love using these <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/geni.us\\/UryzMfY\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\\">Souper Cubes<\\/a> to freeze leftovers in individual portions. You\'ll likely want to thin the curry with a bit of water as you\\u2019re heating it up.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Creamy Cabbage Curry","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/7943c9c8c6cf9cec898fd08ad2629b4d"},"description":"If you think cabbage can\\u2019t be luxurious, think again! This creamy cabbage curry delivers nourishment while being seriously indulgent. The cabbage melts down into silky sweetness and mingles with warming Indian spices before simmering with coconut milk and chickpeas for a cozy, complete meal.","datePublished":"2025-10-21T21:36:19+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-scaled.jpg","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/10\\/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["4"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT35M","totalTime":"PT50M","recipeIngredient":["2 tablespoons (28g) neutral oil of choice ((such as avocado oil))","4 fat garlic cloves (21g), (chopped)","1 to 3 serrano peppers, (finely chopped (3 for spicy!))","8 cups (400 to 480g) green cabbage, (shredded or thinly sliced (see Note 1))","Diamond Crystal kosher salt and freshly cracked black pepper ((see Note 2))","2 tablespoons (30g) tomato paste","2 teaspoons Kashmiri chili powder ((see Note 3))","1 \\u00bd teaspoons ground coriander","1 \\u00bd teaspoons ground cumin","\\u00bd teaspoon ground turmeric","8 ounces (227g) ripe tomatoes, (finely chopped (see Note 4))","1 (13.5 oz \\/ 400 mL) can full-fat coconut milk","1 (15 oz \\/ 425g) can chickpeas, (drained and rinsed)","2 tablespoons (32g) almond butter or cashew butter ((unsweetened, see Note 5))","1 teaspoon garam masala","1 lime, (juiced)","1 cup (16g) fresh cilantro (leaves and tender stems, chopped)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat the oil in a 12-inch saut\\u00e9 pan over medium-high for a few minutes, or until shimmering. Add the garlic and serrano pepper and stir very frequently for 30 to 60 seconds until fragrant (don&#39;t let the garlic brown).","name":"Heat the oil in a 12-inch saut\\u00e9 pan over medium-high for a few minutes, or until shimmering. Add the garlic and serrano pepper and stir very frequently for 30 to 60 seconds until fragrant (don&#39;t let the garlic brown).","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-46659-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the cabbage and use tongs to coat it into the oil and aromatics, tossing well so the garlic and serrano pepper aren&#39;t stuck to the bottom of the pan. Season with \\u00bd teaspoon kosher salt. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until tender, silky, and browned in spots.NOTE: If it starts to brown quickly, lower the heat to medium and\\/or add a splash of water to deglaze.Multitasking: While the cabbage cooks: (a) In a small bowl combine the tomato paste, Kashmiri chili powder, coriander, cumin, turmeric, 1 teaspoon kosher salt, and lots of black pepper; (b) finely chop the tomatoes and set aside.","name":"Add the cabbage and use tongs to coat it into the oil and aromatics, tossing well so the garlic and serrano pepper aren&#39;t stuck to the bottom of the pan. Season with \\u00bd teaspoon kosher salt. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until tender, silky, and browned in spots.NOTE: If it starts to brown quickly, lower the heat to medium and\\/or add a splash of water to deglaze.Multitasking: While the cabbage cooks: (a) In a small bowl combine the tomato paste, Kashmiri chili powder, coriander, cumin, turmeric, 1 teaspoon kosher salt, and lots of black pepper; (b) finely chop the tomatoes and set aside.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-46659-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To the cabbage, add the tomato paste-spice mixture. Stir very frequently for 2 minutes, coating the tomato paste into the cabbage. If it dries out, add a splash of water. Add the tomatoes and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, or until softened and almost melting into the cabbage.","name":"To the cabbage, add the tomato paste-spice mixture. Stir very frequently for 2 minutes, coating the tomato paste into the cabbage. If it dries out, add a splash of water. Add the tomatoes and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, or until softened and almost melting into the cabbage.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-46659-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour in the coconut milk, chickpeas, almond butter, and \\u00bd teaspoon kosher salt. Simmer uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring every few minutes to prevent sticking. The curry will thicken, so if you want a looser texture, add \\u00bc to \\u00bd cup water (60 to 120 mL).NOTE: I prefer simmering for 20 minutes, as it gives the ingredients enough time to mask the coconut flavor, but you can taste at 15 minutes and check.","name":"Pour in the coconut milk, chickpeas, almond butter, and \\u00bd teaspoon kosher salt. Simmer uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring every few minutes to prevent sticking. The curry will thicken, so if you want a looser texture, add \\u00bc to \\u00bd cup water (60 to 120 mL).NOTE: I prefer simmering for 20 minutes, as it gives the ingredients enough time to mask the coconut flavor, but you can taste at 15 minutes and check.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-46659-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove from the heat. Stir in the garam masala, several squeezes of lime juice, and the chopped cilantro. Season to taste with salt or more lime juice as desired.","name":"Remove from the heat. Stir in the garam masala, several squeezes of lime juice, and the chopped cilantro. Season to taste with salt or more lime juice as desired.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-46659-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve with cooked rice or flatbread. NOTE: leftovers will thicken considerably in the fridge, so you may want to thin it out with some water on the stove.","name":"Serve with cooked rice or flatbread. NOTE: leftovers will thicken considerably in the fridge, so you may want to thin it out with some water on the stove.","url":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#wprm-recipe-46659-step-0-5"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.98","ratingCount":"131","reviewCount":"8"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I only ever started cooking vegetarian meals about 3 years ago, and this is my favourite vegan meal.\\r\\nI am eating it right now! It\'s so delicious and creamy.\\r\\nI do add leek and fresh ginger and turmeric, and I use red cabbage, coconut cream, tahini and tinned tomatoes and no tomato paste.\\r\\nIt\'s a nice recipe to cook and I always can\'t wait to eat it!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sharon"},"datePublished":"2026-06-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Great recipe! I cook Indian food quite often and this is easily the best cabbage curry I\'ve tasted. I used the almond butter as recommended and it was delicious. I\'ll definitely be making it again. Thanks for sharing.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Darrel"},"datePublished":"2026-05-30"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"my picky MIL had three helpings! I didn\'t add any chilies at all and subbed with paprika as you suggested. really easy and delicious! I could change it up - tofu or potatoes instead of chickpeas next time","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lori"},"datePublished":"2026-05-29"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Deliciously creamy from the coconut milk\\/cream and the nut butter. And sweet from the cabbage. Amazing recipe as always Nisha thank you!! This dish is a banger!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Anthony L"},"datePublished":"2026-05-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is so good! I used the suggestion for paprika and cayenne as a replacement for the chili powder. My husband and I are eating this as I write. I was skeptical of some of the ingredients, but they work so well together!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Trish"},"datePublished":"2026-05-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Absolutely fantastic! My carnivore husband had two servings and my teenage son thought it was delicious. (I, too, had a small second serving.) Since I\\u2019m allergic to almonds and sesame, I substituted peanut butter. I was impressed by the phenomenal flavor and also my family\\u2019s acceptance of a veggie-heavy dish. This is definitely a make-again meal. Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kathy Biallas"},"datePublished":"2026-05-16"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I\'ve since made this so many times, it\'s definitely a staple in our household and I always double the recipe so that I can freeze the leftovers!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Merlijn"},"datePublished":"2026-05-15"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Oh my God, this was AMAZING!!!!! Thank you so much for the recipe!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kat"},"datePublished":"2026-05-08"}],"recipeCategory":["Dinner","Lunch"],"recipeCuisine":["Indian-Inspired"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/GlutenFreeDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VeganDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VegetarianDiet"],"keywords":"cabbage curry, cabbage with curry, curry cabbage, Indian cabbage curry","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"453.1 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"35.1 g","proteinContent":"11.6 g","fatContent":"31.4 g","saturatedFatContent":"17.8 g","sodiumContent":"695.44 mg","fiberContent":"9.93 g","sugarContent":"8.12 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"10.24 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/rainbowplantlife.com\\/cabbage-curry\\/"}]}',
                'image' => 'https://rainbowplantlife.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Cabbage-Curry-hero-1-scaled.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["2 tablespoons (28g) neutral oil of choice ((such as avocado oil))","4 fat garlic cloves (21g), (chopped)","1 to 3 serrano peppers, (finely chopped (3 for spicy!))","8 cups (400 to 480g) green cabbage, (shredded or thinly sliced (see Note 1))","Diamond Crystal kosher salt and freshly cracked black pepper ((see Note 2))","2 tablespoons (30g) tomato paste","2 teaspoons Kashmiri chili powder ((see Note 3))","1 \\u00bd teaspoons ground coriander","1 \\u00bd teaspoons ground cumin","\\u00bd teaspoon ground turmeric","8 ounces (227g) ripe tomatoes, (finely chopped (see Note 4))","1 (13.5 oz \\/ 400 mL) can full-fat coconut milk","1 (15 oz \\/ 425g) can chickpeas, (drained and rinsed)","2 tablespoons (32g) almond butter or cashew butter ((unsweetened, see Note 5))","1 teaspoon garam masala","1 lime, (juiced)","1 cup (16g) fresh cilantro (leaves and tender stems, chopped)"]',
            'directions' => '["Heat the oil in a 12-inch saut\\u00e9 pan over medium-high for a few minutes, or until shimmering. Add the garlic and serrano pepper and stir very frequently for 30 to 60 seconds until fragrant (don&#39;t let the garlic brown).","Add the cabbage and use tongs to coat it into the oil and aromatics, tossing well so the garlic and serrano pepper aren&#39;t stuck to the bottom of the pan. Season with \\u00bd teaspoon kosher salt. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until tender, silky, and browned in spots.NOTE: If it starts to brown quickly, lower the heat to medium and\\/or add a splash of water to deglaze.Multitasking: While the cabbage cooks: (a) In a small bowl combine the tomato paste, Kashmiri chili powder, coriander, cumin, turmeric, 1 teaspoon kosher salt, and lots of black pepper; (b) finely chop the tomatoes and set aside.","To the cabbage, add the tomato paste-spice mixture. Stir very frequently for 2 minutes, coating the tomato paste into the cabbage. If it dries out, add a splash of water. Add the tomatoes and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, or until softened and almost melting into the cabbage.","Pour in the coconut milk, chickpeas, almond butter, and \\u00bd teaspoon kosher salt. Simmer uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring every few minutes to prevent sticking. The curry will thicken, so if you want a looser texture, add \\u00bc to \\u00bd cup water (60 to 120 mL).NOTE: I prefer simmering for 20 minutes, as it gives the ingredients enough time to mask the coconut flavor, but you can taste at 15 minutes and check.","Remove from the heat. Stir in the garam masala, several squeezes of lime juice, and the chopped cilantro. Season to taste with salt or more lime juice as desired.","Serve with cooked rice or flatbread. NOTE: leftovers will thicken considerably in the fridge, so you may want to thin it out with some water on the stove."]',
                'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"453.1 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"35.1 g","proteinContent":"11.6 g","fatContent":"31.4 g","saturatedFatContent":"17.8 g","sodiumContent":"695.44 mg","fiberContent":"9.93 g","sugarContent":"8.12 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"10.24 g","servingSize":"1 serving"}]',
                'slug' => 'creamy-cabbage-curry',
                'raw_data' => NULL,
                'category' => 'Dinner, Lunch',
