hat are the health benefits of coconut milk?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Coconut milk is rich in healthy fats that support satiety, hormone balance, and brain function, especially its medium-chain triglycerides (MCTs). It also provides antioxidants and minerals like manganese and copper that help support metabolism and overall immune health.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/coconut-lime-tofu-soup-with-rice\\/#faq-question-1729621560710","position":3,"url":"https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/coconut-lime-tofu-soup-with-rice\\/#faq-question-1729621560710","name":"Is this recipe gluten free?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"As long as you use tamari instead of soy sauce.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Coconut Lime Tofu Soup With Rice","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/9672699ccfbdf3802f89f9b9384e801d"},"description":"This Coconut Lime Tofu Soup With Rice is a deliciou","datePublished":"2025-11-13T19:45:38+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/IMG_2025-11-13-132228.jpeg","https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/IMG_2025-11-13-132228-500x500.jpeg","https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/IMG_2025-11-13-132228-500x375.jpeg","https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/IMG_2025-11-13-132228-480x270.jpeg"],"recipeYield":["5"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT29M","recipeIngredient":["1 tablespoon sesame oil","1 bunch scallions - finely chopped (reserve 2-3 tablespoons of the green parts for topping soup)","1 cup sliced bell pepper (from 1 large or 2 smaller bell peppers)","1 cup chopped green beans","4-6 cloves garlic - minced (adjust to your garlic preference)","1 jalapeno - finely chopped","2 tablepoons grated ginger","3\\/4 cup jasmine rice","1 can full fat coconut milk (you can use low fat but the soup will be less creamy)","6-8 cups vegetable broth* (if you&#39;e not vegetarian you can use bone broth for extra protein)","1 bunch cilantro - finely chopped (reserve 2-3 tablespoons for topping the soup)","juice from 2 limes","zest from 1 lime","3 tablespoons soy sauce or tamari (use tamari if gluten free)","salt to taste (I did not add any additional salt but adjust to your preference)","1\\/4-1\\/2 teaspoon black pepper","2-3 tablespoons maple syrup","~14 oz block extra firm tofu - cubed","chili oil\\/chili crisp","sesame seeds"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add sesame oil to a soup pot over medium heat. Add scallions and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes. Add jalapeno, ginger and bell pepper. Cook for another 3 minutes.","name":"Add sesame oil to a soup pot over medium heat. Add scallions and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes. Add jalapeno, ginger and bell pepper. Cook for another 3 minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/coconut-lime-tofu-soup-with-rice\\/#wprm-recipe-15605-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add all remaining ingredients to the pot. Bring to a simmer and cook for 15-20 minutes, until rice is cooked through. Taste and add additional salt\\/pepper if desired.","name":"Add all remaining ingredients to the pot. Bring to a simmer and cook for 15-20 minutes, until rice is cooked through. Taste and add additional salt\\/pepper if desired.","url":"https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/coconut-lime-tofu-soup-with-rice\\/#wprm-recipe-15605-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Divide out soup and serve with desired toppings.","name":"Divide out soup and serve with desired toppings.","url":"https:\\/\\/avocadoskillet.com\\/coconut-lime-tofu-soup-with-rice\\/#wprm-recipe-15605-step-0-2"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"1","reviewCount":"1"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody"