            'user_id' => 1,
            'description' => 'These vibrant Thai chicken and brown rice bowls are topped with a rainbow of crunchy vegetables and drizzled with curried peanut sauce.',
        'content' => '{"headline":"Spicy Thai Chicken and Brown Rice Bowls","@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org","url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055","@type":"Recipe","publisher":{"@type":"NewsMediaOrganization","address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"New York","addressRegion":"NY","postalCode":"10012","streetAddress":"270 Lafayette Street, Ste 1300","addressCountry":"US"},"brand":{"@type":"Brand","name":"The Kitchn"},"description":"The Kitchn provides inspiration for the food our readers want to eat, and resources for them to become the cooks they want to be.","email":"info@thekitchn.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/static\\/logos\\/publisher-logo.png","width":180,"height":46},"masthead":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/team","name":"The Kitchn","parentOrganization":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Apartment Therapy Media LLC","alternateName":"AT Media LLC","url":"https:\\/\\/www.apartmenttherapymedia.com"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/thekitchn\\/","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/thekitchn","https:\\/\\/www.tiktok.com\\/@thekitchn","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/channel\\/UCuNKgYLb0wOoMvclzSlBvbQ","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/thekitchn\\/","https:\\/\\/www.apartmenttherapymedia.com\\/our-brands\\/thekitchn"],"url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com","telephone":"212-966-7174"},"description":"These vibrant Thai chicken and brown rice bowls are topped with a rainbow of crunchy vegetables and drizzled with curried peanut sauce.","brand":{"@type":"Thing","name":"The Kitchn"},"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"1305 cal","carbohydrateContent":"84.7 g","cholesterolContent":"0 mg","fiberContent":"24.3 g","proteinContent":"39.8 g","saturatedFatContent":"65.6 g","sodiumContent":"828.9 mg","sugarContent":"20.1 g","fatContent":"96.4 g","servingSize":"Serves 4","unsaturatedFatContent":"0.0 g"},"suitableforDiet":"https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/GlutenFreeDiet,https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/LowLactoseDiet","recipeCategory":["Dinner","Main dish","Lunch","Poultry dish"],"recipeCuisine":["Thai","Asia"],"recipeIngredient":["1\\/2 cup creamy peanut butter","3 tablespoons tamari or soy sauce","3 tablespoons water","2 tablespoons rice vinegar","2 teaspoons toasted (Asian) sesame oil","1 tablespoon Thai red curry paste","1 tablespoon finely grated peeled fresh ginger","1\\/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)","1 cup short-grain brown rice"," Kosher salt","2 tablespons coconut oil, divided","1 medium red bell pepper, thinly sliced"," Freshly ground black pepper","1 pound ground chicken","2 cloves garlic, minced","1\\/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper","2 medium scallions, thinly sliced, divided","2 cups finely shredded red cabbage","1 cup shredded carrot"," Chopped fresh Thai basil leaves, for garnish"," Chopped roasted peanuts, for garnish"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Make the peanut sauce: ","url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055#instructions-12756-instructiongroup-1","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Step 1: Make the peanut sauce: ","text":"Place all the ingredients in a food processor fitted with the blade attachment or blender. Process continuously until smooth, about 2 minutes; set aside. ","image":null,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055#step-12756-instructiongroup-1-1"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Make the bowls:","url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055#instructions-12756-instructiongroup-2","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Step 1: Make the bowls:","text":"Place the rice, 2 cups of water, and a generous pinch of salt in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and cook until the rice is tender, about 40 minutes. Remove from the heat and set aside to steam, covered, for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cook the bell pepper and chicken.","image":null,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055#step-12756-instructiongroup-2-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Step 2: Make the bowls:","text":"Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add the bell pepper, season with a salt and pepper, and cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, about 4 minutes. Transfer to a plate.","image":null,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055#step-12756-instructiongroup-2-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Step 3: Make the bowls:","text":"Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon oil in the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken, garlic, and cayenne, season with salt and pepper, and cook, breaking up the meat with a wooden spoon, until browned and cooked through, 6 to 8 minutes. Stir in 1\\/2 of the scallions and 2 tablespoons of the reserved peanut sauce, and cook for 1 minute more.","image":null,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055#step-12756-instructiongroup-2-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","name":"Step 4: Make the bowls:","text":"To serve, divide the cabbage and carrots among 4 bowls. Divide the brown rice, ground chicken mixture, and bell pepper among the bowls. Drizzle with the peanut sauce and sprinkle with the basil, remaining scallions, and peanuts.","image":null,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055#step-12756-instructiongroup-2-4"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Recipe Notes","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"Substitutions: Ground turkey can be substituted for ground chicken.Make ahead: The sauce, rice, bell pepper, and chicken can be made up to 1 day in advance and refrigerated in separate airtight containers.Storage: Leftovers can be refrigerated in an airtight container for up to 4 days.Reprinted with permission from Buddha Bowls by Kelli Foster, copyright (c) 2018. Published by Harvard Common Press."}]}],"recipeYield":4,"prepTime":"PT900S","cookTime":"PT2040S","totalTime":"PT2940S","review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"bagel_Lover8"},"reviewBody":"This recipe has made me like brown rice. The chicken and peanut sauce are delicious and I love the addition of carrots and cabbage for freshness. It\'s a keeper!","datePublished":"2024-01-18"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"user_170295837"},"reviewBody":"The sauce is incredibly flavorful.. creamy with just a kiss of heat. Don\'t skip the cabbage as it adds such a nice crunch.","datePublished":"2024-01-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"SalsaMachaEverything"},"reviewBody":"Super flavorful lunch to enjoy all week long! I want to put that peanut sauce on everything -- in fact, I recommend making a double batch of the sauce.","datePublished":"2024-01-18"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"John.doe"},"reviewBody":"The sauce is incredibly flavorful.. creamy with just a kiss of heat. Don\'t skip the cabbage as it adds such a nice crunch.","datePublished":"2024-01-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"doylehr"},"reviewBody":"So good! The combination of fresh and cooked ingredients really made a difference, and the peanut sauce was perfect. Make this, you will be happy you did!","datePublished":"2024-07-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"doylehr1865"},"reviewBody":"So good! The combination of fresh and cooked ingredients really made a difference, and the peanut sauce was perfect. Make this, you will be happy you did!","datePublished":"2024-07-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"bagel_lover82278"},"reviewBody":"This recipe has made me like brown rice. The chicken and peanut sauce are delicious and I love the addition of carrots and cabbage for freshness. It\'s a keeper!","datePublished":"2024-01-18"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"johndoe6164"},"reviewBody":"The sauce is incredibly flavorful.. creamy with just a kiss of heat. Don\'t skip the cabbage as it adds such a nice crunch.","datePublished":"2024-01-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"salsamachaeveryt8944"},"reviewBody":"Super flavorful lunch to enjoy all week long! I want to put that peanut sauce on everything -- in fact, I recommend making a double batch of the sauce.","datePublished":"2024-01-18"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"susanbowen83057"},"reviewBody":"I didn\'t think I liked peanut sauce but this is OUTSTANDING! You won\'t be disappointed! ","datePublished":"2024-09-14"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"christina12663"},"reviewBody":"I made this dish using tofu instead of chicken because my husband and I no longer eat meat. This was absolutely delicious. I will definitely be making this again, using tofu of course, or I\'ll try it with chickpeas.","datePublished":"2024-09-26"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"user7031628"},"reviewBody":"I knew just reading the recipe it would be good. So going to make this on repeat loved it made with ground turkey. ","datePublished":"2025-07-28"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055\\/#aggregate-rating"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055\\/#post-recipe-12756","identifier":{"@type":"PropertyValue","propertyID":"recipeID","value":"12756"},"name":"Spicy Thai Chicken and Brown Rice Bowls","articleSection":"Recipes","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/cdn.apartmenttherapy.info\\/image\\/upload\\/f_auto,q_auto:eco,c_fill,g_auto,w_1500,ar_3:2\\/k%2Farchive%2Fc87ea6ebc20ae1529932d8aeaf80409838ca7bff","image":[{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https:\\/\\/cdn.apartmenttherapy.info\\/image\\/upload\\/f_jpg,q_auto:eco,c_fill,g_auto,w_1500,ar_16:9\\/k%2Farchive%2Fc87ea6ebc20ae1529932d8aeaf80409838ca7bff"},{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https:\\/\\/cdn.apartmenttherapy.info\\/image\\/upload\\/f_jpg,q_auto:eco,c_fill,g_auto,w_1500,ar_4:3\\/k%2Farchive%2Fc87ea6ebc20ae1529932d8aeaf80409838ca7bff"},{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https:\\/\\/cdn.apartmenttherapy.info\\/image\\/upload\\/f_jpg,q_auto:eco,c_fill,g_auto,w_1500,ar_1:1\\/k%2Farchive%2Fc87ea6ebc20ae1529932d8aeaf80409838ca7bff"}],"author":[{"name":"Kelli Foster","URL":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/authors\\/kelli-foster","description":"I\'m a recipe developer, food writer, stylist, and video producer (and The Kitchn\'s Dinner Therapist), with more than 10 years professional experience. Since graduating from The French Culinary Institute, I\'ve authored 3 cookbooks: Buddha Bowls, Plant-Based Buddha Bowls, and The Probiotic Kitchen. ","jobTitle":"","@type":"Person"}],"creator":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kelli Foster"},"keywords":["asian","chicken","dairy-free","dinner","egg-free","gluten-free","ingredient","keeps-well","lunch","main-dish","make-ahead","nuts","oils","pinterest","poultry","recipe","rice-grains","root-vegetables","side-dish","spices","stovetop","thai","updated:2020-02-06","vegetables","vinegar"],"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.thekitchn.com\\/recipe-spicy-thai-chicken-and-brown-rice-bowls-259055","dateCreated":"2018-07-31T10:00:00-04:00","datePublished":"2018-07-31T10:00:00-04:00","dateModified":"2020-02-06T03:25:49-05:00","abstract":null}',
            'image' => 'https://cdn.apartmenttherapy.info/image/upload/f_jpg,q_auto:eco,c_fill,g_auto,w_1500,ar_16:9/k%2Farchive%2Fc87ea6ebc20ae1529932d8aeaf80409838ca7bff',
        'ingredients' => '["1\\/2 cup creamy peanut butter","3 tablespoons tamari or soy sauce","3 tablespoons water","2 tablespoons rice vinegar","2 teaspoons toasted (Asian) sesame oil","1 tablespoon Thai red curry paste","1 tablespoon finely grated peeled fresh ginger","1\\/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)","1 cup short-grain brown rice"," Kosher salt","2 tablespons coconut oil, divided","1 medium red bell pepper, thinly sliced"," Freshly ground black pepper","1 pound ground chicken","2 cloves garlic, minced","1\\/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper","2 medium scallions, thinly sliced, divided","2 cups finely shredded red cabbage","1 cup shredded carrot"," Chopped fresh Thai basil leaves, for garnish"," Chopped roasted peanuts, for garnish"]',
        'directions' => '{"Make the peanut sauce: ":["Place all the ingredients in a food processor fitted with the blade attachment or blender. Process continuously until smooth, about 2 minutes; set aside. "],"Make the bowls:":["Place the rice, 2 cups of water, and a generous pinch of salt in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and cook until the rice is tender, about 40 minutes. Remove from the heat and set aside to steam, covered, for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, cook the bell pepper and chicken.","Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add the bell pepper, season with a salt and pepper, and cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, about 4 minutes. Transfer to a plate.","Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon oil in the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken, garlic, and cayenne, season with salt and pepper, and cook, breaking up the meat with a wooden spoon, until browned and cooked through, 6 to 8 minutes. Stir in 1\\/2 of the scallions and 2 tablespoons of the reserved peanut sauce, and cook for 1 minute more.","To serve, divide the cabbage and carrots among 4 bowls. Divide the brown rice, ground chicken mixture, and bell pepper among the bowls. Drizzle with the peanut sauce and sprinkle with the basil, remaining scallions, and peanuts."],"Recipe Notes":["Substitutions: Ground turkey can be substituted for ground chicken.Make ahead: The sauce, rice, bell pepper, and chicken can be made up to 1 day in advance and refrigerated in separate airtight containers.Storage: Leftovers can be refrigerated in an airtight container for up to 4 days.Reprinted with permission from Buddha Bowls by Kelli Foster, copyright (c) 2018. Published by Harvard Common Press."]}',
            'nutrition' => '{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"1305 cal","carbohydrateContent":"84.7 g","cholesterolContent":"0 mg","fiberContent":"24.3 g","proteinContent":"39.8 g","saturatedFatContent":"65.6 g","sodiumContent":"828.9 mg","sugarContent":"20.1 g","fatContent":"96.4 g","servingSize":"Serves 4","unsaturatedFatContent":"0.0 g"}',
