0M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT45M","recipeIngredient":["1\\/3 cup plain Greek yogurt, (any fat content)","2 tablespoons mayonnaise","3 tablespoons sweet chili sauce","1 teaspoon sriracha","Pinch of salt","1 pound salmon fillets, (skin removed and cut into 1 inch cubes)","2 tablespoons low sodium tamari or soy sauce","1 tablespoon sweet chili sauce","1 tablespoon rice vinegar","1\\/2 teaspoon garlic powder","2 cups diced Persian or English cucumbers","1\\/2 cup shelled edamame","2 green onions, (thinly sliced)","2 tablespoons chopped cilantro","2 teaspoons sesame seeds","Juice of a lime","Salt to taste","2 cups cooked rice","1 avocado (peeled and sliced)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cook the rice.","name":"Cook the rice.","url":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-39421-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a small bowl, whisk together all of the ingredients for the bang bang sauce. Taste for seasoning then refrigerate until ready to serve.","name":"In a small bowl, whisk together all of the ingredients for the bang bang sauce. Taste for seasoning then refrigerate until ready to serve.","url":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-39421-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat oven to 450\\u00b0 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.","name":"Preheat oven to 450\\u00b0 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.","url":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-39421-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a mixing bowl combine ingredients for the salmon marinade. Add in the cubes of salmon and toss them until they\'re coated. Dump the salmon out onto the baking sheet and spread it into an single layer. Bake for 7-10 minutes or until it\'s opaque.","name":"In a mixing bowl combine ingredients for the salmon marinade. Add in the cubes of salmon and toss them until they\'re coated. Dump the salmon out onto the baking sheet and spread it into an single layer. Bake for 7-10 minutes or until it\'s opaque.","url":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-39421-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"While the salmon bakes, add all of the ingredients for the cucumber salsa to a mixing bowl. Stir together and taste for seasoning.","name":"While the salmon bakes, add all of the ingredients for the cucumber salsa to a mixing bowl. Stir together and taste for seasoning.","url":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-39421-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"To assemble, add a 1\\/2 cup of rice to a bowl. Top with some of the salmon, cucumber salsa, and a few slices of avocado. Drizzle with the bang bang sauce and garnish with sesame seeds and cilantro.","name":"To assemble, add a 1\\/2 cup of rice to a bowl. Top with some of the salmon, cucumber salsa, and a few slices of avocado. Drizzle with the bang bang sauce and garnish with sesame seeds and cilantro.","url":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-39421-step-0-5"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"4","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We loved this recipe!!! I forgot the Greek yogurt and had to use all mayo but it didn\\u2019t seem to hurt the recipe!!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kelley Dykstra"},"datePublished":"2026-06-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Thank you for this delicious and unique recipe! \\nI usually only like simple lemon and salt on salmon, but your marinade is perfect! I\'ll be using it for salmon in the future!\\n The sauce was good, but since we generally don\'t love mayo, we\'ll try doubling the marinade to use as a dressing\\/sauce instead next time. The cuke\\/edamame salad is great combo! Next time, I\'ll try a simple vinaigrette rather than just the lime juice. \\n All in all, my partner and I loved it, and can\'t wait to try it again with a few adjustments to our taste!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Julie"},"datePublished":"2026-03-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"So good!! I love doubling recipe and making it my lunch for the week!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kathryn Yanuszeski"},"datePublished":"2025-08-29"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was incredibly delicious and super easy to make! \\r\\n\\r\\nMy pickiest kid asked to have a leftovers for lunch the next day - and that\\u2019s as good as it gets!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Janet Van Huysse"},"datePublished":"2025-05-01"}],"recipeCategory":["Bowls","Dinners","Fish + Seafood"],"recipeCuisine":["Asian"],"keywords":"bang bang salmon, bang bang salmon bowls, salmon bowls, salmon rice bowls","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"457 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"43 g","proteinContent":"31 g","fatContent":"18 g","saturatedFatContent":"3 g","transFatContent":"0.01 g","cholesterolContent":"64 mg","sodiumContent":"605 mg","fiberContent":"7 g","sugarContent":"11 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/reciperunner.com\\/bang-bang-salmon-bowls\\/"}]}',
