ttps:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/#organization","name":"Gimme Some Oven","url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/09\\/Logo-square.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/09\\/Logo-square.png","width":410,"height":410,"caption":"Gimme Some Oven"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/GimmeSomeOvenBlog\\/","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/gimmesomeoven\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/gimmesomeoven\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/user\\/gimmesomeovenblog"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/f2ec3b8956be0c3431af79ad7e71d6b5","name":"Ali","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/2a46f70c682717622ea29d081ed6cbfed1d8b1d89faa6e768a984b7970610c83?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/2a46f70c682717622ea29d081ed6cbfed1d8b1d89faa6e768a984b7970610c83?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/2a46f70c682717622ea29d081ed6cbfed1d8b1d89faa6e768a984b7970610c83?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","caption":"Ali"},"description":"Hi, I\'m Ali Martin! I created this site in 2009 to celebrate good food and gathering around the table. I live in Kansas City with my husband and two young boys and love creating simple, reliable, delicious recipes that anyone can make!","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/about\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/gimmesomeoven"],"url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/about\\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Roasted Sweet Potato and Chickpea Bowls","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Ali"},"description":"These zesty roasted sweet potato and chickpea bowls are layered with saut\\u00e9ed spinach and brown rice and tossed with my favorite 4-ingredient chipotle tahini dressing. Naturally gluten-free and vegan too.","datePublished":"2024-01-22T10:05:41+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Roasted-Sweet-Potato-and-Chickpea-Bowls-Recipe-7.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Roasted-Sweet-Potato-and-Chickpea-Bowls-Recipe-7-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Roasted-Sweet-Potato-and-Chickpea-Bowls-Recipe-7-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/01\\/Roasted-Sweet-Potato-and-Chickpea-Bowls-Recipe-7-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["3","3 to 4 servings"],"prepTime":"PT20M","cookTime":"PT30M","totalTime":"PT50M","recipeIngredient":["1 1\\/2 pounds sweet potato (diced into 1\\/2-inch cubes)","1 (15-ounce) can chickpeas (rinsed, drained and patted dry)","2 tablespoons olive oil (divided)","2 teaspoons chili powder","1 teaspoon each: ground cumin (garlic powder)","fine sea salt and freshly-ground black pepper","half of a small white onion (thinly sliced)","2 cloves garlic (thinly sliced)","5 ounces baby spinach","4 cups cooked brown rice (farro or quinoa)","1 ripe avocado (thinly sliced)","toppings: chopped fresh cilantro (hemp hearts, pepitas, and\\/or cotija cheese)","1\\/2 cup water","1\\/4 cup tahini","2 tablespoons lime juice","1 to 2 teaspoons maple syrup","1 large chipotle in adobo sauce (plus 1 teaspoon adobo sauce)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Prep the oven and baking sheet. Heat oven to 425\\u00b0F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.","name":"Prep the oven and baking sheet. Heat oven to 425\\u00b0F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-83672-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Roast the sweet potatoes and chickpeas. Add the sweet potatoes and chickpeas to a large mixing bowl. Drizzle evenly with 1 tablespoon of oil and sprinkle evenly with the spices. Toss until combined. Spread the mixture out on the prepared baking sheet in a single layer, then season generously with salt and pepper. Bake for 30 minutes or until the potatoes are tender and the chickpeas are lightly crispy, then transfer the baking sheet to a wire rack.","name":"Roast the sweet potatoes and chickpeas. Add the sweet potatoes and chickpeas to a large mixing bowl. Drizzle evenly with 1 tablespoon of oil and sprinkle evenly with the spices. Toss until combined. Spread the mixture out on the prepared baking sheet in a single layer, then season generously with salt and pepper. Bake for 30 minutes or until the potatoes are tender and the chickpeas are lightly crispy, then transfer the baking sheet to a wire rack.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-83672-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Make the dressing. Add all of the dressing ingredients to a blender and pur\\u00e9e until smooth. Taste and season with salt and pepper or additional lime juice if needed.","name":"Make the dressing. Add all of the dressing ingredients to a blender and pur\\u00e9e until smooth. Taste and season with salt and pepper or additional lime juice if needed.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-83672-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Saut\\u00e9 the spinach. Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to a large saut\\u00e9 pan over medium-high heat. Add the onion and saut\\u00e9 for 4-5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until softened. Add the garlic and saut\\u00e9 for 1 minute, stirring occasionally. Add the spinach and a generous pinch of salt and pepper and cook, tossing frequently, until wilted. Remove from heat.","name":"Saut\\u00e9 the spinach. Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to a large saut\\u00e9 pan over medium-high heat. Add the onion and saut\\u00e9 for 4-5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until softened. Add the garlic and saut\\u00e9 for 1 minute, stirring occasionally. Add the spinach and a generous pinch of salt and pepper and cook, tossing frequently, until wilted. Remove from heat.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-83672-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve. Portion the cooked rice, roasted sweet potatoes and chickpeas, saut\\u00e9ed spinach and a few avocado slices in each serving bowl. Drizzle with the dressing then add your desired toppings. Serve and enjoy!","name":"Serve. Portion the cooked rice, roasted sweet potatoes and chickpeas, saut\\u00e9ed spinach and a few avocado slices in each serving bowl. Drizzle with the dressing then add your desired toppings. Serve and enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-83672-step-0-4"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.93","ratingCount":"14","reviewCount":"13"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"As vegetarians, our family eats a lot of bowls and this one is a favorite! Love the blend of flavors.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Melissa Whitt"},"datePublished":"2024-12-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"yummy yummy yummy !!!!!! i used kale because that\'s what i had and my own sauce i already had ..but everything else i followed your recipe it was so delish and im still full hours later.,,,,soooooo gooooooood","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"pat"},"datePublished":"2024-08-31"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Please provide a calorie count and macros- protein, carbs and fat. This would make my tracking so much easier! Thank you.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Joanne"},"datePublished":"2024-03-18"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Loved this! It reheated well through out the week. Thank you so much for sharing this awesome recipe. It ended up making 5 servings for me the way that I ate it.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Emily"},"datePublished":"2024-02-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This recipe is amazing ! I used black eyed peas- not sure if you can eat those but was a yummy substitute !","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Becca"},"datePublished":"2024-02-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was so yum! And even better, we had some leftover sauce - it turns out that it works perfectly as a quick and easy pasta sauce (make the sauce as the pasta is boiling, stir it through once the pasta has drained)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jo"},"datePublished":"2024-02-16"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Great combination of flavors and that dressing is positively delish! This recipe is a KEEPER!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Caren Bueshi"},"datePublished":"2024-02-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I\\u2019ve made this twice now and we love it. Planning to incorporate this into our regular rotation. Thanks for sharing this recipe!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jenny"},"datePublished":"2024-02-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"The whole family really liked this! I had to change the proportions for the dressing and used much less than 1 chipotle in adobo (I roughly dice up a can and freeze in small blobs so that we can use a tiny amount at a time).","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jenna"},"datePublished":"2024-01-31"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Absolute winner! I adapted it for the air fryer and did not need to dry out the chickpeas after rinsing and draining. Cooked at 390\\u00b0 for 15-17 min. The dressing is phenomenal.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"DS"},"datePublished":"2024-01-31"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"A big hit with my family!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cate"},"datePublished":"2024-01-25"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made this tonight for dinner and it was delicious. Even my usually carnivorous husband and teen son liked it. Thanks!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jennifer"},"datePublished":"2024-01-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I tried this for supper last night and it was delicious!! I am sharing it with all my friends, vegan or just foodies.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Norma"},"datePublished":"2024-01-24"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"keywords":"bean, budget friendly, gluten free, vegan, vegetarian","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.gimmesomeoven.com\\/roasted-sweet-potato-and-chickpea-bowls\\/"}]}',
            'image' => 'https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Roasted-Sweet-Potato-and-Chickpea-Bowls-Recipe-7.jpg',
        'ingredients' => '["1 1\\/2 pounds sweet potato (diced into 1\\/2-inch cubes)","1 (15-ounce) can chickpeas (rinsed, drained and patted dry)","2 tablespoons olive oil (divided)","2 teaspoons chili powder","1 teaspoon each: ground cumin (garlic powder)","fine sea salt and freshly-ground black pepper","half of a small white onion (thinly sliced)","2 cloves garlic (thinly sliced)","5 ounces baby spinach","4 cups cooked brown rice (farro or quinoa)","1 ripe avocado (thinly sliced)","toppings: chopped fresh cilantro (hemp hearts, pepitas, and\\/or cotija cheese)","1\\/2 cup water","1\\/4 cup tahini","2 tablespoons lime juice","1 to 2 teaspoons maple syrup","1 large chipotle in adobo sauce (plus 1 teaspoon adobo sauce)"]',
            'directions' => '["Prep the oven and baking sheet. Heat oven to 425\\u00b0F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.","Roast the sweet potatoes and chickpeas. Add the sweet potatoes and chickpeas to a large mixing bowl. Drizzle evenly with 1 tablespoon of oil and sprinkle evenly with the spices. Toss until combined. Spread the mixture out on the prepared baking sheet in a single layer, then season generously with salt and pepper. Bake for 30 minutes or until the potatoes are tender and the chickpeas are lightly crispy, then transfer the baking sheet to a wire rack.","Make the dressing. Add all of the dressing ingredients to a blender and pur\\u00e9e until smooth. Taste and season with salt and pepper or additional lime juice if needed.","Saut\\u00e9 the spinach. Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to a large saut\\u00e9 pan over medium-high heat. Add the onion and saut\\u00e9 for 4-5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until softened. Add the garlic and saut\\u00e9 for 1 minute, stirring occasionally. Add the spinach and a generous pinch of salt and pepper and cook, tossing frequently, until wilted. Remove from heat.","Serve. Portion the cooked rice, roasted sweet potatoes and chickpeas, saut\\u00e9ed spinach and a few avocado slices in each serving bowl. Drizzle with the dressing then add your desired toppings. Serve and enjoy!"]',
