m.com\\/tachyon\\/Headshot-Main-Bio-Circle.jpg"},"description":"A little thing about me: I \\u2661 FOOD. I used to be a teacher, and now making food and writing about it online is my full-time job. I love talking with people about food, and I\'m so glad you\'re here. Did you make a recipe? Tag @pinchofyum on Instagram so we can find you!","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com","https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/pinchofyum","https:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/pinchofyum","https:\\/\\/pinterest.com\\/pinchofyum","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/pinchofyum"],"url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/author\\/lindsay"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#faq-question-1610477400400","position":1,"url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#faq-question-1610477400400","name":"How can I make this recipe soy-free?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We\'d recommend substituting another favorite protein for the tofu (chicken, salmon, shrimp, mushrooms, etc) and pea pods for the edamame. ","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#faq-question-1610477553665","position":2,"url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#faq-question-1610477553665","name":"Is this recipe meal prep-friendly?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Definitely! We\'d just recommend adding the cucumber, jalape\\u00f1o, spicy mayo, and crunchy fried onions right before eating. ","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#faq-question-1610477691323","position":3,"url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#faq-question-1610477691323","name":"Can I make the crunchy fried onions myself?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Sure! It just takes a little bit more work. Here\'s a <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.delish.com\\/cooking\\/recipe-ideas\\/a28846394\\/fried-onions-recipe\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">recipe<\\/a> we like for making homemade crunchy fried onions. ","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/","@type":"Recipe","name":"Crunchy Roll Bowls","description":"Crunchy Roll Bowls! A block of tofu, nicely browned in teriyaki sauce, served on a bed of sticky rice with edamame, cucumber, avocado, jalape\\u00f1o, and a handful of crushed-up crunchy onions, buried under a thick drizzle of extra teriyaki and spicy mayo.\\u00a0","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lindsay Ostrom","url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/about"},"keywords":"sushi bowl, tofu bowl, crunch roll bowl, crunch roll, vegetarian sushi","image":["https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/tachyon\\/Crunch-Roll-Bowls-2.jpg?fit=150%2C225","https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/tachyon\\/Crunch-Roll-Bowls-2.jpg?fit=130%2C195","https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/tachyon\\/Crunch-Roll-Bowls-2.jpg?fit=120%2C180","https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/tachyon\\/Crunch-Roll-Bowls-2.jpg"],"url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls","recipeIngredient":["1 block extra firm tofu","1 cup rice, uncooked","2 cups frozen shelled edamame","1 cucumber, finely diced","1 avocado, cut into chunks or slices","1 jalape\\u00f1o, thinly sliced","swish of neutral oil","1\\/2 cup teriyaki or savory-sweet Asian-inspired sauce (I used the store-bought Soy Vay brand &#8211; you could also make your own)","1\\/2 cup crunchy fried onions, crushed (like the kind you put on green bean casserole from the store!)","spicy mayo (see notes)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Press the water out of the tofu.","name":"Prep the tofu","url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#instruction-step-1","video":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Crunchy Roll Bowls Step 1","description":"Press the water out of the tofu.","duration":"PT9S","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/player.vimeo.com\\/video\\/493453843?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/493453843","thumbnailUrl":["https:\\/\\/i.vimeocdn.com\\/video\\/1020418292-bff475a658cfeee35481cdd9f7d2000fd65e7ae927f25f42a114be47d6645d16-d_295x166?region=us"],"uploadDate":"2020-12-21T13:31:53+00:00"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cook rice according to package directions.","name":"Make the rice","url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#instruction-step-2","video":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Crunchy Roll Bowls Step 2","description":"Cook rice according to package directions.","duration":"PT10S","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/player.vimeo.com\\/video\\/493454002?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/493454002","thumbnailUrl":["https:\\/\\/i.vimeocdn.com\\/video\\/1020419028-555eaf519af9fa0973d9b739db69f36a0911b971c08bcb888cf2068b362fee68-d_295x166?region=us"],"uploadDate":"2020-12-21T13:32:25+00:00"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cook edamame according to package directions.","name":"Prep the edamame","url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#instruction-step-3","video":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Crunchy Roll Bowls Step 3","description":"Cook edamame according to package directions.","duration":"PT9S","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/player.vimeo.com\\/video\\/493454295?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/493454295","thumbnailUrl":["https:\\/\\/i.vimeocdn.com\\/video\\/1020419131-4bd7f5c1882e98eb0c513c263dbfec593d53ea7916d2ee9eb191c701094f8ba5-d_295x166?region=us"],"uploadDate":"2020-12-21T13:33:15+00:00"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cut the tofu into cubes. Heat a little oil over medium high heat. Add the tofu and fry until golden brown. Add about 1\\/4 to 1\\/3 cup of sauce &#8211; just enough to coat the tofu &#8211; and stir fry again until golden brown.","name":"Cook the tofu","url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#instruction-step-4","video":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Crunchy Roll Bowls Step 4","description":"Cut the tofu into cubes. Heat a little oil over medium high heat. Add the tofu and fry until golden brown. Add about 1\\/4 to 1\\/3 cup of sauce - just enough to coat the tofu - and stir fry again until golden brown.","duration":"PT15S","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/player.vimeo.com\\/video\\/493454568?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/493454568","thumbnailUrl":["https:\\/\\/i.vimeocdn.com\\/video\\/1020420302-10715f1c5af48df2635896dda500b313d012698fb55c1ab35af8c886557707c0-d_295x166?region=us"],"uploadDate":"2020-12-21T13:34:04+00:00"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Assemble bowls with rice, tofu, more teriyaki sauce, edamame, cucumber, jalape\\u00f1o, crunchy onions, and spicy mayo.","name":"Serve","url":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#instruction-step-5","video":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Crunchy Roll Bowls Step 5","description":"Assemble bowls with rice, tofu, more teriyaki sauce, edamame, cucumber, crunchy onions, and spicy mayo.","duration":"PT16S","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/player.vimeo.com\\/video\\/493454885?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/493454885","thumbnailUrl":["https:\\/\\/i.vimeocdn.com\\/video\\/1020420320-59f6cf125ba51c6609aaa0cbc5a485abd162240ad92b911507ecdb1a467ff8c6-d_295x166?region=us"],"uploadDate":"2020-12-21T13:35:07+00:00"}}],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT30M","recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"recipeCategory":"Bowl","cookingMethod":"Oven","recipeCuisine":"Japanese-Inspired","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","reviewCount":"475","ratingValue":"4.9"},"nutrition":{"servingSize":null,"calories":"608 calories","sugarContent":"9.5 g","sodiumContent":"934.7 mg","fatContent":"30.9 g","saturatedFatContent":"4.9 g","transFatContent":"0 g","carbohydrateContent":"60.1 g","fiberContent":"7.7 g","proteinContent":"23.5 g","cholesterolContent":"5.8 mg","@type":"nutritionInformation"},"video":{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Crunchy Roll Bowls","description":"Crunchy Roll Bowls! A block of tofu, nicely browned in teriyaki sauce, served on a bed of sticky rice with edamame, cucumber, avocado, jalape\\u00f1o, and a handful of crushed-up crunchy onions, buried under a thick drizzle of extra teriyaki and spicy mayo. ","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/videos\\/7bAfrrgq.mp4","thumbnailUrl":["https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/thumbs\\/7bAfrrgq-720.jpg"],"uploadDate":"2021-02-05T20:30:47+00:00"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Amy"},"datePublished":"2026-05-13","reviewBody":"When I say we\\u2019ve made this 100 times\\u2026 I mean it. I\\u2019m obsessed! I never get tired of it. I love the textures, flavors, it\\u2019s easy to make! 100\\/10!!!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jill Bloedorn"},"datePublished":"2026-02-25","reviewBody":"We\\u2019ve made these several times with shrimp and the entire family loves them. I also made them for a ladies luncheon and everyone asked for the recipe."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Corrinne Henderson"},"datePublished":"2026-01-14","reviewBody":"We love this one! So good. I\'d love to know what the saturated fat is for this recipe, as only the total fat is listed. Trying to watch my saturated fat since my cholesterol is high. ;)"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sara"},"datePublished":"2025-12-23","reviewBody":"Made this tonight and it was so good!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Meredith Blackburn"},"datePublished":"2025-12-21","reviewBody":"Our favorite super fast weeknight dinner is a combination of two recipes from Pinch of Yum - Ridiculously Good Air Fryer Salmon, and Crunchy Roll Bowls. We do salmon, rice and leafy greens, diced cucumber and edamame, topped with crispy onions and spicy mayo. It takes less than 20 minutes to put together and the whole family loves it!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lex"},"datePublished":"2025-12-09","reviewBody":"My sushi loving family loved this meal! My 9 year old rated it a 10\\/10! I didn\\u2019t love the crispy onions I grabbed at TJ so I browned some panko in a pan with oil and onion powder and it worked great!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Becky"},"datePublished":"2025-10-23","reviewBody":"love this. it\'s on rotation at our house. easy to please everyone as they assemble their own bowls &amp; toppings."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Katie"},"datePublished":"2025-09-16","reviewBody":"This was fantastic and so easy! I marinated shrimp in the teriyaki while the tofu cooked for my husband. A hit for the entire family, will definitely make again."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Amy"},"datePublished":"2025-08-19","reviewBody":"Obsessed. Cannot stop making it. Thank you!!!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jessie Brown"},"datePublished":"2025-08-07","reviewBody":"This was a household hit! Super easy to make, extra tasty and the kids asked for seconds (with a couple modifications). This will be going on my regular rotation!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Steph"},"datePublished":"2025-07-29","reviewBody":"Made this last night and I\\u2019m wishing we had leftovers for breakfast! What an excellent recipe! I used ground turkey rather than tofu, a bag of frozen\\/microwavable rice, and topped with cilantro. From fridge to fork, it was just 21 minutes! Super easy and sooo delicious. Thank you!!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Julie"},"datePublished":"2025-02-10","reviewBody":"These were fantastic! All of my toddlers, and husband loved it as their first time having tofu! So easy to put together too!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sarah"},"datePublished":"2025-02-08","reviewBody":"I know this recipe has been posted for a while at this point, but I just had to leave a comment to say this is a staple in our house! So delicious and easy."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Emily"},"datePublished":"2025-02-07","reviewBody":"This is the best thing I\\u2019ve ever made. From your site, and maybe ever. It\\u2019s ridiculously good and so easy. Love all the flavors together!!! Like deconstructed sushi"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Louisa"},"datePublished":"2025-01-20","reviewBody":"Love these tofu bowls!! We make them monthly, so easy and delicious!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Erin"},"datePublished":"2024-05-06","reviewBody":"Incredible flavor, so easy to make and am mad at myself that I didn\\u2019t find this recipe sooner. Can\\u2019t wait to make again! You should do a feature of older but amazing recipes!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kristen"},"datePublished":"2024-04-20","reviewBody":"Another keeper, thank you! Our local place uses mango so I added some to your recipe. I thought it was a great addition \\ud83d\\ude0a"}],"datePublished":"2022-09-09","@id":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/pinchofyum.com\\/crunchy-roll-bowls"}]}',
