{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2026\\/04\\/half-baked-harvest-yoast-black.png","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2026\\/04\\/half-baked-harvest-yoast-black.png","width":1000,"height":1000,"caption":"Half Baked Harvest"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/hbharvest","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/hbharvest","http:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/halfbakedharvest","https:\\/\\/pinterest.com\\/hbharvest\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/user\\/tieghangerard\\/videos"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/9b2904ad2a2c76cbcd62517659d460f7","name":"Tieghan Gerard","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/7036495bc5ea357403212cff0b64834c57cfbd3ed04ba77bfdf88b1b027f1d84?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/7036495bc5ea357403212cff0b64834c57cfbd3ed04ba77bfdf88b1b027f1d84?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/7036495bc5ea357403212cff0b64834c57cfbd3ed04ba77bfdf88b1b027f1d84?s=96&d=mm&r=pg","caption":"Tieghan Gerard"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/meet-tieghan\\/"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Sheet Pan Chicken Tinga Bowls","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/9b2904ad2a2c76cbcd62517659d460f7"},"description":"This is a simple dinner that comes together in under 45 minutes and is perfect for Cinco de Mayo!","datePublished":"2024-04-23T01:00:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Sheet-Pan-Chicken-Tinga-Bowls-1-scaled.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Sheet-Pan-Chicken-Tinga-Bowls-1-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Sheet-Pan-Chicken-Tinga-Bowls-1-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Sheet-Pan-Chicken-Tinga-Bowls-1-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Sheet Pan Chicken Tinga Bowls_ReelTikTok2024.mp4","description":"A new go-to weeknight dinner, Sheet Pan Chicken Tinga Bowls. Chipotle seasoned chicken roasted on a sheet pan with peppers and onions and served bowl style with rice, chunky avocado salsa (yummy), cheese, and chips on the side for scooping everything up!","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/thumbs\\/SYRscYbx-720.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/videos\\/SYRscYbx.mp4","uploadDate":"2025-05-07T16:43:49+00:00","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["6"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT20M","totalTime":"PT35M","recipeIngredient":["1 1\\/2 pounds boneless chicken breasts or thighs","3\\/4 cup red enchilada sauce","2-3 chipotle peppers in adobo, chopped","1 teaspoon dried oregano","1 teaspoon ground cumin","1 teaspoon salt","2 bell peppers, sliced","1 yellow onion, sliced","3-4 cups cooked rice","1 cup shredded cheddar\\/cotija cheese","yogurt\\/sour cream + limes, for serving","2-3 avocados, chopped","1 jalape\\u00f1o, seeded if desired, and chopped","1\\/2 cup fresh cilantro, chopped","1\\/4 cup lime juice","flaky salt"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"1. Preheat the oven to 425\\u00b0 F.\\u00a02. On a baking sheet, toss the chicken with 2 tablespoons olive oil, enchilada sauce, chipotle peppers, oregano, cumin, and salt.\\u00a03. Add the bell peppers, onion, and 1 tablespoon olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and toss. Arrange everything evenly on the pan. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the chicken is cooked and the peppers begin to char.\\u00a04. Shred the chicken and toss with the sauce on the pan.5. Meanwhile, make the salsa. Toss all ingredients in a bowl and season with salt.6. Serve the chicken and peppers over bowls of rice. Top the chicken with cheese and avocado. Add a dollop of yogurt + zest, and squeeze the limes over each bowl. Enjoy with warmed tortillas or chips. YUM!","name":"1. Preheat the oven to 425\\u00b0 F.\\u00a02. On a baking sheet, toss the chicken with 2 tablespoons olive oil, enchilada sauce, chipotle peppers, oregano, cumin, and salt.\\u00a03. Add the bell peppers, onion, and 1 tablespoon olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and toss. Arrange everything evenly on the pan. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the chicken is cooked and the peppers begin to char.\\u00a04. Shred the chicken and toss with the sauce on the pan.5. Meanwhile, make the salsa. Toss all ingredients in a bowl and season with salt.6. Serve the chicken and peppers over bowls of rice. Top the chicken with cheese and avocado. Add a dollop of yogurt + zest, and squeeze the limes over each bowl. Enjoy with warmed tortillas or chips. YUM!","url":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/chicken-tinga-bowls\\/#wprm-recipe-163239-step-0-0"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"18","reviewCount":"9"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Recipe was delicious","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Billy Mayer"},"datePublished":"2026-04-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I first had this at a girls\\u2019 getaway weekend and had to have the recipe. I just made it at home and my husband also said it was a keeper. I did not have any raw chicken on hand but I did have a rotisserie chicken. I shredded the chicken, added the sauce, and then put it in a covered casserole dish and put it in the oven along with the vegetables while they roasted. Turned out perfectly!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sandy H"},"datePublished":"2025-06-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was delicious. We did things slightly differently. We doubled the sauce, marinated the chicken in half of that, and grilled it. Then we shredded the chicken and tossed it with the remaining warmed sauce. I think next time we would do as you recommended and broil the chicken for a minute for a little crispiness. We did the veggies in the oven as directed. It was a great meal for an informal family gathering.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Andrea"},"datePublished":"2025-06-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This meal was simple and very tasty! I read another reviewer\'s comment and they roasted the veggies seperately. I did the same, because I like my veggies with extra char, not so much for my chicken. The veggies roasted a litte longer while I shredded the chicken. My son said it was like Chipotle and asked if I could make a beef version. This would be a nice meal for company, tastes like you spent a lot of time in the kitchen, but was really easy. Thanks for sharing Tieghan! I have delighted my family with several of your recipes. Your meals are awesome!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Nicole Mattson"},"datePublished":"2025-03-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made this last night. Excellent recipe. Def a keeper.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Diego"},"datePublished":"2024-10-17"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Tried this last night, it was an absolute HIT! Great flavor, good balance of spicy (my fam likes spicy foods) and filling meal. It was so simple and even more simple clean up. My husband requested to add it to our \\u201cgo to\\u201d list. My kids (3yr, 1yr) both devoured what I served them. I meal prep on Sundays so I had premade rice\\/quinoa batch which made it even easier to just throw together. Great job with this one Tieghan!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Daniela"},"datePublished":"2024-08-23"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was great\\u2026a little spicy (we\\u2019ll need antacids later, lol). So much easier than the recipe I was using which dirtied a food processor, blender and instant pot. Serving it in a bowl with rice\\u2026genius! Thank you for an easy way to make meals.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Carol"},"datePublished":"2024-07-16"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Love this! The Chipotles are too hot for me so I just use about 2 T of the adobo sauce and love the smokiness that it brings. I usually have to bake the peppers\\/onions on a separate pan because they get too juicy and don\'t really char when cooked with the chicken. I also use chicken thighs so that probably contributes to the moisture. \\r\\nBut I\'ve made this a few times now and it\'s definitely a keeper! I am a very very slow cook and I can still get this one done in an hour without too much effort.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Emily"},"datePublished":"2024-05-31"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was amazing!! Both my husband and I loved it and it was super easy without a lot of dishes, which is always a plus.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Meagan"},"datePublished":"2024-05-06"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["American","Mexican"],"keywords":"bowl food, Cinco de Mayo, under an hour","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"453 kcal","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/chicken-tinga-bowls\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/chicken-tinga-bowls\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.halfbakedharvest.com\\/chicken-tinga-bowls\\/"}]}',
            'image' => 'https://www.halfbakedharvest.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Sheet-Pan-Chicken-Tinga-Bowls-1-scaled.jpg',
            'ingredients' => '["1 1\\/2 pounds boneless chicken breasts or thighs","3\\/4 cup red enchilada sauce","2-3 chipotle peppers in adobo, chopped","1 teaspoon dried oregano","1 teaspoon ground cumin","1 teaspoon salt","2 bell peppers, sliced","1 yellow onion, sliced","3-4 cups cooked rice","1 cup shredded cheddar\\/cotija cheese","yogurt\\/sour cream + limes, for serving","2-3 avocados, chopped","1 jalape\\u00f1o, seeded if desired, and chopped","1\\/2 cup fresh cilantro, chopped","1\\/4 cup lime juice","flaky salt"]',
            'directions' => '["1. Preheat the oven to 425\\u00b0 F.\\u00a02. On a baking sheet, toss the chicken with 2 tablespoons olive oil, enchilada sauce, chipotle peppers, oregano, cumin, and salt.\\u00a03. Add the bell peppers, onion, and 1 tablespoon olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and toss. Arrange everything evenly on the pan. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the chicken is cooked and the peppers begin to char.\\u00a04. Shred the chicken and toss with the sauce on the pan.5. Meanwhile, make the salsa. Toss all ingredients in a bowl and season with salt.6. Serve the chicken and peppers over bowls of rice. Top the chicken with cheese and avocado. Add a dollop of yogurt + zest, and squeeze the limes over each bowl. Enjoy with warmed tortillas or chips. YUM!"]',
