arro-bowl\\/#breadcrumb"},"mainEntity":[{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997288830"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997342813"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997358054"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997379037"}],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/Farro-Bowl-003.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/Farro-Bowl-003.jpg","width":1200,"height":1501,"caption":"Farro Bowl"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/category\\/recipes\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Fast Dinner Ideas","item":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/category\\/recipes\\/fast-dinner-ideas\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":4,"name":"Farro Bowl"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/","name":"A Couple Cooks","description":"Recipes that make your life better!","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/#organization","name":"A Couple Cooks","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/acouplecooks-logo.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/acouplecooks-logo.jpg","width":696,"height":696,"caption":"A Couple Cooks"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/aCoupleCooks","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/acouplecooks\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/acouplecooks\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/aCoupleCooksTV","https:\\/\\/www.tiktok.com\\/@sonjaeverynight"],"publishingPrinciples":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/editorial-policy\\/","actionableFeedbackPolicy":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/contact-us\\/"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/d084a97547d6ac8f3d3602a9e2dd6c35","name":"Sonja Overhiser","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-includes\\/images\\/blank.gif","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-includes\\/images\\/blank.gif","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-includes\\/images\\/blank.gif","caption":"Sonja Overhiser"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/about\\/","https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/aCoupleCooks"]},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997288830","position":1,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997288830","name":"What is farro, and why should I use it in this bowl?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Farro is an ancient grain with a chewy texture and nutty flavor. It\'s packed with fiber and protein, making it a hearty and satisfying base for this bowl. It also holds up well when mixed with other ingredients, so your bowl won\'t get soggy.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997342813","position":2,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997342813","name":"Can I use a different grain if I don\'t have farro?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Absolutely! If you can\'t find farro or want to try something different, you can substitute it with quinoa, brown rice, barley, or even couscous. Just adjust the cooking time accordingly.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997358054","position":3,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997358054","name":"Can I make this bowl ahead of time?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, you can! The farro and chickpeas can be cooked in advance and stored separately in the refrigerator. The dressing can also be prepared ahead of time. Assemble the bowls just before serving to keep the vegetables fresh and crunchy.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997379037","position":4,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#faq-question-1718997379037","name":"How can I customize this bowl to my liking?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Feel free to get creative! You can add other vegetables like roasted red peppers, <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/grilled-zucchini\\/\\">grilled zucchini<\\/a>, or chopped kale. You can also swap the feta for goat cheese or omit it for a vegan option. Experiment with different herbs and spices to change up the flavor profile.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@context":"https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/","@type":"Recipe","name":"Farro Bowl","description":"This hearty farro bowl recipe is packed with Mediterranean flavors! Juicy tomatoes, crisp cucumbers, briny olives, and a creamy dressing make a satisfying grain bowl that\'s the perfect meal for summer or any season.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sonja Overhiser","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/sonja-overhiser\\/"},"keywords":"Farro bowl, farro grain bowl, farro bowl recipe","image":["https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/Farro-Bowl-004-225x225.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/Farro-Bowl-004-260x195.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/Farro-Bowl-004-320x180.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/06\\/Farro-Bowl-004.jpg"],"url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/","recipeIngredient":["1 cup uncooked farro, pearled or semi-pearled (not whole)","\\u00be teaspoon kosher salt, divided","2 tablespoons chopped fresh herbs (parsley, dill or cilantro)","1 garlic clove, minced","1 tablespoon butter or olive oil","15-ounce can chickpeas","1 garlic clove, minced","1 tablespoon olive oil","1\\/2 teaspoon each cumin and coriander","1\\/4 teaspoon each smoked paprika and onion powder","1\\/2 teaspoon kosher salt","2 cups cherry tomatoes, sliced in half","1 English cucumber, chopped","1 handful olives, sliced in half","1 handful baby greens (like arugula)","Feta cheese, to serve (optional)","1\\/2 cup high quality hummus (avoid Sabra)","1 tablespoon olive oil","2 tablespoons lemon juice (more water if necessary)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Rinse the farro under cold water in a fine mesh strainer. In a large saucepan, place the farro, 3 cups water and \\u00bd teaspoon of the kosher salt and bring it to a boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer, cover, and cook until the grains are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes for pearled farro and 25 to 30 minutes for semi-pearled farro. Taste test a grain to see if it is tender (if the package is unmarked, just cook until tender). Drain any excess water. Add the additional \\u00bc teaspoon salt and olive oil or butter. Stir in the minced garlic and herbs. Taste and add additional salt if desired.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#instruction-step-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Drain and rinse the chickpeas. Mince the garlic. In a small bowl, mix the cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, onion powder, and salt. In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the garlic and saut\\u00e9 for 1 minute until fragrant but before it browns. Add the chickpeas, spices, salt, and several grinds of black pepper. Cook 2 minutes until warmed through.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#instruction-step-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Make the hummus dressing by mixing together the ingredients in a medium bowl. Taste and if\\u00a0desired, you can add a pinch or two of salt or sugar.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#instruction-step-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the green in a shallow bowl (if using), then the farro, tomatoes, cucumbers, chickpeas, and olives. Top with feta cheese, if using, and drizzle with hummus dressing.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#instruction-step-4"}],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT30M","recipeYield":"4","recipeCategory":"Main Dish","cookingMethod":"Stovetop","recipeCuisine":"Mediterranean","suitableForDiet":"VegetarianDiet","aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","reviewCount":"5","ratingValue":"4.8"},"nutrition":{"servingSize":null,"calories":"833 calories","sugarContent":"36.2 g","sodiumContent":"1065.8 mg","fatContent":"64.3 g","saturatedFatContent":"41.3 g","transFatContent":"0 g","carbohydrateContent":"57.9 g","fiberContent":"10.2 g","proteinContent":"16.1 g","cholesterolContent":"33.4 mg","@type":"nutritionInformation"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Tammy D"},"datePublished":"2024-06-29","reviewBody":"I made this tonight for dinner! It was delicious and filling. Next time, I think I will add some pickled onions for a bit more zing and, if I get organized enough, bake a loaf of bread to go with it \\ud83d\\ude0a\\r\\nAn excellent, healthy, simple meal!"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Carol Lynn"},"datePublished":"2024-07-02","reviewBody":"We loved this recipe\\u2014so many great flavors and textures. I did not have hummus and made the tahini sauce with white vinegar instead. I also added pickled onions as was suggested. Will make again, a great summer meal."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Frances"},"datePublished":"2025-07-25","reviewBody":"Love this, something I could eat everyday. Sometimes I just make the chickpeas to be able to toss them into some salad or pasta etc--"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Nancy"},"datePublished":"2025-10-28","reviewBody":"Absolutely delicious!! This is going to be my weekly go to. Thank you."},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jamie"},"datePublished":"2026-01-06","reviewBody":"I LOVE this. I discovered farro a couple of years ago and I love the taste and texture of it so much! I could eat this several times a week!!"}],"datePublished":"2025-08-16","@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.acouplecooks.com\\/farro-bowl\\/"}]}',
            'image' => 'https://www.acouplecooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Farro-Bowl-003.jpg',
        'ingredients' => '["1 cup uncooked farro, pearled or semi-pearled (not whole)","\\u00be teaspoon kosher salt, divided","2 tablespoons chopped fresh herbs (parsley, dill or cilantro)","1 garlic clove, minced","1 tablespoon butter or olive oil","15-ounce can chickpeas","1 garlic clove, minced","1 tablespoon olive oil","1\\/2 teaspoon each cumin and coriander","1\\/4 teaspoon each smoked paprika and onion powder","1\\/2 teaspoon kosher salt","2 cups cherry tomatoes, sliced in half","1 English cucumber, chopped","1 handful olives, sliced in half","1 handful baby greens (like arugula)","Feta cheese, to serve (optional)","1\\/2 cup high quality hummus (avoid Sabra)","1 tablespoon olive oil","2 tablespoons lemon juice (more water if necessary)"]',
        'directions' => '["Rinse the farro under cold water in a fine mesh strainer. In a large saucepan, place the farro, 3 cups water and \\u00bd teaspoon of the kosher salt and bring it to a boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer, cover, and cook until the grains are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes for pearled farro and 25 to 30 minutes for semi-pearled farro. Taste test a grain to see if it is tender (if the package is unmarked, just cook until tender). Drain any excess water. Add the additional \\u00bc teaspoon salt and olive oil or butter. Stir in the minced garlic and herbs. Taste and add additional salt if desired.","Drain and rinse the chickpeas. Mince the garlic. In a small bowl, mix the cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, onion powder, and salt. In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the garlic and saut\\u00e9 for 1 minute until fragrant but before it browns. Add the chickpeas, spices, salt, and several grinds of black pepper. Cook 2 minutes until warmed through.","Make the hummus dressing by mixing together the ingredients in a medium bowl. Taste and if\\u00a0desired, you can add a pinch or two of salt or sugar.","Place the green in a shallow bowl (if using), then the farro, tomatoes, cucumbers, chickpeas, and olives. Top with feta cheese, if using, and drizzle with hummus dressing."]',
