,"name":"Gaby Dalkin"},"description":"Your new fav grain bowl of summer with the most incredible Green Goddess Feta Dressing!","datePublished":"2021-06-07T07:00:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/06\\/WGC-Green-Goddess-Dressing-copy-2.jpg","https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/06\\/WGC-Green-Goddess-Dressing-copy-2-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/06\\/WGC-Green-Goddess-Dressing-copy-2-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/06\\/WGC-Green-Goddess-Dressing-copy-2-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["6","6 people"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT30M","totalTime":"PT45M","recipeIngredient":["8 ounces feta cheese, in brine (drained)","1 cup Greek Yogurt","4 tablespoons chopped chives","4 tablespoons chopped packed basil","4 tablespoons chopped cilantro","1\\/4 cup water","1\\/2 lemon, juiced","1\\/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes","Kosher salt and freshly cracked black pepper to taste","1 cup farro (quinoa or rice also works)","3 Persian cucumbers, halved and sliced","2\\/3 cup fresh corn","2 peaches, cubed (or any other stone fruit)","1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved","fresh basil to garnish","Kosher salt and freshly cracked black pepper to taste"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the ingredients for the dressing into a blender and blend until smooth. Add a few tablespoons of water if needed to smooth out until consistency is similar to ranch.","name":"Place the ingredients for the dressing into a blender and blend until smooth. Add a few tablespoons of water if needed to smooth out until consistency is similar to ranch.","url":"https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/summer-grain-bowl-with-green-goddess-feta-dressing\\/#wprm-recipe-45910-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cook the farro according to the package directions. Let cool slightly.","name":"Cook the farro according to the package directions. Let cool slightly.","url":"https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/summer-grain-bowl-with-green-goddess-feta-dressing\\/#wprm-recipe-45910-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Toss the farro with \\u00bd cup of the dressing, more if needed. And then add the Persian cucumbers, corn, cubed peaches, cherry tomatoes and season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine","name":"Toss the farro with \\u00bd cup of the dressing, more if needed. And then add the Persian cucumbers, corn, cubed peaches, cherry tomatoes and season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine","url":"https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/summer-grain-bowl-with-green-goddess-feta-dressing\\/#wprm-recipe-45910-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve as a side dish or a main dish with fresh basil on top for garnish.","name":"Serve as a side dish or a main dish with fresh basil on top for garnish.","url":"https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/summer-grain-bowl-with-green-goddess-feta-dressing\\/#wprm-recipe-45910-step-0-3"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"5","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"When I try a new Gaby recipe, I know it\\u2019s going to be good - but I was surprised by how much this recipe blew me away! The peaches are the perfect fresh &amp; sweet complement to the farro &amp; feta dressing. It\\u2019s the perfect summertime lunch! 10\\/10","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rachel"},"datePublished":"2021-07-29"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is so fresh and flavorful! Will definitely make it again\\u2026 especially the dressing!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Abbie"},"datePublished":"2021-07-13"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Wow!!! This green goddess feta is perfect to have on hand to jazz up any summer meal!!! I\\u2019ve made it twice already!!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Mallory"},"datePublished":"2021-07-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Incredible combination of flavors. Dressing is amazing with stone fruit and the Persian cucumber adds a nice fresh bite of crunchiness. I used brown rice and absolutely loved this recipe.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Alison"},"datePublished":"2021-06-09"}],"recipeCategory":["Side Dish","Salad"],"recipeCuisine":["Mediterranean"],"keywords":"easy Green Goddess Dressing, how to make a green goddess dressing","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"285 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"40 g","proteinContent":"14 g","fatContent":"9 g","saturatedFatContent":"5 g","transFatContent":"0.003 g","cholesterolContent":"35 mg","sodiumContent":"462 mg","fiberContent":"7 g","sugarContent":"8 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"3 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/summer-grain-bowl-with-green-goddess-feta-dressing\\/#recipe","mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/summer-grain-bowl-with-green-goddess-feta-dressing\\/#webpage","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/whatsgabycooking.com\\/summer-grain-bowl-with-green-goddess-feta-dressing\\/#richSnippet"}}]}',
