"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/03\\/Sweetgreen-Harvest-Bowl-9-1.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/03\\/Sweetgreen-Harvest-Bowl-9-1.jpg","width":1200,"height":1800,"caption":"Sweetgreen harvest bowl with rice, roasted sweet potatoes, diced apples, pecans, goat cheese, roasted brussel sprouts, diced chicken, and small ramekin of creamy balsamic dressing over greens. Another harvest bowl is off to the side and a small bowl of pecans to the other side."},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/recipe-index\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Meal Prep","item":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/product-category\\/meal-prep\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":4,"name":"Sweetgreen Harvest Bowl Recipe"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/","name":"Eat the Gains","description":"Easy &amp; Healthy Macro Friendly Recipes","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/#organization","name":"Eat the Gains","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/02\\/primary-logo.svg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/02\\/primary-logo.svg","width":278,"height":171,"caption":"Eat the Gains"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/x.com\\/eatthegains","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/eatthegains\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/eatthegains\\/"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/a8c65475acae93497d3103c33fab7c84","name":"Kelly Nardo","description":"Hi, I\'m Kelly, a nutrition coach and lover of food and fitness. I like to create healthy recipes that help fuel my workouts and enrich my health.","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/about"]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Sweetgreen Harvest Bowl","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/a8c65475acae93497d3103c33fab7c84"},"description":"Copycat Sweetgreen harvest bowl with juicy marinated chicken, roasted sweet potato and brussel sprouts, apples, pecans, goat cheese, and a creamy balsamic dressing. It&#39;s makes a delicious and flavor-packed grain bowl for a healthy lunch or dinner and is perfect for meal prep. Gluten-free and easily made dairy-free.","datePublished":"2024-09-01T12:49:54+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/03\\/Sweetgreen-Harvest-Bowl-9-1.jpg","https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/03\\/Sweetgreen-Harvest-Bowl-9-1-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/03\\/Sweetgreen-Harvest-Bowl-9-1-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/03\\/Sweetgreen-Harvest-Bowl-9-1-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT45M","totalTime":"PT60M","recipeIngredient":["1 pound chicken thighs","1\\/3 cup coconut aminos","1 teaspoon garlic powder","1 teaspoon ground ginger","1\\/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes","1\\/2 teaspoon salt","1\\/2 teaspoon pepper","2\\/3 cups sprouted brown rice ((uncooked))","2 small sweet potatoes, diced ((10 ounces))","1 pound brussel sprouts, trimmed and cut in half","1 large apple ((175 grams))","1\\/2 cup pecans","1\\/2 cup goat cheese ((2 ounces))","8 packed cups baby kale ((8 ounces))","1 1\\/2 tablespoons olive oil","salt and pepper, to taste","1\\/4 cup balsamic vinegar","2 tablespoons almond butter","1-2 tablespoons water ((or more for thinning it out))","salt, to taste"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Marinate your chicken.\\u00a0Add the chicken, coconut aminos, garlic, ginger, red pepper flakes, and salt and pepper to a large glass baking dish or plastic bag and mix well to combine, making sure the spices evenly coat the chicken. Let marinate for 30 minutes or up to 8 hours. When done marinating, roast in the oven on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper at 400 degrees Fahrenheit for 35-45 minutes until cooked through.","name":"Marinate your chicken.\\u00a0Add the chicken, coconut aminos, garlic, ginger, red pepper flakes, and salt and pepper to a large glass baking dish or plastic bag and mix well to combine, making sure the spices evenly coat the chicken. Let marinate for 30 minutes or up to 8 hours. When done marinating, roast in the oven on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper at 400 degrees Fahrenheit for 35-45 minutes until cooked through.","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#wprm-recipe-15493-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Roast\\u00a0your veggies.\\u00a0Add diced sweet potatoes and brussel sprouts to a large baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Toss with oil and salt and pepper. Roast in the oven, along with your chicken, for 35-45 minutes under tender.","name":"Roast\\u00a0your veggies.\\u00a0Add diced sweet potatoes and brussel sprouts to a large baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Toss with oil and salt and pepper. Roast in the oven, along with your chicken, for 35-45 minutes under tender.","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#wprm-recipe-15493-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Make your rice.\\u00a0Add to a pot with water or broth (broth adds a little more flavor) and follow instructions according to the package.","name":"Make your rice.\\u00a0Add to a pot with water or broth (broth adds a little more flavor) and follow instructions according to the package.","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#wprm-recipe-15493-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"While the rice and veggies cook, make the dressing. Add the balsamic vinegar, almond butter, salt, and 1 tablespoon of water to a small jar. I find using an immersion blender works best to make sure it&#39;s thoroughly combined, but you can just mix it with a fork. Add more water if you want a thinner consistency.","name":"While the rice and veggies cook, make the dressing. Add the balsamic vinegar, almond butter, salt, and 1 tablespoon of water to a small jar. I find using an immersion blender works best to make sure it&#39;s thoroughly combined, but you can just mix it with a fork. Add more water if you want a thinner consistency.","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#wprm-recipe-15493-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Prep the remaining ingredients.\\u00a0When the rice and veggies are almost done, dice the apple, crumble the goat cheese, and roughly chop the pecans.","name":"Prep the remaining ingredients.\\u00a0When the rice and veggies are almost done, dice the apple, crumble the goat cheese, and roughly chop the pecans.","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#wprm-recipe-15493-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Assemble your bowls.\\u00a0Evenly divide the greens, rice, chicken, roasted veggies, apple, goat cheese, and nuts. Serve with the creamy balsamic dressing.","name":"Assemble your bowls.\\u00a0Evenly divide the greens, rice, chicken, roasted veggies, apple, goat cheese, and nuts. Serve with the creamy balsamic dressing.","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#wprm-recipe-15493-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Enjoy!","name":"Enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#wprm-recipe-15493-step-0-6"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.87","ratingCount":"59","reviewCount":"8"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"3"},"reviewBody":"Oh man the almond butter dressing was not what I wanted or expected when I sent this to my husband. I should have read the recipe closer but maybe don\\u2019t say copy cat sweet greens? The balsamic makes this for me! Other than that I think everything roasted well and chicken was fine.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sheila Urban"},"datePublished":"2024-10-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Absolutely delicious! Enjoyed this for my meal prep for the week and did not get tired of it!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kimberleigh McDermott"},"datePublished":"2024-09-13"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I use the chicken marinade all the time - so good!! Thanks!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Maureen"},"datePublished":"2024-08-16"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I love this recipe! I\\u2019ve been making it every week and if I don\\u2019t make it one week I literally crave. So delicious and satisfying.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rachel"},"datePublished":"2023-04-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This meal is so freaking good. So many different flavors and textures that blend so well together. And it\'s been perfect for leftovers.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sierra"},"datePublished":"2023-01-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I love this one and so does my partner! He complimented me several times about it : ) My only changes I\'ll make next time is 1. not burning the brussels (lol) and 2. finding a different method for creamy balsamic. I\'m not a huge fan of peanutbutters and that flavor was too strong for me but thats totally a personal problem. The chicken thighs marinade was SO yummy and easy. They were JUICY! Thanks always!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Audrey L"},"datePublished":"2022-12-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Loved this one and so does partner. I probaly would make the dressing differently next time I do it - maybe just balmanic? - because I\'m not a fan of peanut butter and the mix was a little over powering for me but thats a personal problem. This chicken was so juicy and tender and the marinade was lovely. big thumbs up.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Audrey L"},"datePublished":"2022-12-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Loved this recipe and SUPER easy to modify. I altered it slightly to make it with what I had on hand (farro &amp; spinach were the base and my protein was left-over pulled pork). It was delish!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jessica Fisher"},"datePublished":"2022-12-17"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"keywords":"copycat sweetgreen harvest bowl, harvest bowl sweetgreen, sweetgreen harvest bowl, sweetgreen harvest bowl recipe, sweetgreen recipes","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 bowl","calories":"640 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"63.7 g","proteinContent":"36.5 g","fatContent":"29.2 g","saturatedFatContent":"5.4 g","fiberContent":"13.3 g","sugarContent":"15.5 g","sodiumContent":"349 mg","cholesterolContent":"113 mg","unsaturatedFatContent":"20.6 g"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/eatthegains.com\\/sweetgreen-harvest-bowl\\/"}]}',
            'image' => 'https://eatthegains.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Sweetgreen-Harvest-Bowl-9-1.jpg',
        'ingredients' => '["1 pound chicken thighs","1\\/3 cup coconut aminos","1 teaspoon garlic powder","1 teaspoon ground ginger","1\\/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes","1\\/2 teaspoon salt","1\\/2 teaspoon pepper","2\\/3 cups sprouted brown rice ((uncooked))","2 small sweet potatoes, diced ((10 ounces))","1 pound brussel sprouts, trimmed and cut in half","1 large apple ((175 grams))","1\\/2 cup pecans","1\\/2 cup goat cheese ((2 ounces))","8 packed cups baby kale ((8 ounces))","1 1\\/2 tablespoons olive oil","salt and pepper, to taste","1\\/4 cup balsamic vinegar","2 tablespoons almond butter","1-2 tablespoons water ((or more for thinning it out))","salt, to taste"]',
        'directions' => '["Marinate your chicken.\\u00a0Add the chicken, coconut aminos, garlic, ginger, red pepper flakes, and salt and pepper to a large glass baking dish or plastic bag and mix well to combine, making sure the spices evenly coat the chicken. Let marinate for 30 minutes or up to 8 hours. When done marinating, roast in the oven on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper at 400 degrees Fahrenheit for 35-45 minutes until cooked through.","Roast\\u00a0your veggies.\\u00a0Add diced sweet potatoes and brussel sprouts to a large baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Toss with oil and salt and pepper. Roast in the oven, along with your chicken, for 35-45 minutes under tender.","Make your rice.\\u00a0Add to a pot with water or broth (broth adds a little more flavor) and follow instructions according to the package.","While the rice and veggies cook, make the dressing. Add the balsamic vinegar, almond butter, salt, and 1 tablespoon of water to a small jar. I find using an immersion blender works best to make sure it&#39;s thoroughly combined, but you can just mix it with a fork. Add more water if you want a thinner consistency.","Prep the remaining ingredients.\\u00a0When the rice and veggies are almost done, dice the apple, crumble the goat cheese, and roughly chop the pecans.","Assemble your bowls.\\u00a0Evenly divide the greens, rice, chicken, roasted veggies, apple, goat cheese, and nuts. Serve with the creamy balsamic dressing.","Enjoy!"]',
