        64 => 
        array (
            'id' => 65,
            'name' => 'Warm Garlicky Lemon Zoodles Bowl with Roasted Veggies + Tahini Sauce',
            'url' => 'https://www.healthygffamily.com/recipe/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2/',
            'site_domain' => 'https//www.healthygffamily.com',
            'site_name' => 'Healthy Gluten-free Family',
            'user_id' => 1,
            'description' => 'This vibrant and savory bowl of veggies is warm, cozy and packed with flavor. Warm garlicky and lemony zucchini noodles and warm roasted vegetables with the yummiest tahini sauce. Feel free to add protein of choice: chicken, tofu, chickpeas. Great for meal prep as it reheats well. One tip, saute zoodles when ready to serve.',
        'content' => '{"@context":"http:\\/\\/schema.org\\/","@type":"Recipe","name":"Warm Garlicky Lemon Zoodles Bowl with Roasted Veggies + Tahini Sauce","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Healthy Gluten-free Family"},"description":"This vibrant and savory bowl of veggies is warm, cozy and packed with flavor. Warm garlicky and lemony zucchini noodles and warm roasted vegetables with the yummiest tahini sauce. Feel free to add protein of choice: chicken, tofu, chickpeas. Great for meal prep as it reheats well. One tip, saute zoodles when ready to serve.","datePublished":"2019-09-08T20:00:06+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/09\\/CFAC0B42-7015-4238-807D-A8B9FC1722A4-300x300-1.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/09\\/CFAC0B42-7015-4238-807D-A8B9FC1722A4-300x300-1-300x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"prepTime":"PT20M","cookTime":"PT30M","totalTime":"PT50M","recipeIngredient":["1 package pre-cubed butternut squash or 1 butternut squash (peeled and cubed)","2 tablespoons olive oil","1 teaspoon ground cumin","1 teaspoon hot smoked Spanish paprika","\\u00bd teaspoon sea salt","Neutral oil of your choice like avocado oil","1 teaspoon turmeric (sometimes I add more depending on how much cauliflower I have)","Kosher Salt","Pepper","4 zucchini","Olive oil (approximately \\u00bd teaspoon - 1 teaspoon per cup of zoodles)","For each 1 cup serving of zoodles (use 1-2 garlic cloves, minced or \\u00bd -1 teaspoon dried minced garlic (we used McCormick brand))","For each 1 cup serving of zoodles (use a few squirts of fresh lemon juice or more to tastef (up to 1 tablespoon))","kosher salt to taste","pepper to taste","1 teaspoon sesame seeds (optional but recommended)","1 cup tahini","1 garlic clove (minced)","2 tablespoons + 2 teaspoons fresh lemon juice","\\u00bc teaspoon of sea salt (add more to taste)","3\\/4 cup of warm water (add more as needed or desired)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Tips for prepping ahead\\/ reheating","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Roasted veggies can be made ahead, stored in the refrigerator in sealed containers and served room temperature or heated up. I find the best way to heat up roasted veggies in in a skillet with a touch of olive oil. Alternatively you can heat them up in the oven.","name":"Roasted veggies can be made ahead, stored in the refrigerator in sealed containers and served room temperature or heated up. I find the best way to heat up roasted veggies in in a skillet with a touch of olive oil. Alternatively you can heat them up in the oven.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Tahini Sauce can be made ahead and stored in a sealed container in the refrigerator for several days.","name":"Tahini Sauce can be made ahead and stored in a sealed container in the refrigerator for several days.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Zoodles: I find it best to spiralize the zucchini noodles ahead of time (if you haven\'t purchased them already spiralized), but to quick saute them in a skillet when ready to eat. The raw spiralized zoodles stay well in the refrigerator in a sealed container for several days.","name":"Zoodles: I find it best to spiralize the zucchini noodles ahead of time (if you haven\'t purchased them already spiralized), but to quick saute them in a skillet when ready to eat. The raw spiralized zoodles stay well in the refrigerator in a sealed container for several days.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-0-2"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Roasted Veggies","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat oven to 400\\u00b0F and line 3 baking sheets with parchment paper.","name":"Preheat oven to 400\\u00b0F and line 3 baking sheets with parchment paper.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-1-0"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Spiced Butternut Squash:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a large bowl add oil, cumin, paprika, and sea salt and mix to combine.","name":"In a large bowl add oil, cumin, paprika, and sea salt and mix to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-2-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add Butternut Squash and toss to cover in oil-spice mixture.","name":"Add Butternut Squash and toss to cover in oil-spice mixture.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-2-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Arrange in a single layer on baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes. Turn squash over. Bake an additional 15 minutes or until tender. For more crispy squash, bake a bit longer. Set aside.","name":"Arrange in a single layer on baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes. Turn squash over. Bake an additional 15 minutes or until tender. For more crispy squash, bake a bit longer. Set aside.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-2-2"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Brussels Spouts","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Toss in a small amount of olive or avocado oil. Place in single layer on baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake for 30 minutes, or until crispy","name":"Toss in a small amount of olive or avocado oil. Place in single layer on baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake for 30 minutes, or until crispy","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-3-0"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Cauliflower","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a medium bowl, mix a 1-2 tablespoons of oil with the turmeric until well combined.","name":"In a medium bowl, mix a 1-2 tablespoons of oil with the turmeric until well combined.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-4-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add cauliflower florets and toss to cover cauliflower with the turmeric-oil mixture. Add more oil and turmeric as needed or desired to coat all the cauliflower.","name":"Add cauliflower florets and toss to cover cauliflower with the turmeric-oil mixture. Add more oil and turmeric as needed or desired to coat all the cauliflower.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-4-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place cauliflower in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.","name":"Place cauliflower in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-4-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bake 30 minutes or until starting to brown and get crispy on edges.","name":"Bake 30 minutes or until starting to brown and get crispy on edges.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-4-3"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Garlicky and Lemony Zoodles (recommended to saute when ready to serve)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat olive oil in a medium sauce pan over medium heat. When olive oil hot and shimmering (not smoking), add garlic* if using fresh garlic, stir for about 30 seconds until fragrant. Add zucchini noodles. Saute stirring frequently until Zucchini noodles are tender crisp, approximately 5 minutes. (Adjust cooking time if your noodles are thicker or thinner). *If using dried minced garlic, add to zoodles, once they are already cooking.","name":"Heat olive oil in a medium sauce pan over medium heat. When olive oil hot and shimmering (not smoking), add garlic* if using fresh garlic, stir for about 30 seconds until fragrant. Add zucchini noodles. Saute stirring frequently until Zucchini noodles are tender crisp, approximately 5 minutes. (Adjust cooking time if your noodles are thicker or thinner). *If using dried minced garlic, add to zoodles, once they are already cooking.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-5-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Season with salt to taste and give a few squirts of fresh lemon juice. A little goes a long way so start with a few squirts and add more to taste.","name":"Season with salt to taste and give a few squirts of fresh lemon juice. A little goes a long way so start with a few squirts and add more to taste.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-5-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove from heat and Stir in sesame seeds.","name":"Remove from heat and Stir in sesame seeds.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-5-2"}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Tahini Sauce","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place all ingredients in a food processor and process until smooth, You may have to stop and scape down the sides.","name":"Place all ingredients in a food processor and process until smooth, You may have to stop and scape down the sides.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-6-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Taste and adjust as desired. Add more water for a thinner sauce, more lemon juice for a brighter and tangier sauce.","name":"Taste and adjust as desired. Add more water for a thinner sauce, more lemon juice for a brighter and tangier sauce.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.healthygffamily.com\\/recipe\\/warm-zoodle-bowl-with-roasted-veggies-and-tahini-sauce-2\\/#wprm-recipe-17110-step-6-1"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"1","reviewCount":"1"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I recently made the roasted veggies and tahini sauce from this recipe and I could not be happier. Not only did my husband and I enjoy the richness of the tahini sauce, but my two and a half year old daughter devoured all of her veggies and kept asking for more sauce! I am going to keep a batch of this sauce on hand so that I can give it to her as an alternative to her beloved vegan ranch dressing :). Thank you for sharing your recipes!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Pam"},"datePublished":"2018-11-26"}],"recipeCategory":["Sides","Dinner","Veggie"],"recipeCuisine":["Gluten-Free","Vegetarian","Vegan"],"keywords":"fall vegetable bowls, gluten-free vegan cozy meal"}',
            'image' => 'https://www.healthygffamily.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/CFAC0B42-7015-4238-807D-A8B9FC1722A4-300x300-1.jpg',
        'ingredients' => '["1 package pre-cubed butternut squash or 1 butternut squash (peeled and cubed)","2 tablespoons olive oil","1 teaspoon ground cumin","1 teaspoon hot smoked Spanish paprika","\\u00bd teaspoon sea salt","Neutral oil of your choice like avocado oil","1 teaspoon turmeric (sometimes I add more depending on how much cauliflower I have)","Kosher Salt","Pepper","4 zucchini","Olive oil (approximately \\u00bd teaspoon - 1 teaspoon per cup of zoodles)","For each 1 cup serving of zoodles (use 1-2 garlic cloves, minced or \\u00bd -1 teaspoon dried minced garlic (we used McCormick brand))","For each 1 cup serving of zoodles (use a few squirts of fresh lemon juice or more to tastef (up to 1 tablespoon))","kosher salt to taste","pepper to taste","1 teaspoon sesame seeds (optional but recommended)","1 cup tahini","1 garlic clove (minced)","2 tablespoons + 2 teaspoons fresh lemon juice","\\u00bc teaspoon of sea salt (add more to taste)","3\\/4 cup of warm water (add more as needed or desired)"]',
        'directions' => '{"Tips for prepping ahead\\/ reheating":["Roasted veggies can be made ahead, stored in the refrigerator in sealed containers and served room temperature or heated up. I find the best way to heat up roasted veggies in in a skillet with a touch of olive oil. Alternatively you can heat them up in the oven.","Tahini Sauce can be made ahead and stored in a sealed container in the refrigerator for several days.","Zoodles: I find it best to spiralize the zucchini noodles ahead of time (if you haven\'t purchased them already spiralized), but to quick saute them in a skillet when ready to eat. The raw spiralized zoodles stay well in the refrigerator in a sealed container for several days."],"Roasted Veggies":["Preheat oven to 400\\u00b0F and line 3 baking sheets with parchment paper."],"Spiced Butternut Squash:":["In a large bowl add oil, cumin, paprika, and sea salt and mix to combine.","Add Butternut Squash and toss to cover in oil-spice mixture.","Arrange in a single layer on baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes. Turn squash over. Bake an additional 15 minutes or until tender. For more crispy squash, bake a bit longer. Set aside."],"Brussels Spouts":["Toss in a small amount of olive or avocado oil. Place in single layer on baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake for 30 minutes, or until crispy"],"Cauliflower":["In a medium bowl, mix a 1-2 tablespoons of oil with the turmeric until well combined.","Add cauliflower florets and toss to cover cauliflower with the turmeric-oil mixture. Add more oil and turmeric as needed or desired to coat all the cauliflower.","Place cauliflower in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.","Bake 30 minutes or until starting to brown and get crispy on edges."],"Garlicky and Lemony Zoodles (recommended to saute when ready to serve)":["Heat olive oil in a medium sauce pan over medium heat. When olive oil hot and shimmering (not smoking), add garlic* if using fresh garlic, stir for about 30 seconds until fragrant. Add zucchini noodles. Saute stirring frequently until Zucchini noodles are tender crisp, approximately 5 minutes. (Adjust cooking time if your noodles are thicker or thinner). *If using dried minced garlic, add to zoodles, once they are already cooking.","Season with salt to taste and give a few squirts of fresh lemon juice. A little goes a long way so start with a few squirts and add more to taste.","Remove from heat and Stir in sesame seeds."],"Tahini Sauce":["Place all ingredients in a food processor and process until smooth, You may have to stop and scape down the sides.","Taste and adjust as desired. Add more water for a thinner sauce, more lemon juice for a brighter and tangier sauce."]}',
            'nutrition' => '[""]',
