9a22e1e7ce39c3"},"description":"Mediterranean Power Bowls with avocado salad, chickpeas, and smoky red pepper sauce. These vegetarian quinoa bowls are packed with nutritious ingredients and perfect for meal prep.","datePublished":"2020-06-24T12:42:45+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/06\\/MediterraneanPowerBowlsSQUARE.jpg","https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/06\\/MediterraneanPowerBowlsSQUARE-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/06\\/MediterraneanPowerBowlsSQUARE-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/06\\/MediterraneanPowerBowlsSQUARE-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["4"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT15M","totalTime":"PT30M","recipeIngredient":["1 cup dry quinoa","1\\/2 tsp. kosher salt, divided","1 (15-oz. can) chickpeas, rinsed and drained","1\\/2 tsp. ground cumin","1\\/2 English cucumber, sliced into coins and then quartered","1 avocado, sliced into small cubes","1\\/2 cup finely chopped red onion","2 Tbsp. rice vinegar","1\\/4 tsp. black pepper","3 oz. crumbled feta cheese","Fresh basil and lemon wedges for serving","1 (12-oz.) jar roasted red peppers, drained","1\\/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil","1 garlic clove","1 tsp. smoked paprika","1\\/4 tsp. red pepper flakes","1\\/4 tsp. kosher salt"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Combine quinoa, 2 cups of water, and 1\\/4 tsp. salt in a saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat to low, cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes, until quinoa is fluffy and all liquid is absorbed. Remove from heat, stir in chickpeas and cumin, cover, and let sit until ready to assemble bowls.","name":"Combine quinoa, 2 cups of water, and 1\\/4 tsp. salt in a saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat to low, cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes, until quinoa is fluffy and all liquid is absorbed. Remove from heat, stir in chickpeas and cumin, cover, and let sit until ready to assemble bowls.","url":"https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/mediterranean-power-bowls-with-smoky-red-pepper-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-12877-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"While quinoa is cooking, prepare avocado-cucumber salad by combining cucumber, avocado, red onion, vinegar, remaining 1\\/4 tsp. salt, and 1\\/4 tsp. black pepper in a bowl. Gently toss to combine.","name":"While quinoa is cooking, prepare avocado-cucumber salad by combining cucumber, avocado, red onion, vinegar, remaining 1\\/4 tsp. salt, and 1\\/4 tsp. black pepper in a bowl. Gently toss to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/mediterranean-power-bowls-with-smoky-red-pepper-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-12877-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Prepare red pepper sauce by combining roasted red peppers, olive oil, garlic, smoked paprika, red pepper flakes, and salt in a small blender or nutribullet. Blend on high speed until creamy.","name":"Prepare red pepper sauce by combining roasted red peppers, olive oil, garlic, smoked paprika, red pepper flakes, and salt in a small blender or nutribullet. Blend on high speed until creamy.","url":"https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/mediterranean-power-bowls-with-smoky-red-pepper-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-12877-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Assemble bowls by dividing quinoa and chickpea mixture evenly between four bowls. Top each portion evenly with avocado-cucumber salad, red pepper sauce, and feta cheese. Garnish with fresh basil and lemon wedges, if desired. Enjoy warm, chilled, or close to room temperature.","name":"Assemble bowls by dividing quinoa and chickpea mixture evenly between four bowls. Top each portion evenly with avocado-cucumber salad, red pepper sauce, and feta cheese. Garnish with fresh basil and lemon wedges, if desired. Enjoy warm, chilled, or close to room temperature.","url":"https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/mediterranean-power-bowls-with-smoky-red-pepper-sauce\\/#wprm-recipe-12877-step-0-3"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"8","reviewCount":"6"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was absolutely delicious. We doubled the sauce to have on hand, which was the smartest decision of the week. This will definitely be on repeat especially during the summer. We also used moroccan couscous instead of quinoa because we made Jamie\\u2019s southwest quinoa salad earlier in the week and wanted to mix up our grains. So basically run to make this recipe and the southwest quinoa salad because they are so good and easy.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Katelyn"},"datePublished":"2021-05-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Loved this recipe! I love how the smokiness of the sauce contrasts the bright flavors of the avocado\\/cucumber\\/onion salad. Basil was definitely a must have too. Used this for meal prep for the week, and I have to say it\\u2019s one of my favorites! Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Ethan E."},"datePublished":"2020-06-30"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"These came together easy and were so delicious!! We ended up with some leftover sauce, so I used it on roasted veggies (broccoli and asparagus) as you suggested.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kate"},"datePublished":"2020-06-29"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Can\\u2019t wait to try these!! That red pepper sauce sounds delicious!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sammie"},"datePublished":"2020-06-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"One of my favorite recipes for meal prep!! Love the crunch of the salad and kick of the sauce!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Bailey"},"datePublished":"2020-06-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Looks absolutely amazing! Can\'t wait to make this for my family!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"HockeyMom1977"},"datePublished":"2016-05-19"}],"recipeCategory":["Grain Bowl","lunch"],"recipeCuisine":["Mediterranean"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/GlutenFreeDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VegetarianDiet"],"keywords":"healthy bowls, quinoa bowls, red pepper sauce","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 bowl","calories":"510 kcal","proteinContent":"16 g","carbohydrateContent":"55 g","fiberContent":"9 g","sugarContent":"7 g","fatContent":"26 g","saturatedFatContent":"5 g","sodiumContent":"890 mg"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/mediterranean-power-bowls-with-smoky-red-pepper-sauce\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/mediterranean-power-bowls-with-smoky-red-pepper-sauce\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/dishingouthealth.com\\/mediterranean-power-bowls-with-smoky-red-pepper-sauce\\/"}]}',
