.jpg","caption":"Suzy Karadsheh"},"description":"Founder and CEO of The Mediterranean Dish | Two-time New York Times Best Selling Cookbook Author | Specializing in Mediterranean Cuisine Suzy Karadsheh is a true daughter of the Mediterranean. She was born on the coast of Egypt in the bustling cosmopolitan city of Port Said, the North entrance of the Suez Canal, and just a boat ride away from places like Italy, Greece, Turkey, Lebanon, Palestine, and Israel.","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/","http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/themediterraneandish","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/themediterraneandish\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/themeddish\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/c\\/themediterraneandish","https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Healthy-Recipes-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B09NPM8CHK?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1","https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Diet-Inspired-Joyfully-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B0CQWZS2Q2?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1","https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/stores\\/Suzy-Karadsheh\\/author\\/B09PF37MGS?ref=ap_rdr&shoppingPortalEnabled=true&ccs_id=b7fed9c5-4667-4aca-8419-9cdba5947dab"],"award":["Two-time New York Times Bestselling author"],"knowsAbout":["Mediterranean cuisine"],"jobTitle":"Author, CEO and Founder of The Mediterranean Dish","worksFor":"The Mediterranean Dish","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/author\\/suzythemediterraneandish-com\\/","hasCredential":[{"@type":"EducationalOccupationalCredential","name":"Published Author: The Mediterranean Dish: 120 Bold and Healthy Recipes You\'ll Make on Repeat","url":"https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Healthy-Recipes-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B09NPM8CHK?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1"},{"@type":"EducationalOccupationalCredential","name":"Published Author: The Mediterranean Dish: Simply Dinner: 125 Easy Mediterranean Diet-Inspired Recipes to Eat Well and Live Joyfully","url":"https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Diet-Inspired-Joyfully-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B0CQWZS2Q2?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1"}]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Mediterranean Spicy Spinach and Lentil Soup","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/a3169080f5b7356eb258ec57a76945c5"},"description":"The secret to this spicy lentil soup recipe is in the bold aromatics and warm Mediterranean spices. And don\\u2019t omit the lime juice; it will brighten the soup and pull the flavors together in the best way possible. Use a bag of frozen spinach, no need to thaw ahead of time. And forthe lentils, I recommend green, black, or small brown lentils.","datePublished":"2022-01-16T10:13:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/spicy-lentil-soup-recipe-10.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/spicy-lentil-soup-recipe-10-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/spicy-lentil-soup-recipe-10-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2022\\/01\\/spicy-lentil-soup-recipe-10-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Spicy Spinach Lentil Soup","description":"This spicy vegan lentil soup is loaded with aromatics, bold Mediterranean spices, and amped up with spinach!","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/thumbs\\/Su7pqMCd-720.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/videos\\/Su7pqMCd.mp4","uploadDate":"2022-01-13T16:47:22.000Z","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["6","6 people (up to)"],"prepTime":"PT5M","cookTime":"PT30M","recipeIngredient":["extra virgin olive oil,","1 large yellow onion, (finely chopped)","1 large garlic clove, (chopped)","kosher salt and black pepper","1 1\\/2 teaspoon ground coriander","1 1\\/2 teaspoon ground cumin","1 1\\/2 teaspoon sumac","1 1\\/2 teaspoon crushed red peppers","2 teaspoon dried mint flakes","Pinch of sugar","1 tablespoon flour","6 cups low-sodium vegetable broth","3 cups water, (more if needed)","12 ounces frozen cut leaf spinach, (no need to thaw)","1 1\\/2 cups green lentils or small brown lentils,","1 lime, (juice of)","2 cups chopped flat leaf parsley"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a large ceramic or cast iron pot, heat 2 tbsp olive oil. Add the chopped onions and sautee until golden brown. Add the garlic, all the spices, dried mint, sugar and flour. Cook for about 2 minutes on medium heat stirring regularly.","name":"In a large ceramic or cast iron pot, heat 2 tbsp olive oil. Add the chopped onions and sautee until golden brown. Add the garlic, all the spices, dried mint, sugar and flour. Cook for about 2 minutes on medium heat stirring regularly.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/mediterranean-spicy-spinach-lentil-soup\\/#wprm-recipe-10551-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Now add the broth and water. Raise the heat to high and bring the liquid to a rolling boil; add the frozen spinach and the lentils. Cook for 5 minutes on high heat then reduce the heat to medium-low. Cover and cook for 20 minutes or until the lentils are fully cooked to tender. (Partway through cooking, check the liquid levels, and if you need to add a little bit of hot water.)","name":"Now add the broth and water. Raise the heat to high and bring the liquid to a rolling boil; add the frozen spinach and the lentils. Cook for 5 minutes on high heat then reduce the heat to medium-low. Cover and cook for 20 minutes or until the lentils are fully cooked to tender. (Partway through cooking, check the liquid levels, and if you need to add a little bit of hot water.)","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/mediterranean-spicy-spinach-lentil-soup\\/#wprm-recipe-10551-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the lentils are fully cooked, stir in the lime juice and chopped parsley. Remove from the heat and let sit covered for 5 minutes or so. Serve hot with pita bread or your favorite rustic Italian bread.","name":"Once the lentils are fully cooked, stir in the lime juice and chopped parsley. Remove from the heat and let sit covered for 5 minutes or so. Serve hot with pita bread or your favorite rustic Italian bread.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/mediterranean-spicy-spinach-lentil-soup\\/#wprm-recipe-10551-step-0-2"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.92","ratingCount":"212","reviewCount":"9"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I didnt incorporate sugar or flour and substituted spinach with carrots and still tastes amazing! Thanks for the recipe this is perfect to snack on through out the week.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Neda"},"datePublished":"2026-07-08"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Hi Suzy\\r\\nI absolutely loved your Spicy lentil soup, in fact I cook one of your soup recipes every week . Your one pot suppers is also a winner!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Colleen"},"datePublished":"2026-02-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Delicious the whole family loves it and I make this recipe often as they ask for it.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Melanie"},"datePublished":"2025-12-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"reviewBody":"I was a little skeptical about adding 1.5 t of crushed red pepper flakes, so I cut it down to 1\\/2t or so. Holy Heck! That\\u2019s spicy!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Steve Sheldon"},"datePublished":"2025-12-19"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I\'m newer to cooking with lentils and found this recipe it was easy to follow. I also like that the base was different than the tomato base, that are good, but I like changing things up. It was delicious I will add it to my meatless Monday list. The only variations since I did not have mint leaves I used parsley and for my husband I added some Italian sausage I had cooked earlier in the week. I will definitely make this again! I can\'t wait to try your Italian lentil soup recipe.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Patty Jacobs"},"datePublished":"2025-12-14"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I\'m newer to cooking with lentils and found this recipe it was easy to follow. I also like that the base was different than the tomato base, that are good, but I like changing things up. It was delicious I will add it to my meatless Monday list. The only variations since I did not have mint leaves I used parsley and for my husband I added some Italian sausage I had cooked earlier in the week. I will definitely make this again! I can\'t wait to try your Italian lentil soup recipe.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Patty"},"datePublished":"2025-12-14"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I found this recipe through an article by the kitchn and I\'m so glad I did: so many lentil soup recipes I\'ve tried go too hard on the cumin and result in a more porridge consistency. This was brighter and less heavy, yet still so filling! I couldn\'t find dried mint or sumac, so I substituted with fresh mint and a dash of lemon pepper (after some internet research). \\r\\nLooking forward to trying this again, maybe adding ground sausage like others have suggested. \\r\\nThank you for a delicious dinner!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"JS"},"datePublished":"2025-12-09"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"3"},"reviewBody":"I usually love your recipes! This one was good, too, but I think it could really shine with some extra veggies \\u2014 maybe potatoes, carrots, celery or canned tomatoes.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jules"},"datePublished":"2025-10-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I made this soup this past weekend. It is delicious","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dianne P Clough"},"datePublished":"2025-10-16"}],"recipeCategory":["Dinner","Soup"],"recipeCuisine":["Mediterranean"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VeganDiet","https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/VegetarianDiet"],"keywords":"green lentil recipe, green lentil soup, Lentil soup","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"249.9 kcal","sodiumContent":"169.7 mg","fatContent":"3.7 g","saturatedFatContent":"0.5 g","carbohydrateContent":"40.3 g","fiberContent":"19.1 g","proteinContent":"16.7 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"2.7 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/mediterranean-spicy-spinach-lentil-soup\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/mediterranean-spicy-spinach-lentil-soup\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/mediterranean-spicy-spinach-lentil-soup\\/"}]}',
