ey, Lebanon, Palestine, and Israel.","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/","http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/themediterraneandish","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/themediterraneandish\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/themeddish\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/c\\/themediterraneandish","https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Healthy-Recipes-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B09NPM8CHK?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1","https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Diet-Inspired-Joyfully-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B0CQWZS2Q2?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1","https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/stores\\/Suzy-Karadsheh\\/author\\/B09PF37MGS?ref=ap_rdr&shoppingPortalEnabled=true&ccs_id=b7fed9c5-4667-4aca-8419-9cdba5947dab"],"award":["Two-time New York Times Bestselling author"],"knowsAbout":["Mediterranean cuisine"],"jobTitle":"Author, CEO and Founder of The Mediterranean Dish","worksFor":"The Mediterranean Dish","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/author\\/suzythemediterraneandish-com\\/","hasCredential":[{"@type":"EducationalOccupationalCredential","name":"Published Author: The Mediterranean Dish: 120 Bold and Healthy Recipes You\'ll Make on Repeat","url":"https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Healthy-Recipes-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B09NPM8CHK?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1"},{"@type":"EducationalOccupationalCredential","name":"Published Author: The Mediterranean Dish: Simply Dinner: 125 Easy Mediterranean Diet-Inspired Recipes to Eat Well and Live Joyfully","url":"https:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/Mediterranean-Dish-Diet-Inspired-Joyfully-Cookbook-ebook\\/dp\\/B0CQWZS2Q2?ref_=ast_author_dp&th=1&psc=1"}]},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Harissa Honey Chicken","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/a3169080f5b7356eb258ec57a76945c5"},"description":"This sweet and spicy chicken recipe is layered with smoky, warming, garlicky, citrusy notes. So easy and yet it brings restaurant-level flavor! You can let the chicken marinate overnight for even more zing, but the marinade is so tasty that even 20 minutes while your oven heats up is plenty.","datePublished":"2024-04-17T08:00:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Harissa-Honey-Chicken-15.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Harissa-Honey-Chicken-15-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Harissa-Honey-Chicken-15-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/04\\/Harissa-Honey-Chicken-15-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Harissa Honey Chicken","description":"Sweet and spicy chicken with my Mediterranean twist!","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/thumbs\\/6hf1xpFM-720.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/content.jwplatform.com\\/videos\\/6hf1xpFM.mp4","uploadDate":"2024-04-11T17:23:45.000Z","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["4","4 to 6"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT35M","totalTime":"PT45M","recipeIngredient":["2 to 4 tablespoons harissa paste","2 tablespoons tomato paste","1\\/4 cup honey","1 lemon, (juiced)","Extra virgin olive oil","1 teaspoon Urfa Biber, (Aleppo pepper, or red chili flakes)","1 teaspoon coriander","1\\/2 teaspoon smoked paprika","5 garlic cloves, (minced)","8 to 10 boneless skinless chicken thighs ((about 2 pounds))","Kosher salt","Black pepper"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Make the honey-harissa marinade. In a large mixing bowl, combine the harissa, tomato paste, honey, lemon juice, and enough olive oil to generously coat the chicken (I used 1\\/3 cup). Add the Urfa Biber, coriander, smoked paprika, and garlic. Whisk until well incorporated.","name":"Make the honey-harissa marinade. In a large mixing bowl, combine the harissa, tomato paste, honey, lemon juice, and enough olive oil to generously coat the chicken (I used 1\\/3 cup). Add the Urfa Biber, coriander, smoked paprika, and garlic. Whisk until well incorporated.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-84393-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Marinate the chicken. Season the chicken well on both sides with salt and pepper, then add to the marinade. Mix well to make sure the chicken is fully coated. If you have the time, cover and refrigerate for a couple of hours or overnight. Otherwise, allow it to sit at room temperature while your oven heats.","name":"Marinate the chicken. Season the chicken well on both sides with salt and pepper, then add to the marinade. Mix well to make sure the chicken is fully coated. If you have the time, cover and refrigerate for a couple of hours or overnight. Otherwise, allow it to sit at room temperature while your oven heats.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-84393-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Get ready. Preheat your oven to 400\\u00b0F.","name":"Get ready. Preheat your oven to 400\\u00b0F.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-84393-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bake. Transfer the chicken and the marinade to a 9x13 baking pan. Place the chicken on the center rack of your heated oven and bake until the chicken is cooked through and the surface is nicely caramelized with some charred bits, about 35 to 40 minutes.","name":"Bake. Transfer the chicken and the marinade to a 9x13 baking pan. Place the chicken on the center rack of your heated oven and bake until the chicken is cooked through and the surface is nicely caramelized with some charred bits, about 35 to 40 minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-84393-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Finish and serve. Drizzle a bit of the pan juices over the chicken and serve!","name":"Finish and serve. Drizzle a bit of the pan juices over the chicken and serve!","url":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/#wprm-recipe-84393-step-0-4"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.98","ratingCount":"39","reviewCount":"11"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I\\u2019ve made this a couple of times. Simple to do and delicious!! I got the harissa from your store\\u2026.this time I served it with a simple side of roasted homegrown asparagus and it was wonderful.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Melissa"},"datePublished":"2026-05-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Oh my goodness!! My husband and I love this chicken. Definitely a keeper.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Pam Harford"},"datePublished":"2025-12-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"My pickiest eater just requested this dish, AGAIN! Delicious and comforting \\ud83d\\ude0b","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kelly Ayers"},"datePublished":"2025-10-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"So yummy and flavorful! My family loved it! These recipes you share that take a marinade and then in the oven for 30 minutes are wonderful! Timesaving and tasty. I love this one and the Balsamic chicken thigh recipe also!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Terri"},"datePublished":"2025-09-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Delicious! Have already repeated the recipe twice.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Felicia"},"datePublished":"2025-07-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Amazing! Tastes so good with some toum and tabbouleh.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"SRN"},"datePublished":"2025-06-09"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Ohhh my.... soooo juicy and full of flavour. I made it in the airfryer and had it simply with tzatziki sauce.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kat"},"datePublished":"2025-06-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Very easy, very flavorful. Everyone loved it. Will definitely repeat!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Felicia"},"datePublished":"2025-05-26"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I loved this recipe. It was like a Mediterranean bbq. Served it with a little couscous and the creamy cucumber salad. Another winner from the Dish.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kim Massetti"},"datePublished":"2025-04-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I have made many things from The Mediterranean Dish site, but this was absolutely the best thing I\'ve made. I can\'t wait to fix it again!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Laura"},"datePublished":"2025-04-11"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This recipe was great! It was sweet with a bit of heat. Huge plus that I had most ingredients on hand.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Sierra Matheson"},"datePublished":"2025-04-10"}],"recipeCategory":["Entree"],"recipeCuisine":["American\\/Mediterranean"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/LowLactoseDiet"],"keywords":"Baked chicken thighs, chicken thighs, harissa, honey","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"361 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"24.4 g","proteinContent":"44.7 g","fatContent":"9.5 g","saturatedFatContent":"2.4 g","transFatContent":"0.04 g","cholesterolContent":"214.7 mg","sodiumContent":"367.1 mg","fiberContent":"1.5 g","sugarContent":"20.1 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"5.3 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/www.themediterraneandish.com\\/harissa-honey-chicken\\/"}]}',
