uthentic Jamaican rice and peas recipe is an easy side dish with lots of island vibes! It\'s packed with flavour and so simple to make.","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/05\\/Jamaican-Peas-and-Rice5200.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/05\\/Jamaican-Peas-and-Rice5200.jpg","width":1200,"height":1800,"caption":"Overhead view of Jamaican rice and peas in pan"},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/recipes\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Diet","item":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/recipes\\/diet\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":4,"name":"Dairy Free","item":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/recipes\\/diet\\/dairy-free\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":5,"name":"Jamaican Rice and Peas"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/","name":"Jessica in the Kitchen","description":"A vegan recipe food blog with simple, delicious and approachable recipes. Pulled from the earth. Hot from the oven. Straight from the heart.","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/#organization","name":"Jessica in the Kitchen","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/05\\/Square-Yoast-Logo.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/05\\/Square-Yoast-Logo.jpg","width":600,"height":600,"caption":"Jessica in the Kitchen"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["http:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/jessicainthekitchenblog","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/jessinkitchen","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/jessicainthekitchen\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/jessicaskitchen\\/","https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/channel\\/UCkP2CvRubyU0MTZv_Qo712g"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/995b11a4372934bc756f38bf85ccd437","name":"Jessica from Jessica in the Kitchen","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/about\\/"],"url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/author\\/jessica\\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Jamaican Rice and Peas","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/995b11a4372934bc756f38bf85ccd437"},"description":"This authentic Jamaican rice and peas recipe is an easy side dish with lots of island vibes! It&#039;s packed with flavour and so simple to make.","datePublished":"2024-05-29T09:14:00+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/05\\/Jamaican-Peas-and-Rice5212.jpg","https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/05\\/Jamaican-Peas-and-Rice5212-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/05\\/Jamaican-Peas-and-Rice5212-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2024\\/05\\/Jamaican-Peas-and-Rice5212-480x270.jpg"],"video":{"name":"Jamaican Rice and Peas (the REAL way) + How to Make Coconut Milk","description":"Full Printable Recipe Here: \\nhttps:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/ \\n\\nMy Homemade Coconut Milk Recipe: \\nhttps:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/coconut-milk\\/ \\n\\nSome dishes just feel like home, and for me, Jamaican Rice and Peas is one of them. It\\u2019s a staple I grew up eating, and while it\\u2019s naturally vegan, this version is packed with so much flavor and nostalgia, I had to share it with you!\\n\\nIn this video, I\\u2019m showing you how to make authentic Jamaican rice and peas with coconut milk, plus how to make coconut milk from shredded coconut at home. I also walk you through two ways to cook kidney beans: the classic overnight soak and a quick boil method for when you\\u2019re short on time. A must-have at dinners, celebrations, and family gatherings, Rice and Peas is ready in just 20 minutes, great for meal prep, and pairs perfectly with everything from brown stew tofu to curries or saut\\u00e9ed greens. Whether you call it Jamaican rice and peas, rice and peas Jamaican style, or Jamaican rice and beans, this dish is a must try side dish! \\n\\nSign up for my free newsletter here: https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/subscribe\\/\\n\\nTimecodes:\\n\\n0:00 - Why Jamaican Rice and Peas in the best side dish \\n0:33 - Ingredients You\\u2019ll Need for Jamaican Rice and Peas\\n1:42 - How to Make Coconut Milk from Coconut Flakes \\n2:27- How to Strain Coconut Milk for a Silky Smooth Finish\\n3:30 - Why You Should Chill Coconut Milk Before Using It\\n3:53 - How to Soak Kidney Beans Overnight for Jamaican Rice and Peas\\n4:30 - Quick Boil Method: How to Cook Kidney Beans Without Soaking Overnight \\n5:40 - How to Make Jamaican Rice and Peas on the Stove \\n6:07 - How to Know When Kidney Beans Are Cooked\\n7:10 - How to Fluff Rice for the Perfect Texture\\n7:15 - Final Results + How to Serve Jamaican Rice and Peas\\n7:44 - Taste Test | The Flavor Breakdown\\n8:25 - Tips and Tricks for the BEST Jamaican Rice and Peas\\n8:45 - What Kind of Kidney Beans and Rice Should You Use for Rice and Peas? \\n9:10 - Can You Make Jamaican Rice and Peas Same-Day? + Pressure Cooker Tips\\n9:30 - DON\\u2019T Burst Your Scotch Bonnet! Here\\u2019s Why\\n10:05 - Can I Use Other Beans in Rice and Peas?\\n10:23 - What to Serve with Jamaican Rice and Peas\\n10:41- Outro | Where to Find More Vegan Jamaican Recipes\\n\\nIngredients you\\u2019ll need: \\n\\nDried red kidney beans\\nWater\\nUncooked long grain rice\\nFull-fat coconut milk\\nSea salt\\nScallion\\nScotch bonnet pepper\\nGarlic\\nPimento berries or allspice\\nThyme\\n\\n#jamaicanriceandpeas #riceandpeas #riceandbeans #jamaicanfood #veganrecipes #easydinnerrecipes \\n\\n___________________________________________________________\\n\\nDownload my Ebook About Transitioning to a Meatless Lifestyle: https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/ebook\\u200b\\n\\nFollow along for more!\\n\\nWebsite: https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\u200b\\nFacebook: https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/jessicainthekitchenblog\\/\\nInstagram: https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/jessicainthekitchen\\/\\nTiktok: https:\\/\\/www.tiktok.com\\/@jessicainthekitchen\\nPinterest: https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/jessicaskitchen\\/\\n\\nAll of my recipes!: https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\u200b\\n\\n___________________________________________________________\\n\\nEquipment:\\n\\nCameras: Canon 5D Mark IV: https:\\/\\/rstyle.me\\/n\\/c2g362bek9f\\u200b\\nCanon 7D Mark II: https:\\/\\/rstyle.me\\/n\\/c2g37ibek9f\\u200b\\n\\n___________________________________________________________\\n\\n\\nThanks so much for watching!! Please subscribe because I\\u2019ll be sharing a new video every week!\\n\\nLove,\\n\\nJessica","uploadDate":"2025-03-30T15:00:06+00:00","duration":"PT11M46S","thumbnailUrl":"https:\\/\\/i.ytimg.com\\/vi\\/NIqM42lwOBk\\/hqdefault.jpg","embedUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/NIqM42lwOBk?feature=oembed","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NIqM42lwOBk","@type":"VideoObject"},"recipeYield":["8","8 people"],"prepTime":"PT20M","cookTime":"PT55M","totalTime":"PT75M","recipeIngredient":["1 cup dried red kidney beans (soaked overnight in water or for 8 hours at least*)","3 cups water (up to 4 cups to cover the peas while boiling)","2 cups uncooked long grain rice (not jasmine rice, and ensure the bag just says long grain rice**, washed and drained)","13.5 ounce can full fat coconut milk","1 teaspoon sea salt","3 stalks scallion (cut or torn in half)","1 scotch bonnet pepper","2 cloves of garlic","1 teaspoon pimento berries\\/allspice","A few sprigs of thyme"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Rinse your soaked kidney beans thoroughly in a sieve, strainer or colander. Discard that water it was soaking in.","name":"Rinse your soaked kidney beans thoroughly in a sieve, strainer or colander. Discard that water it was soaking in.","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#wprm-recipe-42130-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cover with 3 cups water to cover the kidney beans.","name":"Cover with 3 cups water to cover the kidney beans.","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#wprm-recipe-42130-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bring to a boil, then to a simmer at medium heat for 30 minutes to an hour (taste test after 30 minutes to see if it\\u2019s tender. My peas are always finished within 30 minutes. You may need to add up to an extra cup of water while the peas are simmering to ensure there\'s enough water in the pot.","name":"Bring to a boil, then to a simmer at medium heat for 30 minutes to an hour (taste test after 30 minutes to see if it\\u2019s tender. My peas are always finished within 30 minutes. You may need to add up to an extra cup of water while the peas are simmering to ensure there\'s enough water in the pot.","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#wprm-recipe-42130-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"After your peas are cooked (don&#39;t wash the peas nor throw out the leftover water), add in your rice, coconut milk, sea salt, scallion, scotch bonnet pepper, garlic, pimento\\/allsprice, thyme. Stir to combine.","name":"After your peas are cooked (don&#39;t wash the peas nor throw out the leftover water), add in your rice, coconut milk, sea salt, scallion, scotch bonnet pepper, garlic, pimento\\/allsprice, thyme. Stir to combine.","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#wprm-recipe-42130-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cover your pot with a tight fitting lid. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer at medium heat for about 15 minutes, then to low heat for about 5-10 more minutes until the rice is fully cooked through. Just watch your rice. It may cook in a quicker time period, or it may take a little bit longer. You may need to add in an extra \\u00bc cup of water in case the liquid boils out before the rice is fully cooked through.","name":"Cover your pot with a tight fitting lid. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer at medium heat for about 15 minutes, then to low heat for about 5-10 more minutes until the rice is fully cooked through. Just watch your rice. It may cook in a quicker time period, or it may take a little bit longer. You may need to add in an extra \\u00bc cup of water in case the liquid boils out before the rice is fully cooked through.","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#wprm-recipe-42130-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove from heat and let the rice sit, cover still on, for an extra 10 minutes. Taste test and add anything if necessary. Remove the seasonings and enjoy!","name":"Remove from heat and let the rice sit, cover still on, for an extra 10 minutes. Taste test and add anything if necessary. Remove the seasonings and enjoy!","url":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#wprm-recipe-42130-step-0-5"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"37","reviewCount":"6"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This recipe came out great! One note: I washed the rice separately to remove the starch before adding it to the pan with the rest of the ingredients. I appreciated the note to always keep an eye on the peas and rice when cooking, and adjust with extra water as needed. I had to add a bit more water when cooking the peas separately, and then when cooking the rice.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jaya S"},"datePublished":"2026-05-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"excellent recipe \\r\\nvery authentic","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Wendy GRAFE"},"datePublished":"2026-05-01"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Love the presentation of your rice and peas; looks very appealing. I can almost smell the Jamaican herbs and spices in the coconut milk. looks delicious \\ud83d\\ude0b.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kevin Foodie"},"datePublished":"2026-01-25"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Very good recipe. It came out delicious.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Cheryl Andrea Birkett"},"datePublished":"2026-01-05"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"My rice and peas came out perfect. Getting ready to make some for 140 guests.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dorene Smith"},"datePublished":"2025-11-13"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"EASY PEA-SY!\\r\\n\\r\\nGreat straitforwad recipe","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Polley"},"datePublished":"2025-07-17"}],"recipeCategory":["Side Dish"],"recipeCuisine":["Jamaican"],"keywords":"caribbean rice and peas, jamaican rice and peas, rice and beans","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"344 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"53 g","proteinContent":"10 g","fatContent":"11 g","saturatedFatContent":"9 g","sodiumContent":"308 mg","fiberContent":"4 g","sugarContent":"1 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"2 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/jessicainthekitchen.com\\/jamaican-rice-and-peas\\/"}]}',
            'image' => 'https://jessicainthekitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Jamaican-Peas-and-Rice5200.jpg',
        'ingredients' => '["1 cup dried red kidney beans (soaked overnight in water or for 8 hours at least*)","3 cups water (up to 4 cups to cover the peas while boiling)","2 cups uncooked long grain rice (not jasmine rice, and ensure the bag just says long grain rice**, washed and drained)","13.5 ounce can full fat coconut milk","1 teaspoon sea salt","3 stalks scallion (cut or torn in half)","1 scotch bonnet pepper","2 cloves of garlic","1 teaspoon pimento berries\\/allspice","A few sprigs of thyme"]',
        'directions' => '["Rinse your soaked kidney beans thoroughly in a sieve, strainer or colander. Discard that water it was soaking in.","Cover with 3 cups water to cover the kidney beans.","Bring to a boil, then to a simmer at medium heat for 30 minutes to an hour (taste test after 30 minutes to see if it\\u2019s tender. My peas are always finished within 30 minutes. You may need to add up to an extra cup of water while the peas are simmering to ensure there\'s enough water in the pot.","After your peas are cooked (don&#39;t wash the peas nor throw out the leftover water), add in your rice, coconut milk, sea salt, scallion, scotch bonnet pepper, garlic, pimento\\/allsprice, thyme. Stir to combine.","Cover your pot with a tight fitting lid. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer at medium heat for about 15 minutes, then to low heat for about 5-10 more minutes until the rice is fully cooked through. Just watch your rice. It may cook in a quicker time period, or it may take a little bit longer. You may need to add in an extra \\u00bc cup of water in case the liquid boils out before the rice is fully cooked through.","Remove from heat and let the rice sit, cover still on, for an extra 10 minutes. Taste test and add anything if necessary. Remove the seasonings and enjoy!"]',
            'nutrition' => '[{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"344 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"53 g","proteinContent":"10 g","fatContent":"11 g","saturatedFatContent":"9 g","sodiumContent":"308 mg","fiberContent":"4 g","sugarContent":"1 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"2 g","servingSize":"1 serving"}]',
