"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1747694777544"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1763605082233"},{"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1763605365129"}],"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/doner-kebab-featured.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/doner-kebab-featured.jpg","width":1200,"height":1200,"caption":"A close up image on a plate with Doner Kebab sandwiches on a bed of lettuce and Turkish sumac and onion salad."},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Turkish Recipes","item":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/category\\/turkish-recipes\\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Doner Kebab Recipe"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#website","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/","name":"Amira&#039;s Pantry","description":"Classic Mediterranean Dinner &amp; Comfort Food Recipes","publisher":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#organization","name":"Amira\'s Pantry","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/01\\/amiraspantry-logo-mobile-400.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/01\\/amiraspantry-logo-mobile-400.jpg","width":462,"height":140,"caption":"Amira\'s Pantry"},"image":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#\\/schema\\/logo\\/image\\/"},"sameAs":["https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/amiraspantry\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/amiraspantry","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/amiras_pantry\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/amiraspantry\\/"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/d5a0431e1c00c3d6a770bd869af383c9","name":"Amira Ibrahim","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/image\\/","url":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/f720c03d076d3be3e17ffce60907e956?s=96&r=g","contentUrl":"https:\\/\\/secure.gravatar.com\\/avatar\\/f720c03d076d3be3e17ffce60907e956?s=96&r=g","caption":"Amira Ibrahim"},"description":"I\\u2019m overjoyed that you have stopped by! My hope is to introduce you to new flavors, creative ways and fresh takes on favorites. To help you create food with style that will bring everyone around your kitchen table. From weeknight dinners for crazy busy days to desserts with the \\u201cwow\\u201d factor, and classic comforts from the Mediterranean. One thing in common, they are all recipes that have been tried and tested by family and friends.","sameAs":["https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/amira-ibrahim\\/","https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/amiraspantry","https:\\/\\/www.instagram.com\\/amiras_pantry\\/","https:\\/\\/www.pinterest.com\\/amiraspantry\\/","https:\\/\\/x.com\\/amiraspantry"],"url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/author\\/amira\\/"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1747694777544","position":1,"url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1747694777544","name":"How to store Doner Kebab?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Leftover Doner meat can be stored in an airtight container in the fridge for up to 3 days. Reheat in a hot non stick skillet until warmed thoroughly.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1763605082233","position":2,"url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1763605082233","name":"Can I freeze Doner Kebab?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Cooked or uncooked meat can be stored for up to 3 months. Thaw in the fridge before proceeding with the recipe or reheating.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1763605365129","position":3,"url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#faq-question-1763605365129","name":"Can I make this recipe ahead?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, of course you can. Make the rolls, place on a parchment paper and refrigerate for 24hours then bake on the day you are serving it. Freeze for longer as stated above.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Easy Homemade Doner Kebab","author":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/#\\/schema\\/person\\/d5a0431e1c00c3d6a770bd869af383c9"},"description":"This viral recipe for homemade Doner Kebab is so easy to make when you are craving a taste of Middle Eastern tradition. .Tender, spiced layers of meat, perfectly charred and tucked into a warm pita with crisp salad and sauce. All done in the comfort of your own kitchen.","datePublished":"2025-11-19T19:56:42+00:00","image":["https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/doner-kebab-card.jpg","https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/doner-kebab-card-500x500.jpg","https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/doner-kebab-card-500x375.jpg","https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2025\\/11\\/doner-kebab-card-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["8","8 Doner Kebab Rolls"],"prepTime":"PT15M","cookTime":"PT35M","recipeIngredient":["2 lbs ground beef (preferably 80-20)","1 large onion (quartered 300g)","5 large garlic cloves","3 Tablespoons plain yogurt","2 teaspoons salt (or to your liking)","1 teaspoon paprika","1 teaspoon cumin","1 teaspoon coriander","1 teaspoon oregano","1\\/2 teaspoon black pepper","1\\/4 teaspoon cinnamon","2 Tablespoon olive oil (more to moisten your hands)","2 Roma tomatoes","Assorted peppers","1 Tablespoon olive oil","Salt and pepper (to taste)","8 flatbread (preferably Lebanese or Lavash)","Hummus","Tzatziki (Yogurt Dill Sauce)","Toum","1 red onion (thinly sliced)","1\\/2 cup chopped parsley","2 teaspoons sumac","1\\/4 teaspoon salt (or to your liking)","1 teaspoon olive oil","A squeeze of fresh lemon"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cut 5 (16inx12in) parchment paper sheets and set aside. Or buy precut ones.","name":"Cut 5 (16inx12in) parchment paper sheets and set aside. Or buy precut ones.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In the bowl of your food processor add onion and garlic then puree.","name":"In the bowl of your food processor add onion and garlic then puree.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add ground beef with all other spices and yogurt without the olive oil and pulse until it is light in color and forms a paste.","name":"Add ground beef with all other spices and yogurt without the olive oil and pulse until it is light in color and forms a paste.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour the meat mixture into a large bowl, drizzle oil over it, and mix with your hands. This step is done so that the meat mixture is more manageable.","name":"Pour the meat mixture into a large bowl, drizzle oil over it, and mix with your hands. This step is done so that the meat mixture is more manageable.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat oven to 400F.","name":"Preheat oven to 400F.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Divide the mixture into 4 equal parts and oil (or use an oil spray) one sheet of parchment paper.","name":"Divide the mixture into 4 equal parts and oil (or use an oil spray) one sheet of parchment paper.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place another sheet of parchment paper on your cutting board or working surface.","name":"Place another sheet of parchment paper on your cutting board or working surface.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Wet your hands lightly with oil and spread 1\\/4 of the meat mixture over the sheet pressing lightly.","name":"Wet your hands lightly with oil and spread 1\\/4 of the meat mixture over the sheet pressing lightly.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-7"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cover the meat mixture with the oiled parchment sheet (oily part facing the meat mixture) and spread the meat mixture with a rolling pin as thin as you can.","name":"Cover the meat mixture with the oiled parchment sheet (oily part facing the meat mixture) and spread the meat mixture with a rolling pin as thin as you can.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-8"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove the upper parchment paper and roll the meat mixture, keeping the bottom parchment paper on.","name":"Remove the upper parchment paper and roll the meat mixture, keeping the bottom parchment paper on.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-9"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place on a baking sheet and continue with the remaining meat mixture so now you have 4 meat rolls on your baking sheet.","name":"Place on a baking sheet and continue with the remaining meat mixture so now you have 4 meat rolls on your baking sheet.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-10"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"If you are using place the vegetables in the tray and oil with some olive oil and sprinkle with salt and black pepper.","name":"If you are using place the vegetables in the tray and oil with some olive oil and sprinkle with salt and black pepper.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-11"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bake in the oven for 25-30 minutes.","name":"Bake in the oven for 25-30 minutes.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-0-12"},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Meanwhile make the Turkish onion sumac salad:","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"\\u00cen a medium bowl combine ingredients and let it set covered in the fridge until ready to serve.","name":"\\u00cen a medium bowl combine ingredients and let it set covered in the fridge until ready to serve.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-1-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Take the tray out and carefully unroll the sheets and letting them drip all the meat juices inside the baking sheet. Discard the parchment papers.","name":"Take the tray out and carefully unroll the sheets and letting them drip all the meat juices inside the baking sheet. Discard the parchment papers.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-1-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Tear the meat with your hands into chunks and mix them with the meat juices in the pan.","name":"Tear the meat with your hands into chunks and mix them with the meat juices in the pan.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-1-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Optional but highly recommended:","name":"Optional but highly recommended:","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-1-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the pan back into the oven and broil on high for 5-6 minutes or until nicely charred. You can also grill meat pieces on a grill pan.","name":"Place the pan back into the oven and broil on high for 5-6 minutes or until nicely charred. You can also grill meat pieces on a grill pan.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-1-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve as a wrap or platter with onion salad and all the fixes.","name":"Serve as a wrap or platter with onion salad and all the fixes.","url":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#wprm-recipe-55844-step-1-5"}]}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"5","reviewCount":"5"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Very easy to make and incredibly flavourful! I made the Toum recipe you have the first time and the next time I served it with store bought Tzatziki and both were delicious!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Charissa"},"datePublished":"2026-04-23"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I only made the meat and Zoum sauce because the kids didn\\u2019t want the onions or roasted vegetables. I put them in a wrap together with cucumbers and wow!!! It was delicious and the entire family loved all the depth of flavour in the meat and garlic sauce and I was pleased with how easy it was to make. I\\u2019ll definitely be making this again\\u2026probably with the salad and veg for my husband and I too","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Charissa"},"datePublished":"2026-02-02"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I\'ve made this a couple of times.It\'s very good and easy to make. \\ud83d\\ude42","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lindsey"},"datePublished":"2026-01-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is amazing easy recipe, Amira. Thank you so much, I loved it!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Andrea"},"datePublished":"2025-11-21"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I have been seeing this recipe for over a month now and wanted a trusted recipe to try it. It was so delicious and everyone loved it. Now we can have our wrap any day of the week. Thank you. One thing though, it would be so helpful if the recipe had a video too.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"GJ"},"datePublished":"2025-11-21"}],"recipeCategory":["Main Course"],"recipeCuisine":["Turkish"],"suitableForDiet":["https:\\/\\/schema.org\\/HalalDiet"],"keywords":"Doner Kebab, Turkish Doner Kebab, Viral Doner","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"456 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"27 g","proteinContent":"24 g","fatContent":"28 g","saturatedFatContent":"10 g","transFatContent":"1 g","cholesterolContent":"81 mg","sodiumContent":"1243 mg","fiberContent":"2 g","sugarContent":"2 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"14 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\\/\\/amiraspantry.com\\/homemade-doner-kebab\\/"}]}',
